(25, 'branchinfo/img/branch_info1.jpeg', 'img/branch_info_b1.jpeg', 'Chemical Engineering', 'This discipline is all about the chemical conversion of material by economic and environmentally responsible means. As such, Chemical Engineering encompasses diverse fields like petroleum refining, fertilizer technology, processing of food and agricultural products, synthetic food, petrochemicals, synthetic fibres, coal and mineral based industries. and the prevention and control of put environmental pollution.<br>', 'Chemical engineering students study basic and applied sciences. Basic sciences include courses in physics, mathematics, chemistry and biology. Applied sciences include courses in electrical engineering, computing and thermodynamics. Department specific courses or sub disciplines are transport phenomena, reaction engineering, process control and plant design. <br>The basics of computer coding and its implementation in the various sub disciplines as well as experiments showing the basic engineering principles are required for an in depth understanding. Recent advances in the discipline have enabled forays into areas such as biochemical engineering, environmental engineering, nano sciences and nano technology, energy and environment.<br>The technological course components include applied catalysis, drug design, medicinal chemistry, nano materials and nano science, fine and bulk chemicals, green chemical and technological practices. During the course, the students are trained for front line research in interdisciplinary areas, which include materials science, environmental science and molecular biology.<br>', 'Graduates can enter industries like oil, petrochemicals, fertilizers. pharmaceuticals, food processing, semiconductor manufacturing, paper manufacturing, cement manufacturing, personal care and hygiene, water treatment and the power sector. A large number of public sector undertakings (PSUs) that recruit fresh graduates, include Oil and Natural Gas Corporation (ONGC), Indian Oil Corporation (10C), Hindustan Petroleum Corporation Limited (HPCL), Bharat Petroleum Corporation Limited (BPCL), Indian Farmers Fertiliser Cooperative Limited (IFFCO), National Fertilisers Limited (NFL), Rashtriya Chemicals and Fertilizers Ltd. (RCF). Better known private sector recruiters include Reliance, Aditya Birla Chemi cals, Unilever, Tata Honeywell, L&amp;T, EIL, Ranbaxy Dr. Reddys Lab, Britannia, etc. Research organisations like Bhabha Atomic Research Centre (BARC) and Council of Scientific 8: Industrial Research (CSIR) also recruit engineers. <br>', 'Oil and Natural Gas Coorporation (ONGC), Indian Oil Corporation (10C), Hindustan Petroleum Corporation Limited (HPCL), Bharat Petroleum Corporation Limited (BPCL), Indian Farmers Fertiliser Cooperative Limited (IFFCO), National Fertilisers Limited (NFL), Rashtriya Chemicals and Fertilizers Ltd. (RCF)', 'Min entry level salaries 4-6 lakhs', 'IIT Bombay, IIT Kharagpur, IIT Delhi, UICET Chandigarh', 'branchinfo/see_branch_info.php?id=25', 'Chem Chemical Engineering'),
(26, 'branchinfo/', '', 'Computer Science Engineering', 'In India, computer education courses started in IIT Kanpur in the sixties. The first undergraduate program started in IIT Kanpur in 1979. Initially, faculty from electrical, electronics, mathematics and physics taught computer science but today it is a well-established discipline. Computer science and its related discipline (information technology and software engineering) have the most enrollments in the country amongst all the engineering branches. Besides most IITs and NITs, several IIITs also offer this course along with information technology. Strong departments exist at BITS and several other state universities like jadhavpur, Anna University and so on. The discipline got boost in the late nineties because of the Y2K problem in older software across the globe. <br>', 'Computer science and engineering covers theoretical and systems (also called applied) courses. Theoretical computer science includes data structures, algorithm design and analysis, formal languages and automata theory, discrete mathematics, theoretical computer science, etc. the systems side include courses on computer architectures, system and application software (including operating systems, compilers, database management systems, etc.), computer networks, internet technology and mobile computing. Variants of programs abound. Programs named just computer science includes more theoretical courses and fewer system courses while programs named just computer engineering includes more system courses and fewer theoretical courses. Computer science and engineering programs typically offer adequate exposure to both aspects of the discipline.<br>', 'Computer science and engineering programs emphasize logical thinking, analysis and problem solving by breaking them into smaller components. Students learn how to reuse the solutions of smaller problems to solve other larger problems. Acquiring these fundamental skills helps graduates find core jobs like software design as well as fit into other career streams. So from the placement perspective, this discipline offers multiple opportunities. <br><br>India is considered a hub of software services. So, opportunities for such graduates abound. Just that many programs lack quality and as a result, despite a huge no. of vacancies, many graduates do not get placed. Selecting the right college positively, impacts students career options. <br><br>Many companies hire graduates for software design, applications development and some niche areas in networking, internet, mobile computing, and security. Indian companies offering software services also recruit a few such graduates. Most of the jobs in India are in big cities and metros. Many MNCs also recruit for international location, and these positions offer high packages.<br><br>Ample opportunities exist for higher studies and the scope for higher qualified engineers is huge. The sector is currently facing a serious shortage of higher qualified engineers; financial support is more easily available for computer science and engineering than for other engineering disciplines. With software coming into all aspects of our lives, this sector will continue to grow for years to come if not decades.<br>', 'Google, Facebook, Microsoft, TCS, Infosys, Wipro, Cognizant, Accenture', 'Starting salaries for fresh graduates employed for such jobs can range from Rs. 5- 10 lakhs and even higher. Pay packages of Rs. 15-20 lakhs are given to an extremely small no. of gifted students.', 'IIT Bombay, IIT Delhi, IIT Kharagpur, NSIT Delhi, IIIT hyderabad', 'branchinfo/see_branch_info.php?id=26', 'Computer science Engineering CS99 CSE9 Computers'),
(27, 'branchinfo/img/branch_info27.jpeg', 'img/branch_info_b27.jpeg', 'Computer Science Engineering', '&nbsp;In India, computer education courses started in IIT Kanpur in the sixties. The first undergraduate program started in IIT Kanpur in 1979. Initially, faculty from electrical, electronics, mathematics and physics taught computer science but today it is a well-established discipline. Computer science and its related discipline (information technology and software engineering) have the most enrollments in the country amongst all the engineering branches. Besides most IITs and NITs, several IIITs also offer this course along with information technology. Strong departments exist at BITS and several other state universities like jadhavpur, Anna University and so on. The discipline got boost in the late nineties because of the Y2K problem in older software across the globe. <br>', 'Computer science and engineering covers theoretical and systems (also called applied) courses. Theoretical computer science includes data structures, algorithm design and analysis, formal languages and automata theory, discrete mathematics, theoretical computer science, etc. the systems side include courses on computer architectures, system and application software (including operating systems, compilers, database management systems, etc.), computer networks, internet technology and mobile computing. Variants of programs abound. Programs named just computer science includes more theoretical courses and fewer system courses while programs named just computer engineering includes more system courses and fewer theoretical courses. Computer science and engineering programs typically offer adequate exposure to both aspects of the discipline.<br>', 'Computer science and engineering programs emphasize logical thinking, analysis and problem solving by breaking them into smaller components. Students learn how to reuse the solutions of smaller problems to solve other larger problems. Acquiring these fundamental skills helps graduates find core jobs like software design as well as fit into other career streams. So from the placement perspective, this discipline offers multiple opportunities. <br><br>India is considered a hub of software services. So, opportunities for such graduates abound. Just that many programs lack quality and as a result, despite a huge no. of vacancies, many graduates do not get placed. Selecting the right college positively, impacts students career options. <br><br>Many companies hire graduates for software design, applications development and some niche areas in networking, internet, mobile computing, and security. Indian companies offering software services also recruit a few such graduates. Most of the jobs in India are in big cities and metros. Many MNCs also recruit for international location, and these positions offer high packages.<br><br>Ample opportunities exist for higher studies and the scope for higher qualified engineers is huge. The sector is currently facing a serious shortage of higher qualified engineers; financial support is more easily available for computer science and engineering than for other engineering disciplines. With software coming into all aspects of our lives, this sector will continue to grow for years to come if not decades<br>', 'Google, Microsoft, Facebook, TCS, Cognizant, Infosys, Wipro, Amazon', 'Starting salaries for fresh graduates employed for such jobs can range from Rs. 5- 10 lakhs and even higher. Pay packages of Rs. 15-20 lakhs are given to an extremely small no. of gifted students.', 'IIT Bombay, IIT Delhi, IIT Kharagpur, NSIT Delhi, IIIT Hyderabad', 'branchinfo/see_branch_info.php?id=27', 'Computer science Engineering CS99 CSE9'),
(28, 'branchinfo/img/branch_info28.jpeg', 'img/branch_info_b28.jpeg', 'Electronics and Communication Engineering', 'Electronics and communication engineering is a sub- discipline of electrical engineering. Whereas electrical engineering programs conventionally focus on power generation, transmission and distribution, this field of study is concerned with digital circuits, devices, integrated circuits, VLSI design, signal processing, telecommunication, control theory, mobile communication, satellite communication, etc.<br>', 'The program provides students with a sound foundation in electronics devices, circuits and systems, integrated circuits, microelectronics, signal processing, microprocessors, communication systems (both digital and analog), control systems, electromagnetic systems, power electronics, fiber optic communication, instrumentation, etc. the program requires student to gain sufficient maturity in mathematics and physics. <br>&nbsp;There will also be basic courses on electromagnetics, analog circuits, digital circuits and signals and systems. Since all design work today is done using software, it is also essential to understand computer programming. Also, one needs software to control devices and systems and perform analysis.During the program, students acquire some analytical and design skills. Graduates are expected to be familiar with the technical vocabulary associated with these systems and an understanding of their operations.<br>', 'Graduates have job opportunities in electronics, communications and software companies. Opportunities exist both in government sector (including Public Sector Undertaking or the PSUs) and in the private sector. Important government sector recruiters are Bharat electronics ltd. (BEL), Electronics Corporation of India ltd. (ECIL), DRDO, BSNL, C-DoT, etc. Private sector employers are Intel, Samsung, Texas Instruments, Siemens, LG, Nokia, AMD, Motorola, Flextronics, etc. software companies recruiting such engineers are Infosys, Wipro, HCL, TCS, and Accenture.<br><br>Most of the jobs are located in metros and big cities. Bengaluru and Hyderabad lead in the number of such engineers recruited. Delhi (NCR), Mumbai and Chennai are also home to many companies recruiting electronics and communication engineering graduates.<br><br>The opportunities in higher education are enormous in both India and overseas. A Masters degree offers a greater understanding of one areas and specialization. With systems becoming increasingly complex, a second degree is essential if one wants to get into design and analysis. Areas of specialization include micro-electronics and VLSI design, telecommunication systems, photonics, etc.<br>', 'BEL, ECIL, BSNL, TCS, Intel, Samsung, Texas Instruments, Siemens, HCL', 'MNCs offer salaries mostly from Rs. 4-6 lakhs, though some graduates are offered remuneration in excess of Rs. 10 lakhs. A few MNCs occasionally offer placements abroad.', 'IIT Kharagpur, IIT BHU, DTU, NIT Surathkal', 'branchinfo/see_branch_info.php?id=28', 'Electronics and9 Communication Engineering ECE9'),
(29, 'branchinfo/img/branch_info29.jpeg', 'img/branch_info_b29.jpeg', 'Electrical Engineering', 'Electrical Engineering deals with the study and application of electricity, electronics and electromagnetism. The field became a discipline to be studied in universities after the development of communication methods like telegraph and telephones in the 19th century, and also with the commercial generation and distribution of electricity, Darm stadt University was the first university to offer a degree in electrical engineering in 1882. The first department of electrical engineering in India was set up in 1897 in IIT Roorkee.<br>', 'The major sub disciplines of Electrical Engineering are power, control, electronics, signal processing, telecommunication and instrumentation. A program will include courses on physics and mathematics. Other courses are on analogue circuits, digital circuits, introduction to electronics, signal processing, instrumentation, signals and systems, transformers, motors and generators, power systems, control systems, power electronics, electric drives, microprocessors, electromagnetic theory and communication systems.<br>', 'These engineers can work in atomic power plants, hydel or thermal power plants. Job opportunities are ample in both private and public sector like railways, civil aviation, electricity board and utility companies, electrical design and consultancy firms and all types of manufacturing industries.<br><br>After getting a degree in electrical engineering, they can also go into teaching field or join a research lab. Teaching career is also rewarding, with job in top engineering colleges of India offers attractive remuneration packages. The maximum number of jobs is in the government sector.<br>', 'ABB, Bharat Heavy Electronics Limited (BHEL), Bajaj International Private Ltd', 'Min entry level salaries 3-5 lakhs', 'IIT Roorkee, BITS Pilani, VJTI Mumbai', 'branchinfo/see_branch_info.php?id=29', 'Electrical Engineering EE99'),
(30, 'branchinfo/img/branch_info30.jpeg', 'img/branch_info_b30.jpeg', 'Instrumentation Engineering', 'Instrumentation engineering is about managing processes by monitoring and measuring various parameters. Instrumentation engineering design, builds, install and maintain monitoring and measurement devices. Instrumentation ensures that problems are detected early and that processes run efficiently and smoothly.<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;As a concept, Instrumentation per se is as old as human thought- human have always wanted to measure parameters in the world around. But department of Instrumentation engineering are of more recent vintage, emerging in the 1970s and 1980s. It originated as offshoots of electrical engineering. Then gradually, these programs became multi-disciplinary, seeking inputs from mechanical, electronics, computer science, chemical, etc. branches of engineering. Till the 1960s and 1970s Instrumentation was only about measurement so that humans could judge what part of the process to adjust from studying the values of parameters involved. Later, as electrical, electronics and computer science disciplines progressed; controlling processes also became an integral part of in Instrumentation.<br>', 'The curriculum includes deeper mathematics training and exposure to several science courses. It is essential to understand programming languages. Data structures, basic analogue and digital circuits, electronics devices, signal processing, microprocessors, control systems, communication systems, hydraulics and pneumatics, sensors, embedded systems, etc. specific to instrumentation and controls are courses in advanced process control, robotics, and automation, medical instrumentation, virtual instrumentation, neural networks, sensors, networking, etc<br>', 'Typically, graduates of tis discipline are exposed to programming and software design (for the purpose of processing instrumentation data and controlling the system) and are trained to think logically, which enables them to consider a career in software services. Normally, students also do several projects involving hardware. This training helps them to get job in several companies like device manufacturers. Alternatively, they can apply for jobs in companies which recruit electronics and communication engineers. Students are also trained in problem solving and troubleshooting. This enables them to easily switch careers and opt for non- core jobs.<br><br>Almost every industry needs people with an instrumentation background. Industries where accidents could prove costly make it a point to recruit Instrumentation engineers. Hence job opportunities exist in chemical industries, petro-chemical (refineries), steel industry, etc. research labs like DRDO, and organizations like BARC, ISRO, etc. also need Instrumentation engineers.<br><br>There are no large recruiters unlike IT sector and computer science and engineering and electrical engineering disciplines.<br>&nbsp;<br>Higher education is a possibility. However, very few departments dedicated specifically to Instrumentation engineering exist in the top universities in India and overseas. Best is to identify electrical engineering departments with active research in instrumentation, and apply to those places. Start this research in your 4th year itself. Being an applied discipline, a lot of research takes place in the industry.<br>', 'DRDO, ISRO, BARC, Bharat Heavy Electronics Limited (BHEL)', '5-6 Lakhs', 'IIT Kharagpur, NSIT Delhi', 'branchinfo/see_branch_info.php?id=30', 'Instrumentation Engineering ENI9'),
(31, 'branchinfo/img/branch_info31.jpeg', 'img/branch_info_b31.jpeg', 'Mechanical Engineering', 'Mechanical engineering is the discipline that applies the principles of engineering, physics, and materials science for the design, analysis, manufacturing, and maintenance of mechanical systems. It is the branch of engineering that involves the design, production, and operation of machinery. It is one of the oldest&nbsp; and broadest of the engineering disciplines.<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <br>It is considered as an evergreen branch of engineering because opportunities for good mechanical engineer abound irrespective of the fate of economy.<br>', 'Students of mechanical engineering study both the fundamental and applied aspects of thermal and energy systems, robotics, nuclear engineering, and automotive engineering. Other basic courses include statics, dynamics, strength of material, fluid mechanics and design and heat transfer.<br><br>The fundamental subjects of mechanical engineering usually include:<br><br><ul><li>Statics and dynamics</li><li>Strength of materials and solid mechanics</li><li>Materials Engineering</li><li>Thermodynamics, heat transfer, energy conversion, and HVAC </li><li>Internal combustion engine</li><li>Fluid mechanics</li><li>Manufacturing engineering</li><li>Mechanism and Machine design </li><li>Mechatronics, and robotics</li><li>Hydraulics, and pneumatics</li><li>Engineering design and product design</li></ul>', 'Mechanical engineers are always in demand because machines are used in every Industry. Graduates can be absorbed in thermal power plants, automotive industry, heavy engineering industry, nuclear power plants, design firms, hydro power plants, manufacturing companies, railways, airlines, marine industry, oil and petroleum industry.<br><br>The long term prospects for the discipline are very positive as India works toward reviving its manufacturing industry. Fresh graduates get to work in design, production, research, service and maintenance.<br>', 'TATA Motors, Mahindra and Mahindra, Ford, Maruti, ONGC, NTPC, Bharat Heavy Electronics Limited (BHEL)', 'Min entry level salaries 6-8 lakhs', 'IIT Kanpur, NIT Surat, Delhi College of Engineering', 'branchinfo/see_branch_info.php?id=31', 'Mech Mechanical Engineering');
INSERT INTO `branch_review` (`id`, `img`, `b_img`, `clg`, `branch`, `intro`, `infa_labs`, `branch_scope`, `branch_faculty`, `col`, `about`, `url`, `tags`) VALUES
(4, 'branchreview/img/branch_info1.jpeg', 'img/branch_info_b1.jpeg', 'IIT Roorkee', 'Civil Engineering', 'Department was established in the year 1847 bearing the name  <i>Roorkee college of civil engineering </i>which later changes to  <i>Thomson college of civil engineering </i>.\r\n Presently , department offers one U.G. course and one five year dual \r\ndegree programme and P.G. programme in structural engineering &amp; \r\ntwo-year masters in 7 major specialised fields of civil engineering.', 'Civil engineering is taken as one of the core branch. A civil engineer \r\nalways gives an image of roads, flyovers, bridges and structural \r\nconstructions which all means an overall development of the \r\ninfrastructure of a nation. Since being in an IIT is considered as the \r\ntop engineering study a student can acquire in India. So department \r\nprovides each and every possible facility and laboratory to meet the \r\nrecent developing and overgrowing needs of civil engineers.<br><br><p>LABS FOR DIFFERENT FIELDS</p>\r\n<p><i>1. Structural Engineering</i>: Building Material testing Lab<br></p><p>\r\n2. Geomatics: Cartography Lab- I &amp; II<br></p><p>\r\n3. Geotechnical Engineering: Soil Mechanics lab<br></p><p>\r\n4. Transportation Engineering: Material testing Lab<br></p><p>\r\n5. Environmental Engineering: Air Pollution lab\r\n</p><p><em>Facilities:</em></p>\r\n<p>Environmental Engineering:</p>\r\n<ul><li>&nbsp;Air Samplers</li><li>&nbsp;Flame Photometer</li><li>&nbsp;Gas&nbsp; Chromatography Mass Spectrometry( known as GC-MS)</li><li>&nbsp;Ion-analyzer</li><li>&nbsp;Noise monitor</li></ul>\r\n<p><em>Geotechnical Engineering :</em></p>\r\n<ul><li>&nbsp;Large scale direct shear test facility (sample size 1.5m x 1.5m and 0.7m x.7)</li><li>&nbsp;Motorised direct</li><li>&nbsp;shear and vane shear testing device</li><li>&nbsp;Multi unit consolidation</li><li>&nbsp;Device</li></ul>\r\n<p><em>Geomatics Engineering :</em> Digital Compass</p><br>', 'Civil Engineering students gain a diverse set of skills during their \r\ntraining. Civil engineers dont just design structures and then \r\nsupervise their construction, but they need to be able to understand how\r\n infrastructure intersects human lives, where one builds an underpass on\r\n a highway is not simply a technical issue. Performing the cost-benefit \r\nanalysis of different techniques and materials, etc., is an integral \r\npart of this profession. Automation is also becoming important. Such \r\ndiverse training helps civil engineers grow quickly in their profession \r\nand also allows them to switch careers after gaining some experience. \r\nWhile the traditional jobs remain linked to construction, while the \r\ntraditional jobs remain linked to construction, opportunities are \r\nemerging in the areas of planning (city, infrastructure, transportation,\r\n etc.), safety, environment, and so on.', '<p>Area of perfection of Faculty/ Department:</p>\r\n<ul><li>&nbsp;Structural Engineering like Concrete, Steel,</li><li>&nbsp;Geomatics: Surveying &amp; GPS and&nbsp; Remote Sensing and also &nbsp;Land Cover Mapping,</li><li>&nbsp;Geotechnical Engineering: interaction of&nbsp; Geotechnical Engineering ,</li><li>&nbsp;Transportation Engineering: like &nbsp;Traffic Engineering</li><li>&nbsp;Environmental Engineering: example &nbsp;Solid Waste Management.</li><li>&nbsp;Hydraulic Engineering: &nbsp;as Surface water quality management</li></ul>', '<p><strong><i>Collaborations/Tie-ups</i></strong>:</p>\r\n<ul><li>&nbsp;Environmental Engineering : Development of effective decentralized</li><li>&nbsp;wastewater treatment system for rural communities.</li><li>&nbsp;Geomatics Engineering : Reduction of Hyperspectral dimensionality</li><li>Remote Sensing Data.</li><li>&nbsp;Hydraulic Engineering : Energy Dissipation on Block Ramps</li><li>&nbsp;Transportation Engineering : Influence of Moisture States of Recycled Aggregates for use in Pavement Quality Concrete.</li></ul>', 'Today, the scope of civil engineering includes the study of construction\r\n techniques, structures of various forms such as buildings, roads, \r\nbridges, sea ports and airports and other infrastructure works. Civil \r\nengineers also deal with systems that are linked to infrastructure, such\r\n as water resources, transportation, environmental engineering etc. ', 'branchreview/see_branch_review.php?id=4', 'IIT9 Roorkee IITR Civil Engineering '),
(5, 'branchreview/img/branch_info5.jpeg', 'img/branch_info_b5.jpeg', 'NIT Agartala', 'Chemical Engineering', '<p>This department has been set up in the academic year of 2009-10 with sanctioned intake capacity of sixty students at the undergraduate level .Loads of research work is being carried out within the department. In order to ensure unhindered development of department along with the academic performance an Industrial Advisory Committee is formed which would help the students in project management, entrepreneurship and in learning new technology.</p>', '<p><br />The department comprises of following labs:<br /><br />&bull; Fluid Mechanics Laboratory<br />&bull; Mechanical Operation Laboratory<br />&bull; Heat Transfer Laboratory<br />&bull; Mass Transfer Laboratory<br />&bull; Fuel &amp; Combustion Laboratory<br />&bull; Reaction Engineering Laboratory<br />&bull; Computer Laboratory<br />&bull; Process Control and Instrumentation Laboratory<br /><br />Presently library owns around 180 text books, research articles as hardcopy and over 200 research articles, books as softcopy.</p>', '<p>Placement Overview<br /><br />Chemical is one of the core branches and being set up initially regular efforts are being put in to ensure its developments. Hence many companies come to recruit students and offer considerably good package.</p>\r\n<p>Job/Placement &amp; Business Opportunities<br /><br />&nbsp;Placement Overview<br /><br />Chemical is one of the core branches and being set up initially regular efforts are being put in to ensure its developments. Hence many companies come to recruit students and offer considerably good package.<br /><br />* Name of Companies visiting campus for recruitment&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />1. ABCI&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br /><br />2. Capgemini<br /><br />3. IOCL&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br /><br />4. Gammon India<br /><br />5. Ambuja Cement<br /><br />6. L &amp; T Ramboll &nbsp;<br /><br />7. ITD Cementation&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br /><br />8. ERa&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br /><br />9. Manav Rachna International University<br /><br />10.Simplex<br /><br />&nbsp; Average Package: 3.5<br /><br />&nbsp; Maximum Package: 6<br /><br />&nbsp; % Placement: Since the department is newly set up efforts are being put in to ensure placement of students. The percentage placement is considerably good.<br /><br />&nbsp;Branch Scenario<br /><br />* Further Studies/Research Scope<br /><br />One can hope for getting placed in PSU&rsquo;s through GATE scorecard. Also one can opt for CAT if wants to pursue MBA. Another option is administrative services.<br /><br />* Course Curriculum-Are Courses upgrade as per new technology<br /><br />With regular research going on in every field and new results being developed every now and then, the teachers keep a track of all recent developments and also bring the same in notice of students.</p>', '<p><br />Faculties are highly qualified holding PHD/M.tech.<br />8 Assistant Prof, 2 technical staff and 1 office assistant are there to cater the students.<br /><br />Professors are working on national level projects like:-<br />1. Quantification of butanol synthesis using elementary modes and sensitivity analysis.<br />2. Engineering Zymomonas mobilis for the efficient production of biofuels from lignocellulosic biomass.<br />3. Modernization of Fuel and combustion Lab.<br />4. Developing an alternative route for stabilizing and processing of natural latex.<br />5. Developing an off-grid hybrid power system for remote communities of North Eastern India.</p>', '<p>The department aims to collaborate with various industries and institutes to help the students achieve the pinnacle.</p>', '', 'branchreview/see_branch_review.php?id=5', 'NIT9 Agartala Chem Chemical Engineering '),
(6, 'branchreview/img/branch_info6.jpeg', 'img/branch_info_b6.jpeg', 'NIT Agartala', 'Chemical Engineering', '<p>This department has been set up in the academic year of 2009-10 with sanctioned intake capacity of sixty students at the undergraduate level. Loads of research work is being carried out within the department. In order to ensure unhindered development of department along with the academic performance an Industrial Advisory Committee is formed which would help the students in project management, entrepreneurship and in learning new technology.</p>', '<p>The department comprises of following labs:<br /><br />&bull; Fluid Mechanics Laboratory<br />&bull; Mechanical Operation Laboratory<br />&bull; Heat Transfer Laboratory<br />&bull; Mass Transfer Laboratory<br />&bull; Fuel &amp; Combustion Laboratory<br />&bull; Reaction Engineering Laboratory<br />&bull; Computer Laboratory<br />&bull; Process Control and Instrumentation Laboratory<br /><br />Presently library owns around 180 text books, research articles as hardcopy and over 200 research articles, books as softcopy.</p>', '<p><strong>&nbsp;Placement Overview</strong><br /><br />Chemical is one of the core branches and being set up initially regular efforts are being put in to ensure its developments. Hence many companies come to recruit students and offer considerably good package.<br /><br /></p>\r\n<p><strong>Name of Companies visiting campus for recruitment&nbsp;</strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <br /><br />2. Capgemini<br /><br />3. IOCL&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br /><br />4. Gammon India<br /><br />5. Ambuja Cement<br /><br />6. L &amp; T Ramboll &nbsp;<br /><br />7. ITD Cementation&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br /><br />8. ERa&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br /><br />9. Manav Rachna International University<br /><br />10.Simplex<br /><br />&nbsp;<strong> Average Package:</strong> 3.5 lpa<br /><br /><strong>&nbsp; Maximum Package</strong>: 6 lpa<br /><br /><strong>Percentage Placement</strong>: Since the department is newly set up efforts are being put in to ensure placement of students. The percentage placement is considerably good.<br /><br /><strong>Branch Scenario</strong></p>\r\n<p>* Further Studies/Research Scope<strong><br /><br /></strong>One can hope for getting placed in PSU&rsquo;s through GATE scorecard. Also one can opt for CAT if wants to pursue MBA. Another option is administrative services.<br /><br />* Course Curriculum-Are Courses upgrade as per new technology<br /><br />With regular research going on in every field and new results being developed every now and then, the teachers keep a track of all recent developments and also bring the same in notice of students.</p>', '<p><br />Faculties are highly qualified holding PHD/M.tech.<br />8 Assistant Prof, 2 technical staff and 1 office assistant are there to cater the students.<br /><br />Professors are working on national level projects like:-<br />1. Quantification of butanol synthesis using elementary modes and sensitivity analysis.<br />2. Engineering Zymomonas mobilis for the efficient production of biofuels from lignocellulosic biomass.<br />3. Modernization of Fuel and combustion Lab.<br />4. Developing an alternative route for stabilizing and processing of natural latex.<br />5. Developing an off-grid hybrid power system for remote communities of North Eastern India.</p>', '<p>The department aims to collaborate with various industries and institutes to help the students achieve the pinnacle.</p>', '<p>&nbsp;Conferences/Seminars<br /><br />Various workshops and seminars are organised within the department to bring the students closer to evolving technology and build their interest in doing research work.</p>', 'branchreview/see_branch_review.php?id=6', 'NIT9 Agartala Chem Chemical Engineering '),
(7, 'branchreview/img/branch_info7.jpeg', 'img/branch_info_b7.jpeg', 'NIT Agartala', 'Civil Engineering', '<p>The department was established in 1965 with the motive of educating students and encouraging them to do research work.The department provides students with the fundamental knowledge and problem-solving skills in the field of Civil Engineering required for a fulfilling career and to create and disseminate knowledge to improve Civil Engineering research, education, and practice.</p>', '<p>Education to students through high-tech labs such as:<br /><br />1. Soil Mechanics Laboratory<br />2. Structural Engineering Laboratory<br />3. Concrete Laboratory<br />4. Transportation Engineering Laboratory<br />5. Environmental Engineering Laboratory<br />6. Solid Mechanics Laboratory<br />7. Surveying Laboratory<br />8. Engineering Geology Laboratory<br />9. Civil Engineering Computer Laboratory<br />10. Water Resources Engineering Laboratory</p>', '<p><strong>Branch Scenario</strong><br /><br />At NITA various projects are being going on and students are encouraged to come up with more projects. For students interested in pursuing management degree can opt for CAT and for Gate in case of mtech aspirants. After Mtech one can pursue for doctorate for research in specific fields. <br /><br />Course Curriculum-Are Courses upgrade as per new technology<br /><br />A complete review of course is done regularly and is also done through feedback forms filled by students. Course in accordance with evolving technology is being taught in classroom sessions.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Placement overview:</strong><br /><br />Most of the core companies visit the campus and offer a considerably good package for a fresher.&nbsp; <br />Name of Companies visiting campus for recruitment<br /><br />&nbsp;L &amp; T ECC<br />&nbsp;ITDC<br />&nbsp;Mu Sigma<br />&nbsp;Capgemini India<br />&nbsp;Infosys<br />&nbsp;Larsen and Tubro Ltd<br />&nbsp;Gammon India<br />&nbsp;JSPL<br />&nbsp;Indian Army<br />&nbsp;Navy<br /><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <strong>Average Package</strong>: 3lpa<br /><strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Maximum Package</strong>: 6lpa<br /><br /><strong>% Placement</strong>: Civil is one of the oldest branches at NITA and has very good percentage of placement.<br /><br /></p>', '<p>Faculties are highly qualified holding PHD/M.tech.</p>\r\n<p>2 professors, almost 25 Assistant Professors, 2 technical staff and 1 office assistant.<br /><br />Presently these organizations are in collaboration with Dept.:-<br />&bull; S &amp; T, India<br />&bull; AICTE<br />&bull; Science &amp; Technology Dept. Govt of Tripura.<br /><br />Faculties have presented various publications in National conferences, IEEE, IITs.</p>', '<p><br />NIT Agartala aims to tie up with many industries and at the same time with some foreign universities to help in overall development of students.</p>', '<p><br />Branch Events/Conferences<br /><br />Many conferences are organized at NIT-Agartala to bring the students closer to evolving technology and also encourage them to do research.</p>', 'branchreview/see_branch_review.php?id=7', 'NIT9 Agartala Civil Engineering '),
(8, 'branchreview/img/branch_info8.jpeg', 'img/branch_info_b8.jpeg', 'NIT Agartala', 'Computer Science Engineering', '<p>The department of Computer Science and Engineering came into existence in 1999 since then the department is known to have achieved glories. Both UG and PG courses are available at department in CSE.The students are provided knowledge to understand the fundamental of basic sciences and humanities, inter disciplinary knowledge, innovation, creative problem-solving abilities, intellectually honest and professional ethics, capacity for team work in interdisciplinary, national and international environment</p>', '<p><br />The institute has Intel Pentium Based Personal Computers installed in laboratories which are connected to 24 hour internet facility. All the hostels and labs are well connected with internet.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '<p><strong>Placement Overview</strong><br /><br />CS being one of the highly paid branches coupled with that the college is a NIT results in top companies visiting the campus. <br /><br /><strong>Name of Companies visiting campus for recruitment</strong><br /><br />Some of the companies that visit NITA for CS branch are listed below:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br /><br />Capgemini<br /><br />HCL<br /><br />Rancore Technologies<br /><br />Samsung India Software Operations<br /><br />Samsung R&amp;D<br /><br />Polaris Software<br /><br />Drishti Soft<br /><br />Mu Sigma<br /><br />Virtuse <br /><br />&nbsp; <strong>Average Package:</strong> 4.5lpa<br /><br /><strong>&nbsp; Maximum Package:</strong> 7.2lpa<br /><br />&nbsp;<strong> % Placement:</strong> CS being one of the highly paid branches has good placement ratio.<br /><br /><strong>Branch Scenario</strong><br /><br />&nbsp; <strong>Further Studies/Research Scope</strong><br /><br />Computer Science enthusiasts and graduates are sometimes placed in sectors like Information Technology, System management and Banking. Most frequently students prefer investing in their own start-ups. Options like Gate and Cat are open for students who want to pursue their masters. <br /><br />Course Curriculum-Are Courses upgrade as per new technology<br /><br />With evolving technology in computers course upgradation is done on a regular basis.</p>', '<p>Faculties are highly qualified holding PHD/M.tech..<br /><br />Almost 20 Assistant Professors, 5 Technical Staff are presently working.</p>', '<p><br />The Department aims at collaborating with leading industries to facilitate research work.</p>', '<p><strong>Conferences/Seminars</strong><br /><br />Various conferences are organized at department to encourage learning in students.</p>', 'branchreview/see_branch_review.php?id=8', 'NIT9 Agartala Computer Science Engineering CS99 CSE9 Computers'),
(9, 'branchreview/img/branch_info9.jpeg', 'img/branch_info_b9.jpeg', 'NIT Agartala', 'Electrical Engineering', '<p><br />Electrical Engineering department came into existence since the inception of Tripura Engineering College (TEC) An 8 semester Btech course in Electrical Engineering with batch strength of 90 is offered at NITA. Also a 4-semester Mtech course in Power Electronics &amp; Drives, Power System Engineering and Instrumentation Engineering with strength of 10 for each specialization is offered. Ph.D. is provided in Instrumentation, Power System, Power Quality, Renewable Energy etc.</p>', '<p>The department comprises of following labs:<br /><br />Basic Electrical Engineering Laboratory<br />Electrical Machines Laboratory<br />Electrical Measurement Laboratory<br />Control System Laboratory<br />Instrumentation Laboratory<br />High Voltage Engineering Laboratory<br />Microprocessor Laboratory<br />Power Electronics &amp; Electrical Drives Laboratory<br />Computer Programming &amp; Simulation Laboratory<br />Process Control &amp; Instrumentation Lab<br />Optics Lab<br />Embedded System Lab<br />Job/Placement &amp; Business Opportunities</p>', '<p><strong>Placement Overview</strong><br />One of the highly paid branches and has a lot of scope in terms of future growth. Also a large number of companies visit the campus regularly to hire electrical engineers <br /><br /><strong>Name of Companies visiting campus for recruitment</strong><br /><br />Some of the companies that visit NITA for Electrical branch are listed below:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br /><br />1. Larsen and Toubro Ltd<br /><br />2. Infosys<br /><br />3. Virtuse<br /><br />4. ABCI<br /><br />5. Finisar<br /><br />6. Mu Sigma<br /><br />7. Capgemini<br /><br />8. IOCL<br /><br />9. HCL<br /><br />10. JSPL <br /><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;<strong> Average Package:</strong> 5lpa<br />&nbsp;&nbsp; <strong>Maximum Package:</strong> 9.2lpa<br /><br /><strong>% Placement</strong>: Most of the students get placed and % placement is quite good.<br />Branch Scenario<br /><br /><strong>&nbsp;Further Studies/Research Scope</strong><br />Options like Gate and Cat are open for students who want to pursue their masters. <br /><br />Course Curriculum-Are Courses upgrade as per new technology<br /><br />With evolving technology in electronic media course upgradation is done on a regular basis.</p>', '<p>Faculties are highly qualified holding PHD/M.tech. The department comprises of 2 Professors and almost 20 Assistant Professors. Teachers are admirable with the superior teaching skills. They contribute their best in studies and helps&nbsp; gaining productive brain work. They keep on organizing latest seminars and conferences in college.<br /><br />Research in the following areas is being carried out at the department:<br /><br />Nano-wire FET, Nano-wire Solar Cell, Hetero junction nano-wire, Digital Image Processing, Low Power VLSI Design and Testing.</p>', '<p><br />Efforts are being put in to tie up with industries and foreign universities to ensure a brighter future for students.</p>', '<p>Conferences/Seminars<br /><br />Various conferences are held on evolving technology to bring forth the students various research arenas and developments.</p>', 'branchreview/see_branch_review.php?id=9', 'NIT9 Agartala Electrical Engineering EE99 '),
(10, 'branchreview/img/branch_info10.jpeg', 'img/branch_info_b10.jpeg', 'NIT Agartala', 'Mechanical Engineering', '<p>The Department of Mechanical Engineering at NITA offers both UG and PG courses in Mechanical Engineering where students are encouraged to acquire knowledge facilities with an integrated thinking about education research &amp; development, application and training, interdisciplinary knowledge, innovation, creative and problem-solving abilities, intellectually honesty and professional ethics, capacity for teamwork in interdisciplinary, national and international environment</p>', '<p>The department comprises of following labs:<br /><br />Mechanical Computer Lab.<br />Vibration Lab.<br />Mechanical Measurement and Metrology Lab.<br />Refrigeration &amp; Airconditioning Lab.<br />Computational Lab-1<br />Strength of Material Lab.<br />Tribology Lab.<br />FMS (Flexible Manufacturing System) Lab.<br />Thermal Power Lab.<br />Wind Tunnel <br />IC Engine Lab.<br />CAD Lab.<br />Fluid Mechanics Lab.<br />Heat Transfer Lab.<br />CNC Machine Lab.<br />Computational Lab-2</p>', '<p>Job/Placement &amp; Business Opportunities<br /><br />&nbsp;<strong> Placement Overview</strong><br /><br />Mechanical being one of the oldest branches has seen a large scale of growth over years in terms of companies visiting the campus and in terms of package offered.<br /><br />&nbsp;<strong> Name of Companies visiting campus for recruitment</strong><br /><br />Some of the companies that visit NITA for Mechanical branch are listed below:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br /><br />TATA Motors<br />Capgemini<br />IOCL<br />Maruti Suzuki<br />TATA Autocomp<br />SKF<br />Subros<br />Stone India<br />JSPL<br />Voltas<br />&nbsp; <strong>Average Package:</strong> 4lpa<br /><br /><strong>&nbsp; Maximum Package:</strong> 6lpa<br /><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;<strong> % Placement:</strong> The department has a good placement ratio since it was established long before and has experienced loads of development over years.<br /><br /><strong>Branch Scenario</strong><br /><br />&nbsp;&nbsp; <strong>Further Studies/Research Scope</strong><br /><br />If one wants to pursue further studies loads of doors are open like Mtech, MBA and IAS with each field having its own pros and cons. <br /><br />Course Curriculum-Are Courses upgrade as per new technology<br /><br />With evolving technology in machines course upgradation is done on a regular basis.</p>', '<p>Faculties are highly qualified holding PHD/M.tech from various reputed institutes. The department has 1 professor, 23 Assistant professors working intermittently.<br />Faculties have presented various publications in National conferences, IEEE, IITs.<br />Research is going on the following subjects:-<br /><br />Study of Heat Transfer, Microstructure and Mechanical Properties in Friction and Friction stir welding.</p>', '<p><br />With Universities (Indian/Foreign): The department aims at collaborating with various foreign universities to offer the best of knowledge to students. </p>', '<p>Conferences/Seminars<br /><br />A large number of conferences are organized to encourage the students to do research in various fields and help them strengthen their concepts.</p>', 'branchreview/see_branch_review.php?id=10', 'NIT9 Agartala Mech Mechanical Engineering '),
(11, 'branchreview/img/branch_info11.jpeg', 'img/branch_info_b11.jpeg', 'NIT Agartala', 'Electronics and Communication Engineering', '<p>Electronics and Communication Department at NITA came into existence in 2007 .VVLSI, Nano-electronics, Fabrication and Characterization of Quantum Effect Devices, Advance Microwave Electronics, Non-Linear Control System, Modern era of Communication are few of the courses that department offers. </p>', '<p>The department comprises of following labs:<br /><br />Analog Electronics &amp; IC Lab<br />Communication Systems Lab<br />Digital Electronics &amp; Microprocessor Lab<br />Digital Signal Processing (DSP) Lab<br />Microwave Engineering Lab<br />RF Communication Lab<br />VLSI Lab<br />Micro &amp; Nano Lab</p>', '<p><strong>&nbsp;Placement Overview</strong><br /><br />ECE being next to CS in terms of popularity and demand is another highly paid branches. <br /><br /><strong>&nbsp; Name of Companies visiting campus for recruitment</strong><br /><br />Some of the companies that visit NITA for ECE branch are listed below:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br /><br />1. Samsung India Software Operations&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br /><br />2. Mu Sigma&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br /><br />3. Virtuse<br /><br />4. Capgemini India<br /><br />5. Infosys<br /><br />6. Tech Mahindra Satyam <br /><br />7. HCL<br /><br />8. Power Wave<br /><br />9. Rancore Technologies<br /><br />10. Huawei Technologies <br /><br />&nbsp;<strong> Average Package:</strong> 5lpa<br /><br /><strong>&nbsp; Maximum Package:</strong> 7.2lpa<br /><br /><strong>&nbsp; % Placement:</strong> The department has considerable goof percentage ratio. Mostly all average students get placed.<br /><br /><strong>Branch Scenario</strong><br /><br /><strong>&nbsp;&nbsp; Further Studies/Research Scope</strong><br /><br />A branch as good as ECE always hold the option of further studies within it. A student who wants to pursue further studies has various doors open in front of him keeping in mind that he has pursued his/her B.tech from an institute of utmost reputation of an NIT. <br /><br />Course Curriculum-Are Courses upgrade as per new technology<br /><br />With evolving technology in media of communication course upgradation is done on a regular basis.</p>', '<p><br />Faculties are highly qualified, holding PHD/M.tech from various reputed institutes. The department comprises of 1 Professor, more than 15 Assistance professors and 1 technical staff.<br />Faculties have presented various publications in National conferences, IEEE, IITs etc.</p>', '<p><br />The Department aims at collaborating with various industries and universities to ensure development of department and students.</p>', '<p>Various conferences on communication systems are being organized on a regular basis to enhance the knowledge of students.</p>', 'branchreview/see_branch_review.php?id=11', 'NIT9 Agartala ECE9 Electronics and9 Communication Engineering '),
(12, 'branchreview/img/branch_info12.jpeg', 'img/branch_info_b12.jpeg', 'NIT Agartala', 'Instrumentation Engineering', '<p><br />The department was established in 2009-2010 with batch strength of 60 students in UG level.</p>', '<p>Presently the department has an Electronics Lab equipped with digital machines working on latest technologies.</p>', '<p><strong>Placement Overview</strong><br /><br />Being one of the recently developed branches it is highly in demand from companies and it holds a brighter future ahead in terms of placement and package.<br /><br /><strong>&nbsp;&nbsp; Name of Companies visiting campus for recruitment</strong><br /><br />Some of the companies that visit NITA for Electronics and Instrumentation Engineering branch are listed below:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br /><br />Mu Sigma<br /><br />Finisar<br /><br />Capgemini<br /><br />Infosys<br /><br />Larsen &amp; Toubro Ltd <br /><br /><strong>&nbsp;&nbsp; Average Package:</strong> 5lpa<br /><br /><strong>&nbsp;&nbsp; Maximum Package</strong>: 9.2lpa<br /><br /><strong>&nbsp;&nbsp; % Placement</strong>: The department has an average placement ratio and the ratio is expected to increase in forthcoming years.<br /><br /><strong>Branch Scenario</strong><br /><br /><strong>&nbsp;&nbsp; Further Studies/Research Scope</strong><br /><br />If one wants to pursue further studies loads of doors are open like Mtech, MBA and IAS with each field having its own pros and cons. <br /><br />Course Curriculum-Are Courses upgrade as per new technology<br /><br />With evolving technology course upgradation is done on a regular basis.</p>', '<p>Faculties are highly qualified holding PHD/M.tech from various reputed institutes.<br />7 Assistant professors and 4 lab assistants are there in department to help students in every possible way.<br />Faculties have presented various publications in National conferences, IEEE, IITs.</p>', '<p>The department aims at collaborating with various foreign universities and industries to offer the best of knowledge to students since it is established recently.</p>', '<p><br />Conferences/Seminars<br /><br />A large number of conferences are organized to encourage the students to do research in various fields and help them strengthen their concepts.</p>', 'branchreview/see_branch_review.php?id=12', 'NIT9 Agartala Instrumentation Engineering ENI9 '),
(13, 'branchreview/img/branch_info13.jpeg', 'img/branch_info_b13.jpeg', 'NIT Allahabad', 'Chemical Engineering ', '<p>Both Btech and PhD programmes are being offered in Chemical Engineering at institute. The department helps the students in pursuing their goals and helps them out of all the dilemmas regarding their future prospective. The department aims at providing quality education complemented by professional skills including communication to the students.&nbsp;</p>', '<p>Knowledge without practical knowledge is incomplete. So in order to ensure that students are practically strong various laboratories are there in department.</p>\r\n<p><strong>The department comprises of following labs:</strong></p>\r\n<p>1. Mass Transfer laboratory<br />2. Chemical Technology laboratory<br />3. Environmental laboratory<br />4. Process Dynamics &amp; Control laboratory<br />5. FPM laboratory<br />6. Chemical Reaction Engineering laboratory</p>', '<p><strong>Placement Overview</strong></p>\r\n<p>The department experiences loads of companies coming every year and awarding considerable packages.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Name of Companies visiting campus for recruitment</strong></p>\r\n<p>Some of the companies that visit MNNIT for Chemical Engineering branch are listed below:</p>\r\n<p>1. Uttam Galva Steel</p>\r\n<p>2. HPCL-Mittal Energy Ltd. (HMEL)</p>\r\n<p>3. BPCL</p>\r\n<p>4. ReInspire Tech</p>\r\n<p>5. Aditya Birla Chemicals</p>\r\n<p>6. Binani Cements</p>\r\n<p>7. JSW Steel Ltd</p>\r\n<p>8. Saint Gobain</p>\r\n<p>9. Reliance Industries ltd.</p>\r\n<p>10. Cairn India=</p>\r\n<p><strong>Average Package:</strong> 4.22</p>\r\n<p><strong>Maximum Package:</strong> 5.5</p>\r\n<p><strong>Percentage Placement:</strong> Out of 34 eligible students 17 were placed.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Branch Scenario</strong></p>\r\n<p><em>Further Studies/Research Scope:</em><br />One can hope for getting placed in PSU&rsquo;s through GATE scorecard. Also one can opt for CAT if he/she wants to pursue MBA. Another option is administrative services.Course Curriculum-Are Courses upgrade as per new technology.</p>\r\n<p>With regular research going on in every field and new results being developed every now and then, the teachers keep a track of all recent developments and also bring the same in notice of students.</p>', '<p>The department comprises of 1 professors, 1 associate professors, 8 assistant professors having deep knowledge of the subject.</p>\r\n<p><strong>The research interests of the department include:</strong></p>\r\n<p>1. Advance Separation processes</p>\r\n<p>2. Convective heat transfer</p>\r\n<p>3. Multiphase Flow and Heat Transfer</p>\r\n<p>4. Chemical Reaction Engineering</p>\r\n<p>5. Process Modeling and Simulation</p>\r\n<p>6. Computational Fluid Dynamics</p>\r\n<p>7. Boiling &amp; condensation.</p>\r\n<p>8. Process Control &amp; Optimization</p>\r\n<p>9. Membrane Separation</p>\r\n<p>10. Polymer Technology</p>\r\n<p>11. Environmental Engineering</p>\r\n<p>12. Industrial Waste treatment &amp; recycle</p>\r\n<p>13. Industrial Pollution abatement</p>\r\n<p>14. Hydrocarbon Engineering</p>\r\n<p>15. Catalytic reactions</p>\r\n<p>16. Nanotechnology</p>\r\n<p>17. CAD of Process Equipment.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Professors are playing roles in:-</strong><br />A. International Journals<br />B. International Conferences <br />C. National Journal<br />D. National Conferences</p>', '<p>The department aims to collaborate with various industries and institutes to help the students achieve the pinnacle.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '', 'branchreview/see_branch_review.php?id=13', ' NIT9 Allahabad Chem Chemical Engineering '),
(14, 'branchreview/img/branch_info14.jpeg', 'img/branch_info_b14.jpeg', 'NIT Allahabad ', 'Civil Engineering ', '<p>The Department of Civil Engineering at NIT-Allahabad offers a 4 year Btech degree in Civil Engineering and also post graduateNIT Allahabad Civil Engineering courses in Structural, Environmental and Geotechnical Engineering.Department offers part time course as well in Computer Aided Design.A strong foundation is built in students through courses like Concrete and Steel Structures, Geotechnical Engineering, Environmental Engineering, Transportation Engineering, Irrigation Engineering and Computer Application. The course curriculum also comprises of open elective subjects like Soil Properties, Simulation, Rock Mechanics, Ecology and Operations Research. Along with theoretical knowledge practical knowledge is imparted to students with the assistance of well-equipped laboratories. </p>', '<p>Large number of efforts is being put in to give the best of education to students through high-tech labs and a healthy environment.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>CAD Lab</li>\r\n<li>Environmental Engineering</li>\r\n<li>Geotechnical Engineering Lab</li>\r\n<li>Geoinformatics</li>\r\n<li>Structural Engineering Lab</li>\r\n<li>Surveying</li>\r\n<li>Transportation Engineering Lab</li>\r\n</ul>', '<p><strong>Placement Overview</strong></p>\r\n<p>Keeping the reputation of the institute in mind and it&rsquo;s All India Ranking students are offered placements at reputed firms and a considerable good package. Almost all the core companies visit the campus (roughly 30) along with other non-core companies comprising of consultancy firms.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Name of Companies visiting campus for recruitment:</strong></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li style=\\"text-align: justify;\\">Theme Engineering Service Pvt. Ltd.</li>\r\n<li style=\\"text-align: justify;\\">Rays Power Infra</li>\r\n<li style=\\"text-align: justify;\\">Nippon Koei India</li>\r\n<li style=\\"text-align: justify;\\">Reinspire Tech</li>\r\n<li style=\\"text-align: justify;\\">Yashi Consulting</li>\r\n<li style=\\"text-align: justify;\\">Saint Gobain</li>\r\n<li style=\\"text-align: justify;\\">JSW Steel Ltd.</li>\r\n<li style=\\"text-align: justify;\\">Analytics Quotient</li>\r\n<li style=\\"text-align: justify;\\">Bhel</li>\r\n<li style=\\"text-align: justify;\\">NTPC</li>\r\n<li style=\\"text-align: justify;\\">TCS</li>\r\n<li style=\\"text-align: justify;\\">HIndalco</li>\r\n<li style=\\"text-align: justify;\\">DS Constructions</li>\r\n<li style=\\"text-align: justify;\\">Reliance Industries</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p><br /> <strong>Average Package:</strong> 4.23<br /> <strong>Maximum Package:</strong> 9.85</p>\r\n<p><strong>Percentage Placement:</strong> Out of 61 eligible student 48 got placed</p>\r\n<p><strong>Branch Scenario</strong></p>\r\n<p>In case you are aiming to go for research projects at mnnit various projects are being going on and students are encouraged to come up with more projects. For students interested in pursuing management degree can opt for CAT and for Gate in case of mtech aspirants. After Mtech one can pursue for doctorate for research in specific fields.</p>\r\n<p>A complete review of course is done regularly and is also done through feedback forms filled by students. Course in accordance with evolving technology is being taught in classroom sessions. </p>', '<p>The branch has 28 teaching faculties with 10 Professors and 18 Assistant Professors pursuing knowledge from various fields like transportational engineering, geotechnical engineering, Soil mechanics and foundation engineering, earthquake engineering and many more other fields of interests. Research is being carried out on following topics: Environmental Engineering, Geotechnology, Structural Engineering, CAD in Civil Engineering, Transportation Engineering and Geoinformatics. </p>', '<p>NIT Allahabad has tie ups from several foreign universities such as University of Berkellly, Helsinki university of technology. Apart from that, several industries are also tied up. The tie ups with IEEE and TEQIP are notable.</p>', '', 'branchreview/see_branch_review.php?id=14', ' NIT9 Allahabad Civil Engineering '),
(15, 'branchreview/img/branch_info15.jpeg', 'img/branch_info_b15.jpeg', 'NIT Allahabad', ' Computer Science Engineering', '<p>The Department offers UG, PG and doctorate courses in Computer Science. With passing years curriculum has evolved with changing technology. Eminent faculty coupled with well-equipped laboratories makes NIT-Allahabad an apt institute for future Computer Engineers. </p>', '<p>Well Equipped laboratories are a necessity for any branch. Regular maintenance is being done in order to ensure latest technologies at the footsteps of students.</p>\r\n<p><strong>The department comprises of following labs:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Image Processing</li>\r\n<li>Information Security</li>\r\n<li>Microprocessor and Computer Architecture</li>\r\n<li>Distributed Computing</li>\r\n<li>P.G. Lab</li>\r\n<li>U.G. Lab</li>\r\n<li>Software Testing Lab</li>\r\n</ul>', '<p><strong>Placement Overview:</strong></p>\r\n<p>CS being one of the highly paid branches coupled with one of the top institutes of the company results in top companies like Google and Facebook visiting the campus. In previous years Facebook offered a package of 1.35 Crores to one of the students at MNNIT. So what an average Computer Science student can expect is to get placed at a considerable good package in a core company.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Some of the companies that visit MNNIT for CS branch are listed below:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Wipro</li>\r\n<li>Infosys</li>\r\n<li>Cognizant</li>\r\n<li>TCS</li>\r\n<li>ITC Infotech</li>\r\n<li>Oracle</li>\r\n<li>Google</li>\r\n<li>Facebook</li>\r\n<li>Microsoft</li>\r\n<li>Cisco</li>\r\n<li>Adobe</li>\r\n<li>Amazon</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Average Package:</strong> 8.12 LPA</p>\r\n<p><strong>Maximum Package:</strong> 20 LPA</p>\r\n<p><strong>Percentage Placement:</strong> Out of 130 eligible students 114 were placed.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Branch Scenario:</strong></p>\r\n<p><em>Further Studies/Research Scope:</em></p>\r\n<p>Computer Science enthusiasts and graduates are sometimes placed in sectors like Information Technology, System management and Banking. Most frequently students prefer investing in their own start-ups. Options like Gate and Cat are open for students who want to pursue their masters.</p>\r\n<p>With evolving technology in computers course upgradation is done on a regular basis.</p>', '<p>The department comprises of 5 professors, 5 associate professors, 14 assistant professors having deep knowledge of the subject and have carried out research in the following fields:<br />&bull; Networking<br />&bull; Databases<br />&bull; Software Engineering<br />&bull; Data Mining<br />&bull; Mobile &amp; Distributed Computing, Wireless Networks<br />&bull; Digital Image Processing and Compression Techniques<br />&bull; Real Time Systems<br />&bull; Sensor Networks</p>', '<p>With Universities (Indian/Foreign) The institute has collaborated with Queens University and has aimed at collaborating with leading technical universities and research organisations of Germany and Finland in the past.</p>', '', 'branchreview/see_branch_review.php?id=15', ' NIT9 Allahabad Computer Science Engineering CS99 CSE9 Computersg'),
(16, 'branchreview/img/branch_info16.jpeg', 'img/branch_info_b16.jpeg', '  NIT Allahabad ', 'Electrical Engineering ', '<p>The Electrical Engineering Department caters students with a UG course in Electrical Engineering and a PG course in Control ,NIT Allahabad Electrical Engineering Instrumentation and Power System, along with a part-time PG course in Electrical Engineering. Further, the Department also enrolls candidates for Ph.D programs. The Department has qualified and experienced faculty having done research in various fields of Electrical Engineering. The knowledge of the subject is complemented by well-equipped laboratories. There is loads of exchange of ideas between the Electrical Engineering Department and various other departments like Electronics Engineering and Computer Science and Engineering.&nbsp;</p>', '<p>Well-equipped and regularly maintained laboratories are a quality of the department.</p>\r\n<p><strong>The department comprises of following labs:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>CONTROL SYSTEM LABORATORY </li>\r\n<li>POWER ELECTRONICS LABORATORY </li>\r\n<li>COMPUTER SIMULATION LABORATORY</li>\r\n<li>ELECTRICAL MEASUREMENT LABORATORY</li>\r\n<li>PROJECT LABORATORY</li>\r\n<li>ELECTRICAL MACHINES LABORATORY</li>\r\n<li>TESTING AND CALIBERATION FACILITIES</li>\r\n</ul>', '<p><strong>Placement Overview</strong></p>\r\n<p>Electrical being one of the core branches and a necessity of today is one of the highly paid branches and has a lot of scope in terms of future growth. Also a large number of companies visit the campus regularly to hire electrical engineers and offer quite a good amount of money.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Some of the companies that visit MNNIT for Electrical branch are listed below:</strong></p>\r\n<p>1. Uttam Galva Steel</p>\r\n<p>2. HPCL-Mittal Energy Ltd. (HMEL)</p>\r\n<p>3. Lalitpur Power Generation Company Ltd.</p>\r\n<p>4. Rays Power Infra</p>\r\n<p>5. Parker Hennifin India</p>\r\n<p>6. Rajasthan Electronics &amp; Instruments Limited (REIL)</p>\r\n<p>7. ReInspire Tech</p>\r\n<p>8. voylla</p>\r\n<p>9. Aditya Birla Chemicals</p>\r\n<p>10. Binani Cements</p>\r\n<p>11. TATA Power-DDL</p>\r\n<p>12. Trident Group</p>\r\n<p>13. FIAT India Automative Ltd</p>\r\n<p><strong>Average Package:</strong> 6.56 LPA<br /><strong>Maximum Package:</strong> 14 LPA<br /><strong>Percentage Placement:</strong> Out of 61 eligible students 49 were placed.</p>\r\n<p><br /><strong>Branch Scenario</strong></p>\r\n<p><em>Further Studies/Research Scope</em></p>\r\n<p>Options like Gate and Cat are open for students who want to pursue their masters.Course Curriculum are upgraded as per new technology .With evolving technology in electronic media course upgradation is done on a regular basis.</p>', '<p>The department comprises of 5 professors, 6 associate professors, 7 assistant professors having deep knowledge of the subject.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Research is going on the following projects:-</strong></p>\r\n<p>&bull; Reduced order modelling of Systems</p>\r\n<p>&bull; Flexible AC Transmission Systems (FACTS)</p>\r\n<p>&bull; Six phase Transmission systems</p>\r\n<p>&bull; Cyclo-Convertors</p>\r\n<p>&bull; Neural Network Applications</p>', '<p>With Universities (Indian/Foreign): The institute has collaborated with Queens University and has aimed at collaborating with leading technical universities and research organisations of Germany and Finland in the past.</p>', '<p><strong>Conferences/Seminars:</strong></p>\r\n<p>Various conferences are held on evolving technology to bring forth the students various research arenas and developments.</p>', 'branchreview/see_branch_review.php?id=16', 'NIT9 Allahabad Electrical Engineering EE99 ');
