ulty members. The faculties hold the responsibility for the brighter future of students. They try and teach the students all the basics. Although the department lacks in mentorship programs.&nbsp;</p>', '<p style=\\"margin: 0cm; margin-bottom: .0001pt; text-align: justify; line-height: 15.0pt;\\"><span lang=\\"EN-US\\" style=\\"font-size: 10.0pt; font-family: \\''Helvetica\\'',\\''sans-serif\\''; color: #555555;\\">Universities like University of Edinburgh, UK, University of Western Ontario, Canada and University of Texas, North Denton, USA have signed MOU with the department.</span></p>', '<p style=\\"margin: 0cm; margin-bottom: .0001pt; text-align: justify; line-height: 15.0pt;\\"><span lang=\\"EN-US\\" style=\\"font-size: 10.0pt; font-family: \\''Helvetica\\'',\\''sans-serif\\''; color: #555555;\\">Quite a large number of conferences and seminars are organised in the department and some are organised as a part of Wissenaire, a technical fest.&nbsp;</span></p>', 'branchreview/see_branch_review.php?id=21', 'IIT9 Bhubaneshwar Civil Engineering '),
(22, 'branchreview/img/branch_info22.jpeg', 'img/branch_info_b22.jpeg', 'NIT Allahabad ', 'Electronics and Communication Engineering', '<p>Along with one UG course in Electronics and Communication Engineering, the department offers three post-graduate courses in Digital System, Microelectronics and VLSI Design and Communication Systems. Most importantly the department in Government of India sponsored centre for Mtech and PhD programs. &nbsp;The department has well-qualified and extraordinary faculty which impart the best of the knowledge to their students.&nbsp;</p>', '<p>Well Equipped laboratories are a necessity for any branch. Regular maintenance is being done in order to ensure latest technologies at the footsteps of students.</p>\r\n<p><strong> The department comprises of following labs:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Basic Electronics Lab</li>\r\n<li>Communication Engineering Lab</li>\r\n<li>Computer Architecture Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Digital Systems Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>PCB Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Project Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>VLSI Lab.</li>\r\n<li>Signal Processing Lab.</li>\r\n<li>Job/Placement &amp; Business Opportunities</li>\r\n</ul>', '<p>The path of further studies is always open for students which ensures them a higher package.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Some of the companies that visit MNNIT for ECE branch are listed below:</strong></p>\r\n<p>1. Researchwire knowledge solutions</p>\r\n<p>2. Blisterring Solutions</p>\r\n<p>3. Rajasthan Electronics &amp; Instruments Limited (REIL)</p>\r\n<p>4. ReInspire Tech</p>\r\n<p>5. Binani Cements</p>\r\n<p>6. Sapient</p>\r\n<p>7. Compro Technologies</p>\r\n<p>8. Rancore</p>\r\n<p><strong>Average Package:</strong> 5.8</p>\r\n<p><strong>Maximum Package:</strong> 14</p>\r\n<p><strong>Percentage Placement:</strong> Out of 118 eligible students 90 were placed.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Branch Scenario:</strong></p>\r\n<p><em>Further Studies/Research Scope:</em></p>\r\n<p>A branch as good as ECE always hold the option of further studies within it. A student who wants to pursue further studies has various doors open in front of him .Course Curriculum are upgraded as per new technology</p>\r\n<p>With evolving technology in media of communication course upgradation is done on a regular basis. </p>', '<p>The department comprises of 8 professors, 2 associate professors, 14 assistant professors having deep knowledge of the subject and have carried out research in the following fields:</p>\r\n<p><strong>Many sponsored project are going on in the field of :-</strong><br />&bull; Telematics<br />&bull; Modernization of Communication Lab.<br />&bull; Digital Signal Processing<br />&bull; High Speed Communication Lab</p>\r\n<p><strong>RESEARCH PUBLICATIONS OF THE DEPARTMENT:</strong><br />&bull; IEEE Trans. Circuits Systems (U.S.A.)<br />&bull; IEEE Proceedings (U.S.A.)<br />&bull; IEEE Trans. Automat. Control (U.S.A.)<br />&bull; IEEE Trans. Industrial Electron. (U.S.A.)<br />&bull; IEEE Trans. Signal Processing (U.S.A.)<br />&bull; IEE Proceedings (U.K.)<br />&bull; Electronics Letters (U.K.)<br />&bull; International J. Electronics (U.K.)<br />&bull; International J. Control (U.K.)<br />&bull; J. Inst. Engr. Electronics Division (India)<br />&bull; CONFERENCE PAPERS<br />&bull; INVITED (SURVEY) PAPER<br />&bull; PUBLISHED BOOK REVIEWS<br />Published (by invitation from Editors) number of book reviews for various journals including IEEE Transactions (U.S.A.)<br />&bull; IN INTERNATIONAL JOURNALS<br />&bull; IN INTERNATIONAL CONFERENCES</p>', '<p>With Universities (Indian/Foreign): The institute has collaborated with Queens University and has aimed at collaborating with leading technical universities and research organisations of Germany and Finland in the past.</p>', '<p>Various conferences on communication systems are being organized on a regular basis to enhance the knowledge of students.&nbsp;</p>', 'branchreview/see_branch_review.php?id=22', 'NIT9 Allahabad Electronics and9 Communication Engineering ECE9'),
(23, 'branchreview/img/branch_info23.jpeg', 'img/branch_info_b23.jpeg', 'IIT Bombay', 'Mechanical Engineering', '<p>The Mechanical Engineering Dept at IIT Bombay is one of the largest in terms of faculty, students, and activities, continues to lead and expand its activities in various directions. The Department is known for research and projects in robotics, fluid dynamics, heat pumps, cryogenics, nuclear engineering, fracture mechanics, I. C. Engines, Combustion, CFD, CAD-CAM and other areas.</p>', '<p>The dept of Mechanical Engineering, IIT Bombay maintains total of 27 laboratories some of them are:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Machine Tools &amp; Meteorology</li>\r\n<li>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Heat Transfer and Thermodynamics</li>\r\n<li>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Fracture Mechanics</li>\r\n<li>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; IIT-Bombay ONGC Joint Research Centre</li>\r\n<li>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Cummins Research Facility</li>\r\n<li>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Computer Aided Manufacturing</li>\r\n<li>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Computation</li>\r\n<li>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Computational Fluid Dynamics</li>\r\n<li>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Computer Graphics</li>\r\n<li>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Fluid Mechanics and Fluid Power</li>\r\n<li>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Internal Combustion Engines</li>\r\n<li>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Heat Pump</li>\r\n<li>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Machine Design</li>\r\n<li>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Mechatronics, Controls &amp; Measurement</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '<p><strong>Trend and name of companies visited for this branch:&nbsp;</strong>The compnies which regularly visit the dept of ME includes Ashok Leyland, Cummins, TATA Motors, Applied Materials, Bosch, General Motors, Hero Motocorp, Mahindra and Mahindra etc.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Further Scope (MS/MBS/M.Tech/Civil Services/Entrepreneurship):</strong> Dept of ME offers M.Tech and Ph.D in the legion of higher studies. The M.Tech is being offered in three main specializations:</p>\r\n<p>&sect;&nbsp; Thermal and Fluids Engineering</p>\r\n<p>&sect;&nbsp; Design Engineering</p>\r\n<p>&sect;&nbsp; Manufacturing Engineering</p>', '<p>The department has a legion of 41 faculty members, all of them Ph.D. in their areas of research.</p>', '<p>The Department has Tie-ups with ONGC and established an IIT Bombay and ONGC joint research center. The department also has Cummins research center established in collaboration with with Cummins India Limited.</p>', '<p>Radiance is an annual technical festival organized by the Dept. Apart from radiance various workshops and STTPs are regularly organized</p>', 'branchreview/see_branch_review.php?id=23', 'IIT9 Bombay IITB Mech Mechanical Engineering '),
(24, 'branchreview/img/branch_info24.jpeg', 'img/branch_info_b24.jpeg', 'NIT Allahabad ', 'Biotechnology ', '<p>It was established as a new academic unit under Applied Mechanics in 2006 in order to integrate life sciences with engineering.NIT Allahabad Biotechnology An independent department was set up in April, 2012. A full-fledged post graduate programme in Biotechnology was started in 2010. Regular conferences are being organized and funds are generated from governmental bodies to improve the department.&nbsp;</p>', '<p>The department is well facilitated with various equipment required for carrying out any research activity. Practical study is very well encouraged in the department by means of following equipment:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Anaerobic gas System</li>\r\n<li>Weighing Balance</li>\r\n<li>CDC biofilm device</li>\r\n<li>Colorimeter</li>\r\n<li>Digestion unit</li>\r\n<li>DO Meter model with probe</li>\r\n<li>Agarose gel electrophoresis units</li>\r\n<li>Laminar air flow</li>\r\n<li>Magnetic stirrer with hot plate</li>\r\n<li>Microwave Oven</li>\r\n<li>Hot air Ovens</li>\r\n<li>Plant growth chamber</li>\r\n<li>Refrigerator</li>\r\n<li>Southern blotting Apparatus</li>\r\n<li>Transilluminator</li>\r\n<li>UV Visible Spectrophotometer</li>\r\n<li>Vortex Mixture</li>\r\n<li>Fluorescent Microscope with accessories</li>\r\n<li>Biosafety cabinet</li>\r\n<li>Elisa Reader</li>\r\n<li>Gel Documentation system* Autoclaves</li>\r\n<li>BOD Incubator</li>\r\n<li>Centrifuge</li>\r\n<li>Cooling Centrifuge</li>\r\n<li>Deep freezer ( -20 &amp; 800 C )</li>\r\n<li>Digital COD</li>\r\n<li>Digital colony counter</li>\r\n<li>Double distillation unit</li>\r\n<li>Thermal Cycler</li>\r\n<li>Homogenizer</li>\r\n<li>Incubator</li>\r\n<li>Microscope</li>\r\n<li>Orbital shaker incubator</li>\r\n<li>Ph Meter</li>\r\n<li>Serological Water Bath</li>\r\n<li>Spin Win Micro Centrifuge</li>\r\n<li>Tissue Culture Racks</li>\r\n<li>Vacuum pump</li>\r\n<li>Ultra Membrane Filtration Unit</li>\r\n<li>CO2 incubator*</li>\r\n<li>Water purification system</li>\r\n</ul>', '<p><strong>Placement Overview</strong></p>\r\n<p>Various Pharma companies look out for good biotechnology students and hence the branch has a bright future.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Some of the companies that visit MNNIT for Biotechnology branch are listed below:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Cipla</li>\r\n<li>Ranbaxy</li>\r\n<li>Dr. Reddy&rsquo;s</li>\r\n<li>Grace</li>\r\n<li>Agilent Technlogies</li>\r\n<li>Abide</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Average Package:</strong> 3.74 LPA</p>\r\n<p><strong>Maximum Package:</strong> 6 LPa</p>\r\n<p><strong>Percentage Placement:</strong> Out of 15 eligible students 8 were placed.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Branch Scenario:</strong></p>\r\n<p><em>Further Studies/Research Scope:</em></p>\r\n<p>One can opt for Gate if he/she wants to remain in the core field and can opt for CAT if someone wants to get out of the core branch.Course Curriculum are upgraded as per new technology</p>\r\n<p>With evolving technology regular efforts are being put in to ensure the best for students.</p>', '<p>The department comprises of 2 associate professors, 11 assistant professors having deep knowledge of the subject.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Projects are going on in the following areas:-</strong> <br />&bull; Environmental Biotechnology, Plant Microbe interaction, Microbiology.<br />&bull; Genetic Engineering, Molecular Biology, Plant Biotechnology.<br />&bull; Bioprocess and Product Development, Enzyme Technology, Biochemistry.<br />&bull; Microbial Biofilms and Drug Resistance.<br />&bull; Epigenetics &amp; Chromatin remodeling.<br />&bull; Immunodiagnostics, Application of Nanotechnology in diagnostics.</p>\r\n<p><strong>With the following indian organizations:-</strong></p>\r\n<p>University Grants Commission (UGC)<br />Department of Biotechnology (DBT)<br />Ministry of New and Renewable Energy<br />Department of Biotechnology (DBT)<br />Department of Science and Technology (DST)</p>', '<p>With Universities (Indian/Foreign): In order to bring the best out of students the department has tried to collaborate with foreign universities to cater the best to the students.<br />With Industries: The main aim of the department is to meet the demands of the biotechnology based industries. The department has initiated efforts to establish advanced research laboratories in all the thrust areas.</p>', '<p><strong>Conferences/Seminars</strong></p>\r\n<p>Various conferences and seminars are being organised at campus to bring the students closer to evolving technology. Students are even taken outdoors for research work in order to strengthen their concepts. </p>', 'branchreview/see_branch_review.php?id=24', 'NIT9 Allahabad Biotech Biotechnology '),
(25, 'branchreview/img/branch_info25.jpeg', 'img/branch_info_b25.jpeg', 'IIT Bombay', 'Electrical Engineering', '<p>The Department of Electrical Engineering (EE) is one of the major Departments of IIT Bombay since its inception in 1958. The department is very active in teaching and research in the areas of Communications and Signal Processing, Control and Computing, Power Electronics and Power Systems, Microelectronics and VLSI design, and Electronic Systems.</p>', '<p>&nbsp;<strong>Infrastructure and&nbsp;Laboratories:</strong></p>\r\n<p>A long list of labs in the department are:</p>\r\n<p>1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Computer Architecture and Dependable Systems Lab</p>\r\n<p>2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Applied Power Electronics Laboratory&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Bharti Center for Communication</p>\r\n<p>4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Communication Laboratory</p>\r\n<p>5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Control and Computing Laboratory</p>\r\n<p>6.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Digital Audio Processing Lab</p>\r\n<p>7.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Electronic Instrumentation Lab</p>\r\n<p>8.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Fiber Optics Communication</p>\r\n<p>9.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Field Computation Laboratory</p>\r\n<p>10.&nbsp; High Performance Computing Lab</p>\r\n<p>11.&nbsp; Information Networks Laboratory (Infonet Lab)</p>\r\n<p>12.&nbsp; Nanoelectronics Computation Lab</p>\r\n<p>13.&nbsp; TTSL &ndash; IITB Center of Excellence in Telecommunication (TICET)</p>\r\n<p>14.&nbsp; Vision and Image Processing</p>\r\n<p>15.&nbsp; VLSI Design Lab</p>\r\n<p>16.&nbsp; Wadhwani Electronics Lab &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>', '<p><strong>Trend and name of companies visited for this branch:</strong></p>\r\n<p>The Cpmpanies which visit the Electrical Engg. Department are AMD India, BHEL, Applied materials, Broadcomm India research, NVIDIA, Samsung electronix, Qualcomm India etc. &nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Further Scope (MS/MBS/M.Tech/Civil Services/Entrepreneurship):</strong></p>\r\n<p>The department offers M.tech nad Ph.D in the field of both core electrical and electronix stream. Some of the programs are:</p>\r\n<p>&sect;&nbsp; Communications Engineering</p>\r\n<p>&sect;&nbsp; Control and Computing&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&sect;&nbsp; Power Electronics and Power System&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&sect;&nbsp; Microelectronics and VLSI&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&sect;&nbsp; Electronic Systems</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp;Now a days students are also showing interest towards civil services and&nbsp;entrepreneurship.&nbsp;</p>', '<p>The EE department has 60 efficient and highly qualified faculty members to guide the students. &nbsp;</p>', '<p>Branch faculty have a strong relationship with other institute as well as department also support various indian organization in technical matters. Department also has a&nbsp;Tie-up with IEEE.</p>', '<p>Various conferences/ workshops and lectures are organized at a regular interval such as&nbsp;Workshops on advanced electronic system design. &nbsp;</p>', 'branchreview/see_branch_review.php?id=25', 'IIT9 Bombay IITB Electrical Engineering EE99 '),
(26, 'branchreview/img/branch_info26.jpeg', 'img/branch_info_b26.jpeg', 'IIT Bombay', 'Biosciences and Bioengineering', '<p>The Department of Biosciences and Bioengineering (BSBE) is a nodal center for applying science and engineering principles to further fundamental knowledge and applications in biology and biomedical engineering. The BSBE department aims to create an ambience for the smooth pursuit of scholarly activities in research and education, to make an international impact, and to produce future leaders in the field of Biosciences and Bioengineering.</p>', '<p><strong>Infrastructure and Laboratories:</strong></p>\r\n<p>The BSBE department maintains following labs:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Protein Sequencing&nbsp; Facility</li>\r\n<li>Parimal and Pramod Chaudhari Laboratory for Cell Culture</li>\r\n<li>Microscopy Fermentation facility</li>\r\n<li>Radioactivity facility &nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Central Facility Equipments</li>\r\n</ul>', '<p><strong>Trend and name of companies visited for this branch:</strong></p>\r\n<p>Students from this field normally opt for further study . &nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Further Scope (MS/MBS/M.Tech/Civil Services/Entrepreneurship):</strong></p>\r\n<p>M.sc Biotechnology</p>\r\n<p>M.Tech bio medical Engineering</p>\r\n<p>Integrated M.sc- Ph.D program</p>\r\n<p>PhD program.</p>', '<p>The department has 25 faculty members all are Ph.Ds having profound research interests.</p>', '<p>The BSBE departments publishes research journals on regular basis and has research tie up with labs across India.</p>', '<p><strong>Branch events/conferences:</strong> The BSBE department is mainly focused on research in the field of Biotech and Biomedical engineering</p>', 'branchreview/see_branch_review.php?id=26', 'IIT9 Bombay IITB Bio9 Biological Sciences');
INSERT INTO `branch_review` (`id`, `img`, `b_img`, `clg`, `branch`, `intro`, `infa_labs`, `branch_scope`, `branch_faculty`, `col`, `about`, `url`, `tags`) VALUES
(27, 'branchreview/img/branch_info27.jpeg', 'img/branch_info_b27.jpeg', 'NIT Allahabad  ', 'Information Technology ', '<p>The branch plays an important role in developing software and networking world. The course provides one with a strong academic ground and a strong foundation for a vibrant future. The department aims at imparting all the basic skills required to meet varying challenges in the field. &nbsp;Varying job opportunities such as programmer, system analyst, software engineers and consultants stand high in front of IT professionals.</p>', '<p>Well Equipped laboratories are a necessity for any branch. Regular maintenance is being done in order to ensure latest technologies at the footsteps of students.</p>\r\n<p><strong>The department comprises of following labs:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Image Processing</li>\r\n<li>Information Security</li>\r\n<li>Microprocessor and Computer Architecture</li>\r\n<li>Distributed Computing</li>\r\n<li>P.G. Lab</li>\r\n<li>U.G. Lab</li>\r\n<li>Software Testing Lab<br /><br /></li>\r\n</ul>', '<p><strong>Placement Overview</strong></p>\r\n<p>The future of an engineer with IT branch is definitely a software company which has high prospects of growth and greater package with increasing experience. MNNIT holds great reputation due to which a great number of software companies visit campus for on-campus placements and hire students for a considerably good package.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Some of the companies that visit MNNIT for IT branch are listed below:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Salesforce</li>\r\n<li>ReInspire Tech</li>\r\n<li>Misys Software Solutions</li>\r\n<li>Newgen Software Technologies</li>\r\n<li>Rancore</li>\r\n<li>polaris financial technology</li>\r\n<li>amdocs</li>\r\n<li>oracle financial services software</li>\r\n<li>Drishti Soft</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Average Package:</strong> 7.47 LPA</p>\r\n<p><strong>Maximum Package</strong>: 18 LPA</p>\r\n<p><strong>Percentage Placement:</strong> Out of 72 eligible students 56 were placed.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Branch Scenario:</strong></p>\r\n<p><em>Further Studies/Research Scope</em></p>\r\n<p>Most frequently students prefer investing in their own start-ups. Options like Gate and Cat are open for students who want to pursue their masters.Course Curriculum are upgraded as per new technology</p>\r\n<p>With evolving technology in computers course upgradation is done on a regular basis.</p>', '<p>The department comprises of 5 professors, 5 associate professors, 14 assistant professors. The department has qualified and experienced faculty in the areas of Computer Architecture, Database Systems, Image Processing, Artificial Intelligence, Data Mining, Wireless and Sensor Networks, Computer Networks, &nbsp;and Software Engineering.&nbsp;</p>', '<p>With Universities (Indian/Foreign): The institute has collaborated with Queens University and has aimed at collaborating with leading technical universities and research organisations of Germany and Finland in the past.</p>', '<p><strong>Conferences/Seminars:</strong></p>\r\n<p>Varying conferences are organized pertaining to the branch to enhance the thinking level of students.</p>', 'branchreview/see_branch_review.php?id=27', 'NIT9 Allahabad Information Technology IT99'),
(28, 'branchreview/img/branch_info28.jpeg', 'img/branch_info_b28.jpeg', 'NIT Bhopal', ' Chemical Engineering ', '<p>Department is one of the important and well equipped engineering departments of NIT Bhopal and established in theNIT Bhopal Chemical Engineering year 1988. It aims at creating a centre of excellence in research and technical aspects of the branch. Department offers a 4 year B.Tech course, M.tech course and P.hd degrees with an intake of of 68 students in B&gt;tech course and 24 in Phd course.</p>', '<p><strong>A number of labs are present in the department like:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Chemical Reaction Engineering Lab</li>\r\n<li>Mass Transfer Lab</li>\r\n<li>Heat Transfer Lab</li>\r\n<li>Fluid Particle Mechanics Lab</li>\r\n<li>Momentum Transfer Operations Lab</li>\r\n<li>Process Dynamics and Control Lab</li>\r\n<li>Analytical Instrumentation Lab</li>\r\n<li>Computer Lab and other infrastructural facilities.</li>\r\n</ul>', '<p><strong>Placements &amp; Business Opportunities:</strong></p>\r\n<p>Analytical data displays that a total number of 15-18 companies including core &amp; non core visited the campus for recruiting students. But now a days due to growth in consultancies &amp; trading companies students are attracted by jobs in consulting &amp; marketing.</p>\r\n<p><strong> Some of the past recruiters are:</strong></p>\r\n<p>-Halliburton<br />-HCC Ltd<br />-Headstrong<br />-Hero<br />-Hindalco<br />-HPCL<br />-Hyderabad Inds. Ltd<br />-IBM<br />-Impetus<br />-Infobeans<br />-Infogain<br />-Infosys Tech<br />-IOCL<br />-IOTIESL<br />-ISPAT<br />-Ivy Comptech<br />-J.K. Tyres</p>\r\n<p><br />According to the records of the year 2012-13 a total of 70.5% eligible students got placements from the campus.With an average package of Rs 4.5 lakhs p.a. and highest package of Rs. 12.7 lakhs p.a.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Future scope and internships:</strong></p>\r\n<p>The placement and training cell of NIT Bhopal ensures the placements of the placements of students and collaborates with leading institutes &amp; organisations in the setting up of internship &amp; training programme for the present students. The cell holds responsibility of placements and training and interacts with over 130 companies which visit the department for holding in campus interviews. The companies include core engineering firms, IT sector, manufacturing industries, consultancies, finance &amp; managerial companies, etc&hellip;</p>', '<p>The Department is maintaining a large number of close associations with industries &amp; design organizations of chemical engineering, and is involved in the regular upgradation of the course curriculum. Students are highly motivated and encouraged to analyse industrial problem &amp; participate actively in programmes sponsored from outside. Department is well furnished &amp; equipped to meet the needs of all courses.</p>', '', '', 'branchreview/see_branch_review.php?id=28', 'NIT9 Bhopal Chem Chemical Engineering '),
(29, 'branchreview/img/branch_info29.jpeg', 'img/branch_info_b29.jpeg', 'IIT Bombay', 'Computer Science Engineering', '<p>Department of Computer science and Engineering, IIT Bombay offers a charismatic qualification in the field of Computer software and Hardware including the related electronics.&nbsp;</p>', '<p>Research&nbsp; Laboratories:</p>\r\n<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Centre for Formal Design and Verification of Systems</p>\r\n<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Centre for Indian Language Technologies</p>\r\n<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Database and Information Systems Laboratory</p>\r\n<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Embedded Real-Time Systems Laboratory</p>\r\n<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; GCC Resource Center</p>\r\n<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Gigabit Networking Laboratory</p>\r\n<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Graphics and Vision Laboratory</p>\r\n<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Laboratory for Intelligent Internet Research</p>\r\n<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Systems and Networks Research Group</p>\r\n<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Geospatial Information Science &amp; Engineering</p>', '<p><strong>Trend and name of companies visited for this branch:</strong> <br />Every year a rich no of companies visit to offer jobs to the students. Some of them includes Adobe systems India, Amazon, AMD, NVIDIA, Google, Facebook, Microsoft etc. &nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Further Scope (MS/MBS/M.Tech/Civil Services/Entrepreneurship):<br /></strong> CSE-IITB offers&nbsp; M. Tech., M. Tech. Dual Degree and Ph. D. programmes in Computer Science which is also a good scope for students. Now a days students are also showing interest towards civil services and&nbsp;entrepreneurship.&nbsp;</p>', '<p>The CSE department has a team of highly efficient and qualified faculty members. Alumni network of IIT- B &nbsp;C.S department is also strong.</p>', '<p>Various R&amp;D centers across India. Tie-up with IEEE and NPTEL to bring the advancement in research and learning methods.</p>', '<p><strong>Branch events/conferences:</strong> various conferences and workshops are organized regularly which motivates students towards IT market and scope. &nbsp;</p>', 'branchreview/see_branch_review.php?id=29', 'IIT9 Bombay IITB Computer Science Engineering CS99 CSE9 Computers'),
(30, 'branchreview/img/branch_info30.jpeg', 'img/branch_info_b30.jpeg', 'IIT Bombay', 'Civil Engineering', '<p>The Department of civil Engineering is an integral part of IIT Bombay since its establishment in 1958. The department recorded tremendous growth since and developed strong industrial links over the time. Besides high quality teaching and instruction at both UG and PG levels, the Department is actively involved in basic and applied research and consultancy and provides high quality technical advisory support through various R D projects and consultancy to various organizations.</p>', '<p>The facilities involves:</p>\r\n<p>1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Structural Engineering Laboratories</p>\r\n<p>2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Concrete Technology Laboratory&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Remote Sensing Laboratories</p>\r\n<p>4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Global Positioning System Laboratory</p>\r\n<p>5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Geotechnical Engineering Laboratories</p>\r\n<p>6.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Geo-technical lab</p>\r\n<p>7.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Transportation Systems Engineering Laboratories</p>\r\n<p>8.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Ocean Engineering Laboratories</p>\r\n<p>9.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Computational Laboratories</p>', '<p><strong>Trend and name of companies visited for this branch:<br /></strong> The companies that frequently visit the Department are ACC Limited, Larsen and&nbsp; Toubro, Hindustan Petroleum corporation, Reliance Industries etc. &nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Further Scope (MS/MBS/M.Tech/Civil Services/Entrepreneurship):<br /></strong> Normally students apart from placement prefer M.Tech and Ph.D in various areas of chemical engineering from India as well as foreign</p>', '<p>The Department of civil Engineering accommodates highly efficient faculty involved in high end research programmes, Also providing consultancy to the leading industries</p>', '<p>A large number of consultancy projects in various disciplines are undertaken by the faculty. Each year about 250 consultancy projects worth about Rs.40 Million are&nbsp;undertaken. A few of the recent projects are: Technical Advice on Repair and Strengthening of ONGC buildings &ndash; Oil and Natural Gas Corporation Ltd Health monitoring of railway bridges due to increase in axle loads on iron-ore routes &ndash; Pixel Networks. &nbsp;</p>', '<p><strong>Branch events/conferences:</strong></p>\r\n<p>In order to encourage and facilitate interaction with professionals, a number of activities like organizing short-term courses (under Continuing Education Programme, quality Improvement Programme and programmes sponsored by Government and other agencies), organizing regular Departmental Seminars, facilitating National and International conferences, etc. are promoted by the Department.</p>', 'branchreview/see_branch_review.php?id=30', 'IIT9 Bombay IITB Civil Engineering '),
(31, 'branchreview/img/branch_info31.jpeg', 'img/branch_info_b31.jpeg', 'NIT Bhopal ', 'Civil Engineering', '<p>&nbsp;Established in 1960 as one of the oldest department of the institute offering B.tech course and 7 M.tech courses ofNIT Bhopal Civil Engineering civil engineering. It also has Phd programme. The department is well equipped and enriched with a core team of 30 highly qualified faculty members who are capable of producing good civil engineers out of their students. <br /><br /></p>', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Main laboratories of the department are:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Computer Lab</li>\r\n<li>Environmental Engg. /Public Health Engg. Lab</li>\r\n<li>Survey Lab</li>\r\n<li>Hydraulics Lab</li>\r\n<li>Remote Sensing/GIS Lab</li>\r\n<li>Geology Lab</li>\r\n<li>Soil Lab</li>\r\n<li>Concrete Lab</li>\r\n<li>Structural Dynamics Lab </li>\r\n</ul>', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Placement &amp; Business Opportunities</strong></p>\r\n<p>According to statistics : there were 92.5% placements in 2012-2013 among the eligible students.</p>\r\n<p>Records have shown a total number of 13-15 companies visited the department for recruiting students including core &amp; non-core fields. Some of the past recruiters are:</p>\r\n<p>&middot; Lafarge India<br />&middot; L&amp;T Infotech<br />&middot; LG India<br />&middot; Maruti Suzuki<br />&middot; MediaTech<br />&middot; Microsoft<br />&middot; MindaInds.<br />&middot; Misys<br />&middot; M&amp;M Ltd<br />&middot; Mu-Sigma<br />&middot; Nagarro<br />&middot; NDPL<br />&middot; Nokia Siemens<br />&middot; NTPC Ltd</p>\r\n<p><br />AVERAGE PACKAGE of the department was 4.5 LAKHS P.A.</p>\r\n<p>HIGHEST PACKAGE was 12.7 LAKHS P.A.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Future scope and internships</strong></p>\r\n<p>The placement and training cell of NIT Bhopal ensures the placements of the placements of students and collaborates with leading institutes &amp; organisations in the setting up of internship &amp; training programme for the present students. The cell holds responsibility of placements and training and interacts with over 130 companies which visit the department for holding in campus interviews. The companies include core engineering firms, IT sector, manufacturing industries, consultancies, finance &amp; managerial companies, etc&hellip;</p>\r\n<p>Faculty members are also delivering lectures for fields &amp; industries belonging engineers. A strong emphasis is laid by the faculty on the research &amp; development sector of Indian economy and infrastructure including:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>National highway (NH) development projects</li>\r\n<li>Prime minister&rsquo;s gramin sadak yojna</li>\r\n<li>Power generation involving irrigation facilities</li>\r\n<li>Petroleum related sector- Bina refinery</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>All this promotes a basic approach in students to opt for higher studies and professional work for their bright career.&nbsp;</p>', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The UG course has been rewarded with A grade by NBA. The department has 11 laboratories and is well equipped with all kind of essential facilities. Department has 30 highly qualified teachers for encouraging students and enhance their technical knowledge. All support of faculty have made their students capable of facing the exposure and pressure of the practical work and world.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '', '', 'branchreview/see_branch_review.php?id=31', 'NIT9 Bhopal Civil Engineering '),
(32, 'branchreview/img/branch_info32.jpeg', 'img/branch_info_b32.jpeg', 'IIT Bombay', 'Chemical Engineering', '<p>Started in 1958, the department of Chemical Engineering was established in assistance with Soviet union with UNESCO&rsquo;s aid. Chemical Engineering at IIT Bombay is today recognized as a leading department in India primarily because of its strong academic programme, large faculty strength and diverse range of research areas.&nbsp;</p>', '<p><strong>Infrastructure and Laborateries:</strong></p>\r\n<p>The department maintains a large number of labs, listed below: &nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Biochemical Engineering</p>\r\n<p>2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Biomolecular Engineering</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp; 3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Biosystem Engineering</p>\r\n<p>4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; CAD Laboratory</p>\r\n<p>5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Cellulose Laboratory</p>\r\n<p>6.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Fluid Mechanics Lab</p>\r\n<p>7.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Heat Transfer Lab</p>\r\n<p>8.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Membrane Lab</p>\r\n<p>9.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Organic Processes Lab</p>\r\n<p>10.&nbsp; Particle and Aerosol Research Lab (PARL)</p>\r\n<p>11.&nbsp; Polymer Laboratory</p>\r\n<p>12.&nbsp; Protein Engineering Lab</p>\r\n<p>13.&nbsp; Reaction Engineering &nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>14.&nbsp; Silicate Engg</p>\r\n<p>15.&nbsp; SoFT (Soft Fluids Technology) Laboratory</p>\r\n<p>16.&nbsp; Thermodynamics Laboratory &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>', '<p><strong>Trend and name of companies visited for this branch:</strong> <br />A very large number of companies visit IIT Bombay every year to offer attractive jobs to the students of chemical engineering department some of them are 3M India Ltd, Cairn Energy, Bharat petroleum, United Phosphorus, TATA Steel, Reliance Industries limited, ONGC, etc.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Further Scope (MS/MBS/M.Tech/Civil Services/Entrepreneurship):</strong> <br />Normally students apart from placement prefer M.Tech and Ph.D in various areas of chemical engineering from india as well as foreign. &nbsp;</p>', '<p>The Department of Chemical Engineering is governed by High potential Faculty members with a vast experience and overwhelming qualifications.&nbsp; &nbsp;</p>', '<p>Department also provide following facilities to industry;</p>\r\n<p>&sect;&nbsp; Consultancy</p>\r\n<p>&sect;&nbsp; CEP Courses</p>\r\n<p>&sect;&nbsp; Technology Transfers</p>\r\n<p>&sect;&nbsp; Patents &sect;&nbsp; R&amp;D, Analytical Services</p>\r\n<p>&sect;&nbsp; Services to Society</p>', '<p><strong>Branch events/conferences:&nbsp;<br /></strong>The department of Chemical Engineering organizes various Guest lectures and conferences time to time to enthusiast and inspire the interest of students towards research and Entrepreneurship.</p>', 'branchreview/see_branch_review.php?id=32', 'IIT9 Bombay IITB Chem Chemical Engineering '),
(33, 'branchreview/img/branch_info33.jpeg', 'img/branch_info_b33.jpeg', 'NIT Bhopal', 'Computer Science Engineering ', '<p>Established in 1994 and its first batch was graduated in the year 1996. It offers mainly B.tech and PG courses. To getNIT Bhopal Computer Science and Engineering into the department one has to get rank within the closing ranks.</p>', '<p>Department has an open library accessible to the students any time during working hours. All necessary laboratories are also available in the department for the students like:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Data Structures Lab</li>\r\n<li>Linear and Digital ICs</li>\r\n<li>System Programming Lab</li>\r\n<li>Microprocessing and Interfacing</li>\r\n<li>Programming Languages</li>\r\n<li>Operating Systems</li>\r\n<li>Database Management Systems</li>\r\n<li>Compiler Design</li>\r\n<li>Software Systems</li>\r\n</ul>', '<p><strong>Placements &amp; Business Opportunities</strong></p>\r\n<p>Statistics shows number of companies which visited the department last year ranged from 12-15 including companies in core as well as non core.</p>\r\n<p><strong>A few of the past recruiters are:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Epic System</li>\r\n<li>Facebook</li>\r\n<li>Amazon</li>\r\n<li>Data 64</li>\r\n<li>Microsoft</li>\r\n<li>Oracle</li>\r\n<li>Honda Motors</li>\r\n<li>Ivy Comptech</li>\r\n<li>Samsung</li>\r\n<li>Hero MotoCorp</li>\r\n<li>Verizon</li>\r\n<li>BPCL</li>\r\n<li>Capillary Tech</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Average package</strong> of the department was Rs<strong> 4.5 lakhs p.a.</strong> nearly and <strong>highest package</strong> was Rs<strong> 12.7 lakhs p.a.</strong> nearly</p>\r\n<p>Statistics have shown that <strong>69.5%</strong> eligible students were placed in the year 2012-13 from the department.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Future scope and internships</strong></p>\r\n<p>The placement and training cell of NIT Bhopal ensures the placements of the placements of students and collaborates with leading institutes &amp; organisations in the setting up of internship &amp; training programme for the present students. The cell holds responsibility of placements and training and interacts with over 130 companies which visit the department for holding in campus interviews. The companies include core engineering firms, IT sector, manufacturing industries, consultancies, finance &amp; managerial companies, etc&hellip;</p>\r\n<p>With a vision of developing: a concrete profile in research in core fields of engineering &amp; technology, curricular programmes best for research in academics &amp; industry, collaborations with leading universities &amp; industries, sustainable methods of education to continue it long, etc&hellip; institute is working day and night. All this provides a background for research of the students for their higher studies and also a strong future scope to handle and enjoy</p>', '<p>Faculty is frank and well interacted with the students to encourage them to take part in academics, research fields &amp; extra-co curricular activities. All the efforts of the faculty members have been reflected in the results and placements of the students which are always earning good in the name of the institute in areas of academics and industries.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '', '', 'branchreview/see_branch_review.php?id=33', 'NIT9 Bhopal Computer Science Engineering CS99 CSE9 Computers'),
(34, 'branchreview/img/branch_info34.jpeg', 'img/branch_info_b34.jpeg', 'IIT Bombay', 'Aerospace Engineering', '<p><strong>:</strong>&nbsp;The Department of Aerospace Engineering, previously called Aeronautical Engineering, was established in 1966. Since its establishment in 1966, it provides courses in both under graduate and post graduate programs with research opportunities in several areas of aeronautical and aerospace sciences.</p>', '<p><strong>Infrastructure and Laboratories:</strong></p>\r\n<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Aerodynamics Lab</p>\r\n<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Dynamics and Control Lab</p>\r\n<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Integrated modeling and Simulation Lab</p>\r\n<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Structures Lab</p>\r\n<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Propulsion Lab</p>\r\n<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Aeromodelling Lab</p>', '<p><strong>Trend and name of companies visited for this branch:<br /></strong> &sect;&nbsp; Jet Airways</p>\r\n<p>&sect;&nbsp; General motor Technical center</p>\r\n<p>&sect;&nbsp; Future First</p>\r\n<p>&sect;&nbsp; JP Morgan</p>\r\n<p>&sect;&nbsp; Accenture etc.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Further Scope (MS/MBS/M.Tech/Civil Services/Entrepreneurship):</strong> <br />Ph.D. and M.Tech in various Aerospace Engineering areas with research facilities in Propulsion, Aerodynamics, Controls and structures.</p>', '<p>The Department of Aerospace Engineering consists of highly qualified and experienced faculty in the area with internationally published research papers and collaborations.</p>', '<p>Strong Industrial relations with defense and Aerospace industries with contributions in programmes like GSLV and LCA.</p>', '<p><strong>Branch events/conferences:</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong><br /></strong> ZEPHYR &ndash; It is an annual aviation festival of Department of Aerospace Engineering.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Udaan &ndash; &nbsp;A school outreach programme to make students aware of the adventures of aviation.</p>', 'branchreview/see_branch_review.php?id=34', 'IIT9 Bombay IITB Aerospace Engineering'),
(35, 'branchreview/img/branch_info35.jpeg', 'img/branch_info_b35.jpeg', 'NIT Bhopal ', 'Electronics and Communication Engineering ', '<p>Department was established to make students able to participate and show their talents in academic field, research &amp;NIT Bhopal Electronics and Communication Engineering extra and co curricular activities and comprise at least 20% students&rsquo; strength of the institute which is the largest in the institute. Students by giving their excellent results in the fields of industrial, academia and research have always earned name in favour of the department.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '<p><strong>The ece department is well equipped with latest and all necessary equipments required during the session like:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Electronics, Digital and LIC Laboratories</li>\r\n<li>Microprocessor and Microcontroller Lab</li>\r\n<li>Signal Processing Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>VLSI Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Wireless Communication Systems Lab</li>\r\n<li>Microwave Lab</li>\r\n<li>Fiber Optics Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Microwave Integrated Circuits Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Signal and Image Processing Laboratory</li>\r\n</ul>', '<p><strong>Placement &amp; Business Opportunities</strong></p>\r\n<p>Annually 15-19 companies visit the department for recruiting the students including core and non core. However students due to increase in number of consultancies and trading companies students are moving towards marketing and consulting sectors. In a total 74.5% of eligible students got placements through the campus in the year 2012-13.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Average package</strong> of the branch was Rs <strong>4.5 lakhs p.a.</strong> &amp; <strong>Maximum package</strong> of the branch was Rs <strong>12.7 lakhs p.a.</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Following is the list of companies which have previously visited the campus for recruiting ECE department students:</strong></p>\r\n<p>-NTPC Ltd</p>\r\n<p>-Oracle</p>\r\n<p>-Orient Papers</p>\r\n<p>-Patni Computers</p>\r\n<p>-Pepsico</p>\r\n<p>-Persistent</p>\r\n<p>-Polaris</p>\r\n<p>-Pradan</p>\r\n<p>-Punj Lloyd</p>\r\n<p>-Rancore</p>\r\n<p>-Reliance Energy</p>\r\n<p>-Saint Gobain</p>\r\n<p>-Samsung Electronics</p>\r\n<p>-Samsung India</p>\r\n<p>-Samsung SISO</p>\r\n<p>-Samsung testing</p>\r\n<p>-Samtel</p>', '<p>The department has a blend of renowned teachers who are dynamic, enthusiastic and young personalities as its faculty who is engaged for full time for providing quality education to its students. With a humble vision of increasing research activity &amp; providing quality education at UG &amp; PG level the department is expanding year after year.</p>\r\n<p><br />The placement and training cell of NIT Bhopal ensures the placements of the placements of students and collaborates with leading institutes &amp; organisations in the setting up of internship &amp; training programme for the present students. The cell holds responsibility of placements and training and interacts with over 130 companies which visit the department for holding in campus interviews. The companies include core engineering firms, IT sector, manufacturing industries, consultancies, finance &amp; managerial companies, etc&hellip;</p>\r\n<p>The department has got sponsorships from AICTE, MHRD, ISRO, etc&hellip; to carry out further research works and many labs have been established like VLSI lab, EM radiation research lab, etc where students can get an edge over their practical work as well a basic approach for their further studies in research field.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '', '', 'branchreview/see_branch_review.php?id=35', 'NIT9 Bhopal Electronics and9 Communication Engineering ECE9'),
(36, 'branchreview/img/branch_info36.jpeg', 'img/branch_info_b36.jpeg', 'NIT Bhopal ', 'Mechanical Engineering', '<p>Established to offer U.G. courses and P.G. courses in mechanical engineering. This department is one of the mostNIT Bhopal Mechanical Engineering populated departments of the institute with a total intake of 1000 students including B.tech, M.tech &amp; Phd students which is increasing in the preceding years. </p>', '<p><strong>Labs in this department includes :</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Steam Lab.</li>\r\n<li>Technical Dynamics Lab</li>\r\n<li>Metrology Lab</li>\r\n<li>Automobile Engineering Lab.</li>\r\n<li>Heat Transfer Lab.</li>\r\n<li>I.C.Engines Lab.</li>\r\n<li>Energy Lab.</li>\r\n<li>Computer Aided Design Lab.</li>\r\n<li>Refrigeration &amp; Air Conditioning lab.</li>\r\n<li>Metal Cutting Lab.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Workshops:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Machine shop</li>\r\n<li>Fitting shop</li>\r\n<li>Foundry shop</li>\r\n<li>Welding shop</li>\r\n</ul>', '<p><strong>Placement &amp; Business Opportunities</strong></p>\r\n<p>According to previous data 14-16 companies visited the department including core as well as non-core background. Due to overgrowing number of consultancies &amp; trading companies students are increasingly attracted towards the consulting &amp; marketing jobs.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Some of the previous recruiters are:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Accenture</li>\r\n<li>Amdocs</li>\r\n<li>Applied Materials</li>\r\n<li>Ashok Leyland</li>\r\n<li>Aspiring Mind</li>\r\n<li>Attos origin</li>\r\n<li>Bajaj Auto</li>\r\n<li>BALCO</li>\r\n<li>BHEL</li>\r\n<li>BirlaSoft</li>\r\n<li>BPCL Refinery</li>\r\n<li>Capgemini</li>\r\n<li>Capillary Tech</li>\r\n<li>C-Dot</li>\r\n<li>CIL</li>\r\n<li>Comviva</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>AVERAGE PACKAGE</strong> of the department was Rs <strong>4.5 lakhs p.a a</strong>nd <strong>HIGHEST PACKAGE</strong> was Rs<strong> 12.7 lakhs p.a.</strong></p>\r\n<p>A total of <strong>94.6%</strong> eligible students got placed in the year 2012-13.</p>', '<p>Faculty is highly qualified &amp; involved in diverse and verified fields of research.<br />Some faculty members have even served as guest editors of different reputed &amp; prestigious journals.<br />Publications of the research work in reputed journals &amp; presenting it at national and international conferences is a general activity.<br />Is involved in improving the quality of programmes offered by evolving new methods of structuring the curriculum &amp; discovering new methods of delivering it.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '<p><strong>The department has collaborations with certain universities like:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>The Consortium of National Institutes of Technology of India</li>\r\n<li>Helsinki University of Technology , Finland</li>\r\n<li>University of Oulu, Finland</li>\r\n<li>Tampere University of Tech., Finland</li>\r\n<li>University of Tamper, Finland</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '<p><strong>Conference and Seminars</strong></p>\r\n<p>An international conference on &ldquo;mechanical engineering: emerging trends for sustainability (IC MEETS) &ldquo;has been organised by the department which aims to provide a platform for research workers, academicians and industrialists involved in mechanical engineering to develop technologies which can help in meeting the needs of the population and industries sustainably.</p>', 'branchreview/see_branch_review.php?id=36', 'NIT9 Bhopal Mech Mechanical Engineering '),
(37, 'branchreview/img/branch_info37.jpeg', 'img/branch_info_b37.jpeg', 'NIT Bhopal ', 'Material Science and Metallurgical Engineering ', '<p>Department was established in the year 1965 and offers B.tech, M.tech and Phd courses in almost every field ofNIT Bhopal Metallurgical and Material Science diverse engineering. With the basic aim of providing quality education to its students the department is in high demand.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '<p><strong></strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Labs in the department includes:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Metallurgical Analysis</li>\r\n<li>Physical Metallurgy and Heat Treatment</li>\r\n<li>Electrometallurgy and Corrosion</li>\r\n<li>Extractive Metallurgy</li>\r\n<li>Powder Metallurgy and Nanomaterials</li>\r\n<li>Mechanical Metallurgy</li>\r\n<li>Materials Science and Plasma Nitriding</li>\r\n<li>Materials Testing</li>\r\n<li>Mineral Processing</li>\r\n</ul>', '<p><strong>Placement &amp; Business Opportunities</strong></p>\r\n<p>According to previous year records 12-15 companies visited campus for recruiting students from the department. 75.5% eligible students got placements in the year 2012-13 from the campus.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Some of the companies visited in the previous years are:</strong></p>\r\n<p>-SourceBits<br />-TATA Autocomp<br />-TATA Motors Ltd<br />-TATA Power<br />-TATA Teleservices<br />-Tata Tech<br />-TCIL, Delhi<br />-TCS<br />-Tech Mahindra<br />-Unisys<br />-Verizon<br />-Virtusa<br />-Volvo Eiocher<br />-Wipro Tech<br />-Zensar <br /> <br /><strong>Future scope and internships</strong></p>\r\n<p>The placement and training cell of NIT Bhopal ensures the placements of the placements of students and collaborates with leading institutes &amp; organisations in the setting up of internship &amp; training programme for the present students. The cell holds responsibility of placements and training and interacts with over 130 companies which visit the department for holding in campus interviews. The companies include core engineering firms, IT sector, manufacturing industries, consultancies, finance &amp; managerial companies, etc&hellip;</p>', '<p>A well dedicated team of faculty members is the real jewel of the department. Courses in the department teach basic studies of the processes &amp; machines regarding conversion of ores into metals &amp; finished products of metals</p>', '', '', 'branchreview/see_branch_review.php?id=37', 'NIT9 Bhopal Material Science Engineering and9 Metallurgical '),
(38, 'branchreview/img/branch_info38.jpeg', 'img/branch_info_b38.jpeg', 'NIT Calicut ', 'Chemical Engineering', '<p>This department has been set up with sanctioned intake capacity of sixty students at the undergraduate level .Loads of research work is being carried out within the department. In order to ensure unhindered development of department along with the academic performance an Industrial Advisory Committee is formed which would help the students in project management, entrepreneurship and in learning new technology.</p>', '<p><strong>In order to sync theoretical knowledge with practical knowledge the department is facilitated with following laboratories:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Fluid and Particle Mechanics Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>&nbsp;Chemical Technology Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Mechanical Operations Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>&nbsp;Heat Transfer Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>&nbsp;Mass Transfer Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>&nbsp;Environmental &amp; Pollution Control Laboratory&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Chemical Reaction Engineering &amp; Process Control Lab8.</li>\r\n<li>Computer Applications Laboratory </li>\r\n</ul>', '<p><strong>Placement Overview</strong></p>\r\n<p>Chemical is one of the core branches and a necessity of today, hence it experiences mass recruiters coming on campus and offering considerably good packages.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Some of the companies that visit NIT- Calicut for Chemical Engineering branch are listed below:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Bharat Petroleum</li>\r\n<li>Indian Oil Tanking Ltd</li>\r\n<li>Indian Oil Ltd</li>\r\n<li>Hindustan Petroleum</li>\r\n<li>ONGC</li>\r\n<li>Reliance</li>\r\n<li>Aditya Birla</li>\r\n<li>Cairn</li>\r\n<li>Binani Cements</li>\r\n<li>Saint Gobain</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Average Package:</strong> 4.2 LPA</p>\r\n<p><strong>Maximum Package</strong>: 6 LPA</p>\r\n<p><strong>Percentage Placement:</strong> Out of 51 students 21 were placed. (<strong>41%</strong>)</p>\r\n<p><strong>Branch Scenario:</strong></p>\r\n<p><em>Further Studies/Research Scope:</em></p>\r\n<p>One can hope for getting placed in PSU&rsquo;s through GATE scorecard. Also one can opt for CAT if he/she wants to pursue MBA. Another option is administrative services.Course Curriculum are upgraded as per new technology</p>\r\n<p>With regular research going on in every field and new results being developed every now and then, the teachers keep a track of all recent developments and also bring the same in notice of students. </p>', '<p>Faculties are highly qualified holding Ph.D.(Engg), M.tech from various reputed institutes. Around 09 Assistance professors and 1 technical staff are working here in order to ensure brighter future of students. </p>', '<p>The department aims to collaborate with various industries and institutes to help the students achieve the pinnacle and follow the path of success.</p>', '<p><strong>Conferences/Seminars</strong></p>\r\n<p>A large number of conferences are organized on a regular basis in the department. Some of them are mentioned below:<br />&bull; FDP ON CHANGING SCENARIO IN ENERGY&amp; ENVIRONMENT<br />&bull; FDP Programme on Recent Research trends in Chemical and Environmental Engineering </p>', 'branchreview/see_branch_review.php?id=38', ' NIT9 Calicut Chem Chemical Engineering '),
(39, 'branchreview/img/branch_info39.jpeg', 'img/branch_info_b39.jpeg', 'NIT Calicut ', 'Civil Engineering', '<p>Presently department offers one UG course in Civil Engineering and four PG courses in Structural Engineering, Traffic and Transportation Planning, Offshore Structures, and Environmental &nbsp;technology.</p>', '<p>Large number of efforts is being put in to give the best of education to students through high-tech labs and a healthy environment.</p>\r\n<p>1.Transportation <br />2.Environmental <br />3.Geology Laboratory and Museum <br />4.Structural Engineering <br />5.Water Resources and Offshore <br />6.Geotechnical <br />7.UG Computing Lab <br />8.Surveying </p>', '<p><strong>Placement &amp; Business Opportunities</strong></p>\r\n<p>Most of the core companies visit the campus and offer a considerably good package for a fresher. But one needs to pursue further studies for better job perspectives.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Name of Companies visiting campus for recruitment</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Brigade Constructions</li>\r\n<li>Condor Builders</li>\r\n<li>Mu Sigma</li>\r\n<li>Capgemini India</li>\r\n<li>Larsen and Tubro Ltd</li>\r\n<li>Gammon India</li>\r\n<li>JSPL</li>\r\n<li>Yashi Consulting</li>\r\n<li>Saint Gobain</li>\r\n<li>JSW Steel Ltd.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Average Package:</strong> 3.8 LPA<br /><strong>Maximum Package</strong>: 5 LPA<br /><strong>Percentage Placement:</strong> Out of 80 students 55 were placed. (<strong>69%</strong>)</p>\r\n<p><strong>Branch Scenario</strong></p>\r\n<p>One can opt for MBA by giving CAT exam, or Mtech by giving GATE exam or you can also pursue administrative services.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Course Curriculum-</strong> Courses are upgraded as per new technology</p>\r\n<p>A complete review of course is done regularly and is also done through feedback forms filled by students. Course in accordance with evolving technology is being taught in classroom sessions.</p>', '<p>Faculties are highly qualified holding Ph.D.(Engg), M.tech from various reputed institutes. Around 1 Professor and 08 Assistant professors and 01 technical staffs are working at the department to ensure development of department and students.</p>\r\n<p><strong>The department offers consultancy in following divisions:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Structural Design</li>\r\n<li>Material Testing and Certification</li>\r\n<li>Turn-key Projects</li>\r\n<li>Site Survey, Levelling, and Layout</li>\r\n<li>Hydrological Surveys</li>\r\n<li>Design of Hydraulic Structures</li>\r\n<li>Preparation of Project Proposals</li>\r\n<li>In-Situ Quality Assessment of Structures</li>\r\n</ul>', '<p>NIT Calicut aims to tie up with many industries as that would help students in research work and at the same time with some foreign universities to help in overall development of students.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '<p><strong>Branch Events/Conferences:</strong></p>\r\n<p>Many conferences are organized at NIT-Calicut to bring the students closer to evolving technology and also encourage them to do research. </p>', 'branchreview/see_branch_review.php?id=39', 'NIT9 Calicut Civil Engineering '),
(40, 'branchreview/img/branch_info40.jpeg', 'img/branch_info_b40.jpeg', 'NIT Calicut', 'Computer Science and Engineering ', '<p>Department of Computer Science and Engineering is comparatively the most developed department of all. &nbsp;It offers UG and PG courses in Computer Science as well as a Doctoral Course. With evolving technology the department has experienced growth in terms of research activities. Research is carried out on almost all the major areas of research.</p>', '<p><strong>Well Equipped laboratories are a necessity for any branch. Following laboratories are a part of the department:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Software Systems Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>&nbsp;Network Systems Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Hardware &amp; Embedded Systems Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>&nbsp;Secure Computing Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>&nbsp;Computational Intelligence Laboratory.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Image Processing &amp; Multimedia Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Biocomputing Research Laboratory</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '<p><strong>Placement Overview</strong></p>\r\n<p>CS being one of the highly paid branches coupled with that the college is a NIT (especially when its NIT-Calicut with 100% placement in the past years) results in top companies visiting the campus. So what an average Computer Science student can expect is to get placed at a considerable good package in a core company.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Some of the companies that visit NIT- Calicut for CS branch are listed below:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Infosys </li>\r\n<li>Cognizant </li>\r\n<li>TCS </li>\r\n<li>Wipro</li>\r\n<li>Oracle </li>\r\n<li>Google </li>\r\n<li>Facebook </li>\r\n<li>Microsoft </li>\r\n<li>Adobe</li>\r\n<li>Amazon</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Average Package:</strong> 7.42 LPA</p>\r\n<p><strong>Maximum Package:</strong> 16 LPA</p>\r\n<p><strong>Percentage Placement:</strong> Out of 90 students 87 were placed. (<strong>97%</strong>)</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>There are a few companies which come on campus to hire interns. Few of them are:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>&nbsp;Amazon</li>\r\n<li>ArbitrinApple Inc</li>\r\n<li>Broadcom Communications Technologies Private LImited</li>\r\n<li>&nbsp;Bharat Sanjar Nigam Ltd.</li>\r\n<li>Ericpol IOOO</li>\r\n<li>Goldman Sachs Services Private Limited</li>\r\n<li>IISER</li>\r\n<li>Information Sciences Institute, University of Southern California</li>\r\n<li>IIST</li>\r\n<li>&nbsp;IIT</li>\r\n<li>&nbsp;ITC Ltd.</li>\r\n<li>Kuwait Oil Company</li>\r\n<li>MIT AITI Labs &amp; Google</li>\r\n<li>MIT &amp; GOOGLE Program India</li>\r\n<li>SAP Labs India Pvt Ltd.</li>\r\n<li>Tata Consultancy Services</li>\r\n<li>Tech-Hue</li>\r\n<li>Texas Instruments</li>\r\n<li>Vikram Sarabhai Space Centre</li>\r\n<li>Weatherford</li>\r\n<li>Zaizi,Asia / Pacific Office</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Branch Scenario:</strong></p>\r\n<p><em>Further Studies/Research Scope</em></p>\r\n<p>Computer Science enthusiasts and graduates are sometimes placed in sectors like Information Technology, System management and Banking. Most frequently students prefer investing in their own start-ups. Options like Gate and Cat are open for students who want to pursue their masters.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Course Curriculum</strong>- Courses are upgraded as per new technology</p>\r\n<p>With evolving technology in computers course upgradation is done on a regular basis. </p>', '<p>Faculties are highly qualified holding Ph.D and M.tech from various reputed institutes. Around 3 professors and 21 Assistant professors and 05 technical staffs work intermittently in the department.</p>\r\n<p>Various international Journals, conferences and seminars add glories to the name of department faculties.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Research is being carried out in following areas:</strong></p>\r\n<p>&bull; Algorithms and Complexity<br />&bull; Bioinformatics<br />&bull; Compilers and Programming languages<br />&bull; Computer Architecture<br />&bull; Database Management Systems<br />&bull; Distributed Computing<br />&bull; Image Processing<br />&bull; Information Security<br />&bull; Networks<br />&bull; Operating Systems</p>', '<p>The Department aims at collaborating with leading industries to facilitate research work.</p>', '<p><strong>Conferences/Seminars</strong></p>\r\n<p>Various conferences are organized at department to encourage learning in students. Association of Computing Machinery (ACM) is a student body started in Nit Calicut in 2012 which in association with Computer Science and Engineering Association (CSEA), NIT Calicut conducts various technical talks, programming contests and workshops. CSEA has concentrated towards academic development over years by means of competitions, workshops and lectures by eminent personalities. </p>', 'branchreview/see_branch_review.php?id=40', 'NIT9 Calicut Computer Science Engineering CS99 CSE9 Computers'),
(41, 'branchreview/img/branch_info41.jpeg', 'img/branch_info_b41.jpeg', '  NIT Calicut', ' Electrical Engineering ', '<p>The department was established in the year 1961 and offers UG, PG and doctorate courses in Electrical Engineering. Mtech degree is offered in Electrical Engineering on specialization in a particular field which will be mentioned on the degree certificate. The master level courses are (i) Instrumentation &amp; Control Systems (ii) Power Systems (iii) Power Electronics and (iv) Industrial Power and Automation. Ph.D degree is offered as a result of research work in Electrical Engineering and Control Systems. Along with this the department organizes programs for the development of faculty which are short term training programmes. </p>', '<p>Well-equipped and regularly maintained laboratories are a quality of the department.</p>\r\n<p><strong>The department comprises of following labs:</strong></p>\r\n<p>1.Electrical Machines Laboratory <br />2.Electrical Measurements Laboratory <br />3.Control Systems Laboratory <br />4.Electronics Circuits Laboratory<br />5.Electrical and Electronics Workshop</p>', '<p><strong>Placement Overview</strong></p>\r\n<p>Electrical being one of the core branches and a necessity of today is one of the highly paid branches and has a lot of scope in terms of future growth. Also a large number of companies visit the campus regularly to hire electrical engineers and offer quite a good amount of money.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Some of the companies that visit NITC for Electrical branch are listed below:</strong></p>\r\n<p>1. HPCL-Mittal Energy Ltd. (HMEL)</p>\r\n<p>2. Infosys</p>\r\n<p>3. TATA Power-DDL</p>\r\n<p>4. ABCI</p>\r\n<p>5. Finisar</p>\r\n<p>6. Mu Sigma</p>\r\n<p>7. Capgemini</p>\r\n<p>8. IOCL</p>\r\n<p>9. HCL</p>\r\n<p>10. JSPL</p>\r\n<p><strong>Average Package:</strong> 5.2 LPA<br /><strong>Maximum Package</strong>: 6 LPA<br /><strong>Percentage Placement:</strong> Out of 83 students 75 were placed. (90%)</p>\r\n<p><strong>Branch Scenario:</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Further Studies/Research Scope</strong></p>\r\n<p>Options like Gate and Cat are open for students who want to pursue their masters.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Course Curriculum-</strong> Courses are upgraded as per new technology</p>\r\n<p>With evolving technology in electronic media course upgradation is done on a regular basis. </p>', '<p>Faculties are highly qualified holding Ph.D.(Engg), M.tech from various reputed institutes. Around 11 Professors and 15 Assistant professors and around 11 technical staffs work here for long hours for the betterment of department.</p>\r\n<p><br /><strong>Following are the main areas of research:-</strong><br />&bull; Power &amp; Energy Systems<br />&bull; Electric Machines &amp; Power Electronics<br />&bull; Control System and Instrumentation Engineering</p>', '<p>Efforts are being put in to tie up with industries and foreign universities to ensure a brighter future for students. Department has already completed many research projects sponsored by the Industries and Department of Science &amp; Technology, Ministry of Human Resource and Developments.</p>', '<p><strong>Conferences/Seminars</strong></p>\r\n<p>Various conferences are held on evolving technology to bring forth the students various research arenas and developments. These are being organized by Industrial Power and Automation Group, a group created within department. </p>', 'branchreview/see_branch_review.php?id=41', 'NIT9 Calicut Electrical Engineering EE99 ');
INSERT INTO `branch_review` (`id`, `img`, `b_img`, `clg`, `branch`, `intro`, `infa_labs`, `branch_scope`, `branch_faculty`, `col`, `about`, `url`, `tags`) VALUES
(42, 'branchreview/img/branch_info42.jpeg', 'img/branch_info_b42.jpeg', 'NIT Calicut ', 'Mechanical Engineering ', '<p>Prominently Mechanical Engineering Department is the largest Department at NITC. It offers not only UG, PG and doctoral NIT Calicut Mechanical Engineering degree courses but also part time doctoral degree course for those who are employed and are working. It also provides Summer/Winter Schools which are sponsored by AICTE. The department is blessed to have a very talented faculty which provide guest lectures to nearby colleges as well. Besides the regular teaching schedule the faculty does consultancy work, they work on research projects and also on product development. </p>', '<p>Well Equipped laboratories are a necessity for any branch. Regular maintenance is being done in order to ensure latest technologies at the footsteps of students.</p>\r\n<p><strong> The department comprises of following labs:</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\\"padding-left: 30px;\\">&bull; Fluid Mechanics Laboratory</p>\r\n<p style=\\"padding-left: 30px;\\">&bull; Industrial Engineering Laboratory</p>\r\n<p style=\\"padding-left: 30px;\\">&bull; Materials Science &amp; Technology Laboratory</p>\r\n<p style=\\"padding-left: 30px;\\">&bull; Production Engineering Laboratory</p>\r\n<p style=\\"padding-left: 30px;\\">&bull; Industrial Engineering Laboratory</p>\r\n<p style=\\"padding-left: 30px;\\">&bull; Fluid Machinery Laboratory</p>\r\n<p style=\\"padding-left: 30px;\\">&bull; Solar Energy Centre</p>\r\n<p style=\\"padding-left: 30px;\\">&bull; Advanced Manufacturing Centre</p>\r\n<p style=\\"padding-left: 30px;\\">&bull; Tribology, Vibration &amp; Acoustics Laboratory</p>\r\n<p style=\\"padding-left: 30px;\\">&bull; Thermal Science Laboratory</p>\r\n<p style=\\"padding-left: 30px;\\">&bull; Heat Engines Laboratory</p>\r\n<p style=\\"padding-left: 30px;\\">&bull; Heat Treatment Laboratory</p>', '<p><strong>Placement Overview</strong></p>\r\n<p>Mechanical being one of the oldest branches has seen a large scale of growth over years in terms of companies visiting the campus and in terms of package offered. With the sudden boom in technology companies want individuals who have knowledge in accordance with modern technology.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Some of the companies that visit NITC for Mechanical branch are listed below:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>TATA Motors</li>\r\n<li>Capgemini</li>\r\n<li>IOCL</li>\r\n<li>Maruti Suzuki</li>\r\n<li>TATA Autocomp</li>\r\n<li>SKF</li>\r\n<li>Subros</li>\r\n<li>Stone India</li>\r\n<li>JSPL</li>\r\n<li>Voltas</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Average Package:</strong> 5.4 LPA</p>\r\n<p><strong>Maximum Package</strong>: 6 LPA</p>\r\n<p><strong>Percentage Placement:</strong> Out of 89 students 77 were placed. (<strong>87%</strong>)</p>\r\n<p><strong>Branch Scenario:</strong></p>\r\n<p><em>Further Studies/Research Scope</em></p>\r\n<p>If one wants to pursue further studies loads of doors are open like Mtech, MBA and IAS with each field having its own pros and cons.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Course Curriculum-</strong> Courses are upgraded as per new technology</p>\r\n<p>With evolving technology in machines course upgradation is done on a regular basis. </p>', '<p>Faculties are highly qualified holding Ph.D. and M.tech from various reputed institutions. Around 15 professors and 24 Assistant professors work for long hours here.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Following are the publications of the eminent faculties of the department:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Books Published</li>\r\n<li>Journal Papers</li>\r\n<li>Papers Published in Conference Proceedings</li>\r\n</ul>', '<p>With Universities (Indian/Foreign): The department aims at collaborating with various foreign universities to offer the best of knowledge to students.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Various organizations have collaborations with Department. Some of them are:</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\\"padding-left: 30px;\\">1. MHRD : Ministry of Human Resources Development, Government of India<br />2. UGC : University Grants Commission<br />3. BRNS : Board of Research in Nuclear Sciences<br />4. DST : Department of Science and Technology</p>', '<p><strong>Conferences/Seminars</strong></p>\r\n<p>A large number of conferences are organized to encourage the students to do research in various fields and help them strengthen their concepts. Workshop on Statistical Analysis for Research on 6th October 2012 by MED, NITC was organized as a part of academic curriculum. </p>', 'branchreview/see_branch_review.php?id=42', 'NIT9 Calicut Mech Mechanical Engineering '),
(43, 'branchreview/img/branch_info43.jpeg', 'img/branch_info_b43.jpeg', 'NIT Calicut', ' Electronics and Communication Engineering ', '<p>This Department was initially a part of Electrical Engineering Department and it became a separate department in 1997. UGNIT Calicut Electronics and Communication Engineering course in ECE was initiated in the year 1980 in Department of Electrical Engineering and a PG course was commenced in 1994. With a rapid growth in the department it was further made into a separate department. Over the years the department has experienced immense growth in terms of faculty, infrastructure and academics.</p>', '<p>Well Equipped laboratories are a necessity for any branch. Regular maintenance is being done in order to ensure latest technologies at the footsteps of students.</p>\r\n<p><strong>The department comprises of following labs:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Electronics Workshop</li>\r\n<li>Electronics Circuits Lab</li>\r\n<li>Integrated Circuits Lab</li>\r\n<li>Embedded Systems Lab</li>\r\n<li>Communication Lab</li>\r\n<li>Signal Processing and Communication Lab</li>\r\n<li>Digital Signal Processing Lab</li>\r\n<li>Simulation Lab</li>\r\n<li>Telecommunication Technology Lab</li>\r\n<li>DST-FIST Lab</li>\r\n<li>Microelectronics and VLSI Lab</li>\r\n<li>PSoC Lab</li>\r\n</ul>', '<p><strong>Placement Overview</strong></p>\r\n<p>ECE being next to CS in terms of popularity and demand is another highly paid branches. Students with average performance get placed easily in any core company at a considerably good package.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Some of the companies that visit NITC for ECE branch are listed below:</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\\"padding-left: 30px;\\">1. Samsung India Software Operations</p>\r\n<p style=\\"padding-left: 30px;\\">2. Mu Sigma</p>\r\n<p style=\\"padding-left: 30px;\\">3. Virtuse</p>\r\n<p style=\\"padding-left: 30px;\\">4. Capgemini India</p>\r\n<p style=\\"padding-left: 30px;\\">5. Infosys</p>\r\n<p style=\\"padding-left: 30px;\\">6. Tech Mahindra Satyam</p>\r\n<p style=\\"padding-left: 30px;\\">7. HCL</p>\r\n<p style=\\"padding-left: 30px;\\">8. Power Wave</p>\r\n<p style=\\"padding-left: 30px;\\">9. Rancore Technologies</p>\r\n<p style=\\"padding-left: 30px;\\">10. Huawei Technologies</p>\r\n<p><strong>Average Package:</strong> 6.3 LPA</p>\r\n<p><strong>Maximum Package:</strong> 12 LPA</p>\r\n<p><strong>Percentage Placement:</strong> Out of 84 students 81 were placed. (97%)</p>\r\n<p><strong>Branch Scenario</strong></p>\r\n<p><em>Further Studies/Research Scope</em></p>\r\n<p>A branch as good as ECE always hold the option of further studies within it. A student who wants to pursue further studies has various doors open in front of him keeping in mind that he has pursued his/her btech from an institute of utmost reputation of an NIT.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Course Curriculum-</strong> Courses are upgraded as per new technology</p>\r\n<p>With evolving technology in media of communication course upgradation is done on a regular basis. </p>', '<p>Faculties are highly qualified, holding PHD/M.tech from various reputed institutes. The department comprises of 4 Professor, 6 Associate Professors and more than 14 Assistant professors.<br />Faculties have presented various publications in National conferences, IEEE, IITs etc. </p>', '<p>The Department aims at collaborating with various industries and universities to ensure development of department and students.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '<p><strong>Conferences/Seminars:</strong></p>\r\n<p>Various conferences on communication systems are being organized on a regular basis to enhance the knowledge of students. </p>', 'branchreview/see_branch_review.php?id=43', 'NIT9 Calicut Electronics and9 Communication Engineering ECE9'),
(44, 'branchreview/img/branch_info44.jpeg', 'img/branch_info_b44.jpeg', 'NIT Durgapur', 'Chemical Engineering ', '<p>The Department of Chemical Engineering of National Institute of Technology, Durgapur, was established with active support of UNESCO. A number of equipment and instruments were donated by UNESCO to the department.The Post-graduate programme with the specialisation \\''Production Fertilisers\\'', along with the doctoral programme in Chemical Engineering. The department has a sanctioned intake of 30 students for the B.E. course per year. For admission to the M. Tech. course, 10 seats are available in regular full-time course with a duration of 1.5 years, while 10 seats are reserved for part-time students from industries with a course duration of 3 years. Cirriculum and syllabi of the courses offered were continuously updated over the years to keep pace with rapidly changing technological developments.<br />To impart quality technical and scientific education and produce engineers, technologists, scientists and citizens who will contribute meaningfully to the growth and development of the country and excel in various disciplines of knowledge.</p>', '<p><strong>There are 10 well-developed laboratories in the department of Chemical Engineering. They are:</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\\"padding-left: 30px;\\">1.Heat &amp; Mass Transfer Laboratory<br />2.Fluid Flow &amp; Mechanical Operations Laboratory<br />3.Computing Laboratory<br />4.Energy Laboratory<br />5.Chemical &amp; Bio-Chemical Reaction Engineering Laboratory<br />6.Process Control Laboratory<br />7.Environmental Engineering &amp; Membrane Technology Laboratory<br />8.Combustion Engineering Laboratory<br />9.Multi-phase Flow Laboratory<br />10.Central Research Laboratory</p>', '<p><strong>Research Areas</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\\"padding-left: 30px;\\">1.Transport Phenomena, Computer Aided Design, Bioprocess Engineering, Energy Engineering<br />Fluidization, Multiphase Flow, Mass Transfer (Spl. Interest: Solid waste management &amp; Energy Management)<br />2.Mathematical Modelling, Combustion &amp; Gasification of Coal &amp; Biomass..<br />Process Intensification through membrane technology, Industrial wastewater treatment, Arsenic removal technology development.<br />3.Multiphase Flow, Slurry Flow Modelling<br />4.Environmental Bio-Engineering, Bio-Reaction Engineering.<br />5.Modelling and Simulation of Pyrolysis, Combustion and Gasification of Coal and Biomass.<br />6.Environmental Engineering, Biochemical Reaction Engineering<br />7.Thermodynamics, Process Heat Transfer, Environmental Energy, Biotechnology<br />8.Boiling Two-phase Flow, Analysis of time series, Optimization &amp; Control<br />9.Membrane Separation Processes, Petroleum Refinery, Mass Transfer Operation, Modeling, 10.Simulation and Optimization, Biosensor, Nano catalyst<br />11.Membrane Separation, Fermentation Technology, Bioprocess Engineering<br />12.Multiphase Flow, Adsorption, Environment Engineering</p>', '', '', '', 'branchreview/see_branch_review.php?id=44', 'NIT9 Durgapur Chem Chemical Engineering '),
(45, 'branchreview/img/branch_info45.jpeg', 'img/branch_info_b45.jpeg', 'NIT Durgapur', 'Civil Engineering', '<p>It is one of the oldest functioning Departments with UG course since inception. The Department started imparting instruction leading to M.Tech Degree since 1956 with its highly qualified faculties and well equipped state-of-the-art UG labs and one PG Laboratory. Presently the Department is acting as State Technical Agency (STA) under Pradhan Mantri Gram Sadak Yojana (PMGSY). The Department is also engaged in regular testing and consultancy activities in various fields of Civil Engineering.&nbsp;</p>', '<p><strong>Laboratories in the department:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Concrete and Structural Engineering</li>\r\n<li>Highway Engineering</li>\r\n<li>Surveying</li>\r\n<li>Environmental Engineering</li>\r\n<li>Soil Mechanics and Foundation Engineering</li>\r\n<li>Rock Mechanics and Water Resources Engineering</li>\r\n</ul>', '', '', '', '', 'branchreview/see_branch_review.php?id=45', 'NIT9 Durgapur Civil Engineering '),
(46, 'branchreview/img/branch_info46.jpeg', 'img/branch_info_b46.jpeg', 'NIT Durgapur', 'Computer Science and Engineering', '<p>Department started imparting instructions with the most modern curricula and syllabus to the students offer undergraduate courses and post graduate course . The Department maintains an excellent teaching/learning and research environment with dedicated, qualified and dynamic faculties and well equiped laboratories.</p>\r\n<p>The Department of Computer Science and Engineering (CSE) embodies the university\\''s tradition of excellence in engineering education. CSE Graduates capture leading academic appointments as well as opportunities in renowned computer industries.</p>\r\n<p>The newly build s department includes highly sophisticated VLSI laboratory,Embedded Systems laboratory, Soft computing and Networking laboratories. Robotics, mobile communication, natural language processing are the broad areas into which the researchers have made a foray.</p>', '<p><strong>Laboratories in the department :</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Database</li>\r\n<li>Programming</li>\r\n<li>Internet</li>\r\n<li>VLSI</li>\r\n<li>Computer Graphics &amp; vision</li>\r\n<li>Microprocessor &amp; Computer Organization</li>\r\n</ul>', '', '', '', '', 'branchreview/see_branch_review.php?id=46', 'NIT9 Durgapur Computer Science Engineering CS99 CSE9 Computers'),
(47, 'branchreview/img/branch_info47.jpeg', 'img/branch_info_b47.jpeg', 'NIT Durgapur', 'Electrical Engineering', '<p>Presently the department offer B. Tech in Electrical Engineering, with intake capacity of 100 students, M. Tech in Power Systems and Power Electronics &amp; Machine Drives, each have intake 20 students, and PhD program. The department has 17 qualified and highly motivated faculty members with various specializations, is equipped with around 15 different laboratories, and among these 8 laboratories has modern state of the art facilities for research and consultancy work. The department also has strong regional and foreign collaboration. </p>', '', '<p><strong>Research Activities</strong></p>\r\n<p>The department is continuously contributing novel and innovative ideas in Electrical Engineering to keep pace with the latest technological developments. The department adapted modern state of the art teaching methodology, various online courses and pedagogy courses are presently being developed with the fund from NMEICT. Faculty members and a total 25 number of research scholars are deeply engaged with research activities in diverse emerging areas. In credit, departments own number of patents, sponsored projects, books and journal publication with reputed publishers. The department also has strong collaboration with various universities at national and international level. The department regularly organizes invited lectures, seminars, conferences &amp; short-term courses by experts from academia &amp; industries in various fields of Electrical Engineering.</p>\r\n<p><br /><strong>List the Ongoing Research :</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Research on DGA, Gas Sensors.</li>\r\n<li>Research on Drives and Control.</li>\r\n<li>System and method of stable rotation of a magnetically levitated ferromagnetic body.</li>\r\n<li>Online monitoring of Transformer.</li>\r\n<li>Power Electronics, Multilevel Converter.</li>\r\n<li>Optimization applied to DGS Power Systems.</li>\r\n<li>Optimization applied to ELD, Unit Commitment, OPF, AGC, PSS and Renewable Energy Sources of Power Systems.</li>\r\n<li>Path tracing of Mobile Robot.</li>\r\n<li>Control of power electronics converter.</li>\r\n<li>Optimization applied to AGC with FACTS in Power Systems.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '', '', '', 'branchreview/see_branch_review.php?id=47', 'NIT9 Durgapur Electrical Engineering EE99 '),
(48, 'branchreview/img/branch_info48.jpeg', 'img/branch_info_b48.jpeg', 'NIT Durgapur', 'Electronics and Communication Engineering', '<p>The embryonic formation of the Department of Electronics and Communication Engineering was in the year 1983 with the introduction of an undergraduate course. Apart from the four years B. Tech course the Department also offers two full time M.Tech courses, one in Telecommunication Engineering and another in Microelectronics and VLSI. The Department also offers PhD in several areas. The faculties are engaged in research in diverse topics focussing in Telecommunication, Antenna and Microwave, Microelectronics and VLSI, Signal and Image processing and Computational Systems Biology. It is well equipped with sophisticated laboratories in the areas of VLSI, Signal Processing, Microwave, Antenna and Wireless Communication. The Department has been supported by, SMDP for VLSI, DST-FIST for Wireless Communications and NPMASS for MEMS Research.</p>\r\n<p>Sponsored research from research initiation grant as well as DST and SERB have been initiated over the years. The Department has also received fund from TEQIP for its development. There are a significant number of institute research scholars presently carrying out PhD under the supervision of faculties while several part time research scholars are also registered for the PhD program. A large number of PhD has already been produced by the Department. The research strength has been reflected by quality publications of the Department. Faculties of the Department are involved in outreach activities by organizing several short term courses, workshops. Faculty members also have academic collaborations with Universities in and outside India. The Department is committed to impart quality education at undergraduate as well as postgraduate level and promulgate quality research in diverse fields of application of electronics engineering.</p>', '<p>Laboratories</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Basic Electronics Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Communication Engineering Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Power Electronics and Instrumentation Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Digital Electronics Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Microwave Egineering Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Microprocessor Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>PCB and Computer Laboratory</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>The department is going to set up laboratories in the field of VLSI, Mobile Communication and Digital Signal Processing</p>', '', '', '', '', 'branchreview/see_branch_review.php?id=48', 'NIT9 Durgapur Electronics and9 Communication Engineering ECE9'),
(49, 'branchreview/img/branch_info49.jpeg', 'img/branch_info_b49.jpeg', 'NIT Durgapur', 'Mechanical Engineering', '<p>Department of Mechanical Engineering is the largest and one of the oldest departments of the Institute started in the year 1960. It offers both undergraduate (B.Tech.) and postgraduate (M.Tech.) degree course apart from doctoral programme.</p>\r\n<p>The annual intake of the UG course is 150+ and that of the PG course is 20+ for each specialization.At present about 14 students are doing there doctoral research with the department. The department comprises of well-qualified faculty, supporting staff and suitably equipped laboratory. The continuous development of faculty and up gradation of the laboratories makes the department at per with the current day academic and research requirement of global standard which is reflected by continuously increasing student of the department opting for higher studies in India and abroad.</p>\r\n<p>Department of Mechanical Engineering offers three PG course with specialization: Machine Design, Thermal Engineering, Fluid Mechanics &amp; Heat transfer. For the benefit of the students who are at the Industry or in other Institute nearby, the department runs a parallel module of part time course. This overview contains the curriculum of the UG and PG courses, profile of the faculty, a list of the laboratories and the publications for the last two years by the faculty.</p>', '<p><strong>Laboratories:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Production Engineering Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Thermal Energy Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Heat Power Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Controls Laboratory (Under Restructuring)</li>\r\n<li>CAD/CAM Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Metrology Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Robotics &amp; A.I. Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Machine Computation &amp; Computer Graphics Laboratory</li>\r\n</ul>', '', '', '', '', 'branchreview/see_branch_review.php?id=49', 'NIT9 Durgapur Mech Mechanical Engineering '),
(50, 'branchreview/img/branch_info50.jpeg', 'img/branch_info_b50.jpeg', 'NIT Hamirpur', 'Chemical Engineering', '<p><strong>About Department:</strong><br />The department of Chemical Engineering was established in the year 2013. The department offers four years B. Tech programme in Chemical Engineering with a total intake of 60 students. The admission to the B. Tech. program is done only through the JEE (Joint Entrance Examination) main score . The department comprises of ten different laboratories for the undergraduates catering to the needs of the curriculum. In addition, analytical instruments, computer facilities and research laboratories for the postgraduates and doctoral resources are under process. All the faculties are well dedicated to teaching and involve themselves in research in various fields of chemical engineering as well as in different interdisciplinary areas of engineering.</p>\r\n<p><strong>VISION OF THE DEPARTMENT:</strong></p>\r\n<p>To make brilliant Chemical Engineers to tackle the challenges of chemical and allied industries with responsibility towards the society and environment.</p>\r\n<p><strong>MISSION OF THE DEPARTMENT:</strong></p>\r\n<p>To provide high quality education through research and innovation to meet the needs of the industry.<br />To develop the new technology through high quality research in various fields.</p>', '', '<p><strong>Research &amp; Development:</strong><br />As this is a new department Collaborations and Research Funding developments are underway. In this regard the department has also initiated the process for research collaborations and research funding and proposal writings.</p>', '', '', '<p><strong>Guest Lecture:</strong><br />The department organizes guest Lectures for the enrichment of technical knowledge of students. In this regard the department has organized a guest Lecture by the Professor and Head of the Department, Chemical Engineering, NIT, Jalandhar in the month of September, 2015.</p>', 'branchreview/see_branch_review.php?id=50', 'NIT9 Hamirpur Chem Chemical Engineering '),
(51, 'branchreview/img/branch_info51.jpeg', 'img/branch_info_b51.jpeg', 'NIT Hamirpur', 'Civil Engineering', '<p>National Institute of Technology, Hamirpur was established in the year 1986. Civil Engineering can be considered as a single largest branch among all the engineering branches. Being one of the primary Engineering Departments of the Institute, the Department of Civil Engineering offers B. Tech., M. Tech. and Ph.D. degrees programmes, accredited by National Board of Accreditation for five years since January 2008 and has been imparting quality education to its students.<br /> <br /><strong>Objective</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>To provide quality education and training to our graduates to cope up with international standards.</li>\r\n<li>To conduct regular continuing education and community development programmes.</li>\r\n<li>To provide extension and consultancy services to Government, private, public and industrial sectors.</li>\r\n<li>To excel in Industrial Research and consultancy with appropriate national and International linkages and to maintain highest standards in the field of Civil Engineering.</li>\r\n<li>To be the best-rated departments in India and world in terms of teaching and quality, research contributions, high-end consultancy and academic leadership.</li>\r\n</ul>', '<p><strong>The Department of civil engineering has well equipped laboratories in the specialized areas:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Material Testing Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Structural Analysis Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Geotechnical Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Transportation Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Hydraulic &amp; Irrigation Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Environmental Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Surveying Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Geology Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Computational Laboratory</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>List of major equipments and software in various laboratories</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Material Testing Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Aggregate Crushing Value Apparatus</li>\r\n<li>Briquete Mould</li>\r\n<li>Cement Autoclave</li>\r\n<li>Compaction Factor Apparatus</li>\r\n<li>Concrete Core Cutter</li>\r\n<li>Concrete Flexural Strength Testing Machine</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '', '', '', '', 'branchreview/see_branch_review.php?id=51', 'NIT9 Hamirpur Civil Engineering '),
(52, 'branchreview/img/branch_info52.jpeg', 'img/branch_info_b52.jpeg', 'NIT Hamirpur', 'Computer Science & Engineering', '<p>Established in 1989 as the Department of Computer Science &amp; Engineering,have an excellent &amp; rich history and an outstanding record of contributions to the profession and community. The Department is well recognized for excellence in facilities and teaching.</p>\r\n<p>The aim of these programmes is to enable students to acquire specialized knowledge for various subjects in computer science &amp; information technology, as well as to enrich the students personal, social and cognitive development to meet challenges of today and tomorrow. The Department is well equipped with high end computers, latest software &amp; state-of-the-art IT infrastructure and all these computing resources are inter-connected with high speed intranet. faculty is involved in cutting-edge research areas, including computer networks, mobile computing, mobile ad hoc networks, wireless sensor networks, security, image processing, data mining, artificial intelligence, computer architecture and reconfigurable computing. The Department prides itself on good career opportunities for students. Our students graduate with more than 100% placement through campus.</p>', '', '', '', '', '', 'branchreview/see_branch_review.php?id=52', 'NIT9 Hamirpur Computer Science Engineering CS99 CSE9 Computers'),
(53, 'branchreview/img/branch_info53.jpeg', 'img/branch_info_b53.jpeg', 'NIT Hamirpur', 'Electronics & Communication Engineering', '<p>Established in the year 1988, the Electronics &amp; Communication Engineering (E&amp;CE) Department NIT Hamirpur . The information and technology revolution has been built on the advances of Electronics. The E&amp;CE Department takes pride in its high national rankings and the international recognition its faculty has received from their peers.</p>\r\n<p>Department is making exhilarating progress in areas ranging from microelectronics, mobile communications to VLSI Design Automation. In labs and classrooms, students draw on the expertise and knowledge of our able faculty, integrating practical, hands-on research experience with challenging and interesting course-work. The team approach is very warm in the Department of E&amp;CE. A palpable excitement surrounds the Department of E&amp;CE, an enthusiasm pervades every classroom and lab, invigorating our students and spurring on our faculty to fresh innovations.</p>\r\n<p><br /><strong>Major goals are:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>To inculcate harmonious and respectful environment.</li>\r\n<li>Service to society and global community.</li>\r\n<li>Develop a culture of group responsibility for mentoring E&amp;CE students.</li>\r\n<li>Passion to respond to rapidly changing social and economic environment.</li>\r\n<li>The direct impact of the program is to develop an allround personality of the students graduating in E&amp;CE.</li>\r\n</ul>', '<p><strong>The department has following labs:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Basic Electronics lab</li>\r\n<li>Digital Electronics &amp; Analog Electronics labs</li>\r\n<li>Industrial Electronics lab</li>\r\n<li>Computer and Embedded System lab</li>\r\n<li>Microwave lab </li>\r\n<li>TV and DSP labs</li>\r\n<li>Communication lab</li>\r\n<li>Advanced Electronics &amp; Simulation lab</li>\r\n<li>Very Large Scale Integration (VLSI ) Design Lab</li>\r\n<li>Linear Integrated Circuit (LIC) Lab</li>\r\n</ul>', '<p><strong>SPONSORED PROJECTS:</strong></p>\r\n<p>Department of Electronics &amp; Communication Engineering, NIT Hamirpur jointly with Dept. of CSE has received an all India Project on Special Manpower Development Programme for VLSI Design &amp; related software (SMDP-II) for a period of six (6) years w.e.f. 2006 from the Ministry of Communication and Information Technology, Department of Information Technology, Govt. of India, New Delhi. It is an important and prestigious project through which quality manpower in the area of VLSI Design and related softwares is planned to be created, to cater to the pressing demand of VLSI Engineers and Designers in the country.&nbsp;</p>', '', '', '', 'branchreview/see_branch_review.php?id=53', 'NIT9 Hamirpur Electronics and9 Communication Engineering ECE9'),
(54, 'branchreview/img/branch_info54.jpeg', 'img/branch_info_b54.jpeg', 'NIt Hamirpur', 'Electrical Engineering', '<p>Electrical Engineering Department, established in the year 1986. The department has been imparting quality education at undergraduate and post graduate level. The faculty members has been active in teaching and research activities. Various departmental laboratories have been strengthened and modernized by procuring state of art equipments. The department is equipped with the latest experimental and computational facilities for taking up R&amp;D and consultancy activities in different areas of electrical engineering.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Vision :</strong></p>\r\n<p>The vision of the Department of Electrical Engineering is to provide excellent technical education in the field of Electrical Engineering and to produce proficient engineers, professionals and researchers with ethical values and attitude towards continuous learning.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Mission :</strong></p>\r\n<p>To provide students with a supportive environment that facilitates in imparting quality and value based education in the area of Electrical and Electronics Engineering and to apply engineering principles to solve real world problems.<br />To prepare students to contribute in professional career and social services with high ethical values and with life-long learning approach and be successful as they move into occupation, research and advanced studies. .</p>', '<p><strong>Laboratory :</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Basic Electrical Lab</li>\r\n<li>Microprocessor Lab</li>\r\n<li>Circuit Theory lab</li>\r\n<li>Computer and Simulation Lab</li>\r\n<li>Instrumentation and Measurement Lab</li>\r\n<li>Electrical Machine Lab</li>\r\n<li>Control Engineering Lab</li>\r\n<li>Power System Lab</li>\r\n<li>Power Electronics Lab</li>\r\n<li>High Voltage Lab</li>\r\n<li>Signal Processing and Biomedical Instrumentation Lab</li>\r\n</ul>', '<p><strong>Projects going on in Electrical Engineering Department:</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\\"padding-left: 30px;\\">-A research project titled Hydrothermal Scheduling Using Artificial Intelligence Techniques sponsored by CSIR <br />-A consultancy project on Development of Software package for Hydro Operation Scheduling and Optimization sponsored by BHEL Banglore <br />-Congestion Management of Restructured Power Sector with renewable Energy Source under the scheme of Research &amp; Development. <br />- Modernization of Existing High Voltage Lab under MODROB <br />- Contingency Screening and Ranking for Voltage Stability under Research &amp; Design Scheme.<br />-Modernization of Existing Power Electronics Laboratory under MODROBS</p>\r\n<p style=\\"padding-left: 30px;\\">&nbsp;</p>', '', '', '', 'branchreview/see_branch_review.php?id=54', 'NIT9 Hamirpur Electrical Engineering EE99 '),
(55, 'branchreview/img/branch_info55.jpeg', 'img/branch_info_b55.jpeg', 'NIT Hamirpur', 'Mechanical Engineering', '<p><br />The discipline of Mechanical Engineering is offering undergraduate programme leading to four year Bachelor of Technology (B.Tech) degree in Mechanical Engineering .The department has started a Postgraduate programme leading to M. Tech. Degree with specialization in Computational Methods and Experimental Techniques in Fluid Flow &amp; Heat transfer, admitting students from the session 2005-2006 and offering a Ph.D programme in the areas of Design, Thermal, Production/Industrial. Research scholars have registered and are pursuing their Ph.D work. The department has also submitted proposals to start new PG programmes on CAD/CAM and MBA (Industrial Management).</p>', '<p><br /><strong>The Mechanical Engineering department is well equipped with various laboratories for training of UG/PG students. The facilities offered are in the fields of -</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Theory of Machine</li>\r\n<li>Ref. &amp; Air Conditioning</li>\r\n<li>Production</li>\r\n<li>Computer Aided Manufacturing</li>\r\n<li>Metallurgy &amp; Metallography</li>\r\n<li>I.C. Engine</li>\r\n<li>Turbo Machine &amp; Thermal</li>\r\n<li>Heat Transfer</li>\r\n<li>Mechanics of Solid</li>\r\n<li>Measurement &amp; Control</li>\r\n<li>Fluid MEchanics</li>\r\n<li>Heat Treatment</li>\r\n<li>Machining Science</li>\r\n</ul>', '<p><strong>Placements:</strong><br />Our graduates are well placed through on-campus and off-campus placement and are holding responsible positions in different organizations viz. ITC, Godrej Consumers, Hero Motocorp., Maruti, Saint Gobain, Future First, Infosys, Wipro, DRDO, ISRO to name a few. Department of Mechanical Engineering is alive to the needs of coming times. Accordingly more facilities and expertise are being developed in the areas of Energy, Materials, Reliability, Robotics, CFD, CAD/CAM etc.</p>', '<p>The department has seventeen faculty members fourteen of which hold Ph.D degrees. Rest of faculty members possess M. Tech. Degrees and are pursuing their Ph.D. degrees. The faculty members are experienced having expertise in Design/Thermal/Industrial/Production and are engaged in research work in the areas of Solar Energy, Heat Transfer, Material Science, Quality and Reliability, Air pollution control, Tribology and Mechanism Design etc apart from teaching. The faculty members have got projects on MODROBS, TAT and R&amp;D from various funding agencies like MHRD, DST, AICTE and TEQIP. A few more projects proposals have recently been submitted for consideration to these agencies.</p>', '', '', 'branchreview/see_branch_review.php?id=55', 'NIT9 Hamirpur Mech Mechanical Engineering '),
(56, 'branchreview/img/branch_info56.png', 'img/branch_info_b56.jpeg', 'MNIT Jaipur', 'Chemical Engineering', '<p>The Department of Chemical Engineering was commenced with 30 undergraduate students in the B. Tech. Chemical Engineering programme. The PG Programmes of MTech.in Chemical Engineering and Ph.D. was started in year 2006 and 2004 respectively. The current sanctioned strength of the B.Tech. Chemical Engineering Program and M.Tech Chemical Engineering Program is 100 and 25 respectively for Full time Courses. The department is well equipped with good undergraduate laboratories and research laboratories that have been strengthened and modernized under TEQIP (World Bank) grants and Institute grants funded from MHRD.The programmes offered by the department are accredited by NBA and has educational objectives that are consistent with the vision and mission of the Department. The curriculum has been designed to meet the programme goals and objectives that lay more stress on learning under the guidance of a vibrant and highly qualified faculty. The department has also acquired standard chemical process simulators such as CHEMCAD and PROSIM ??? a pro-simulator for design, simulation and control of various unit operations in the chemical industry for training the students. The department has many ongoing research projects being funded by many prestigious funding organizations such as Department of Science &amp; Technology in areas of water and environmental research. Department of chemical engineering has got formal research and academic collaboration with chemical engineering department, University of Saskatchewan, Canada. The department has also got informal academic collaborations with IIP Dehradun, BARC Mumbai, IIT Delhi, IIT Bombay, ICT Mumbai, York University Toronto, University of Toronto and many other research/ academic organizations. Few PG students received Canadian Government fellowship under Graduate student exchange program to work at university of Saskatchewan as part of research work which gave them international exposure.</p>\r\n<p>To create a center for imparting technical education of international standards and conducting research at the cutting edge of technology to meet the current and future challenges of chemical and allied industries of the nation.<br />The mission of the chemical engineering department is to impart quality education in chemical engineering and allied areas, foster research and development, evolve innovative applications of technologies, encourage entrepreneurship and ultimately mold younger generation capable of assuming leadership of the society for the betterment of the country.</p>', '<p><strong>Labs:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Momentum Transfer Operations Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Fluid Particle Mechanics Lab</li>\r\n<li>Heat Transfer Lab</li>\r\n<li>Chemical Reaction Engineering Lab</li>\r\n<li>Mass Transfer Lab</li>\r\n<li>Petroleum Lab</li>\r\n<li>Process Dynamics and Control Lab</li>\r\n<li>Numerical Methods in Chemical Engineering Lab</li>\r\n<li>Simulation Lab</li>\r\n<li>Industrial Pollution Abatement Lab</li>\r\n<li>Process Equipment Design Lab</li>\r\n<li>Process Engineering and Plant Design Lab</li>\r\n</ul>', '', '', '<p><strong>Research and academic collaboration with other University/ Institutions:</strong></p>\r\n<p>Department of chemical engineering has got formal research and academic collaboration with chemical engineering department, University of Saskatchewan, Canada. The department has also got informal academic collaborations with IIP Dehradun, BARC Mumbai, IIT Delhi, IIT Bombay, ICT Mumbai, York University Toronto, University of Toronto and many other research/ academic organizations. Many PG students of our department got Canadian Government fellowship under Graduate student exchange program and got opportunity to work at university of Saskatchewan to complete their part of Ph. D. work.</p>', '', 'branchreview/see_branch_review.php?id=56', 'MNIT Jaipur Chem Chemical Engineering '),
(57, 'branchreview/img/branch_info57.png', 'img/branch_info_b57.jpeg', 'MNIT Jaipur', 'Civil Engineering', '<p>Civil engineering discipline was introduced, at Malaviya National Institute of Technology (then Malaviya Regional Engineering College), Jaipur, in 1965. At the beginning world class laboratories, especially material testing, hydraulics, survey, road material testing, and soil testing laboratories were developed. Later the department was split into two separate departments of Civil Engineering and Structural Engineering.The department offers a four year course leading to the Bachelor\\''s Degree in Civil Engineering with a student intake of 93. It also offers three full time and part time postgraduate courses in Water Resources Engineering, Environmental Engineering and Transportation Engineering.</p>', '<p><strong>Labs:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Computer Lab </li>\r\n<li>Environmental Engg. /Public Health Engg. Lab I</li>\r\n<li>Survey Lab </li>\r\n<li>Road Material Testing Lab </li>\r\n<li>Hydraulics Lab</li>\r\n<li>Remote Sensing/GIS Lab </li>\r\n<li>Geology Lab </li>\r\n<li>Soil Lab </li>\r\n<li>Concrete Lab </li>\r\n<li>Structural Dynamics Lab </li>\r\n</ul>', '', '', '', '<p><strong>Conferences/Workshops/Short Term Courses Organized by the Department:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>5th Asia and Pacific Young Researchers and Graduates Symposium on \\"Current challenges in Structural engineering\\" 15/10/2013 To 16/10/2013.</li>\r\n<li>A short term training programme on \\"Natural Disaster Management\\" 29/10/2012 To 31/10/2012.</li>\r\n<li>National workshop on \\"Repair and Rehabilitation of Structures\\" 05/10/2012 To 06/10/2012.</li>\r\n<li>4th International Conference on Structural Stability and Dynamics (ICSSD-2012) 04/</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'branchreview/see_branch_review.php?id=57', 'MNIT Jaipur Civil Engineering '),
(58, 'branchreview/img/branch_info58.png', 'img/branch_info_b58.jpeg', 'MNIT Jaipur', 'Computer Engineering', '<p>Department of Computer Science &amp; Engineering came into existence in 1994. The first degree program offered by the Department was B.E. (Computer Engineering) in affiliation with University of Rajasthan. Another degree programme BE (Information Technology) was initiated in 2001. Since 2004 after MREC was granted status of deemed university and included as NIT (National Institute of Technology), all BE programmes came to be known as B. Tech. In January 2004, first admissions to PhD programme took place. In 2008, M. Tech. (Computer Engineering) programme was initiated. At present, Computer Engineering Department is offering following degree programmes:<br />B.Tech (Computer Engineering)<br />B.Tech (Information Technology)<br />M.Tech (Computer Engineering)<br />Ph. D</p>\r\n<p>To be a Centre of Excellence in Computer Science and Engineering domain and work with industry on cutting edge technology to address current and emerging challenges in global perspective for the development of society.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;To impart quality engineering education, enhance problem solving skills, foster research and innovation, encourage entrepreneurship and mold students of integrity and ethics to provide leadership with social sensitivity for the betterment of the country and humanity as a whole.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '', '', '', '', '', 'branchreview/see_branch_review.php?id=58', 'MNIT Jaipur Computer Science Engineering CS99 CSE9 Computers'),
(59, 'branchreview/img/branch_info59.png', 'img/branch_info_b59.jpeg', 'MNIT Jaipur', 'Electrical Engineering', '<p>The Electrical Engineering Department is one of the oldest department of the institute which was established in the year 1963. At present the department offers both undergraduate and postgraduate Courses in Electrical Engineering. The Department has undertaken a number of research projects/schemes with the financial assistance from AICTE, DST and MHRD. The Department is also actively engaged in research, consultancy and testing in the area of Power Systems.<br />The Department has been recognized as QIP centre for Ph.D. and M.Tech. for polytechnic colleges&rsquo; faculty members. Presently department is offering a postgraduate course of Master of Technology with specialization in Power Systems Engineering as both full-time and part-time programmes. The department is regularly producing research publications in international and national journals and conferences. Many research scholars are pursuing Ph.D. degree in diversified fields of Electrical Engineering.</p>\r\n<p>To create a center of imparting technical education in electrical engineering of international standard and conducting research at the cutting edge of technology &amp; emerging field of electrical engineering to provide quality man power for meeting the current and future challenges.<br /> <br />To provide quality education at under graduate and post graduate level in the field of Electrical Engineering for meeting the current and future requirement of power industry; to enhance and reorganize education and research in close interaction with industry and technological institution of national &amp; international repute with emphasis on latest trends in engineering and technology.</p>', '<p><strong>Labs:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Power Systems </li>\r\n<li>Electrical Machines </li>\r\n<li>Power Electronics &amp; Electric Drives </li>\r\n<li>Electrical Measurement &amp; Instrumentation </li>\r\n<li>Simulation and Modelling </li>\r\n<li>Microprocessor </li>\r\n<li>Electronic Devices &amp; Circuits</li>\r\n</ul>', '<p><strong>projects :</strong><br />01. Analytical and Experimental Investigation on AC Drive System <br />02. Sensorless Control of Induction Motor Drive with Intelligent Controllers <br />03. Integrated Operation of Solar Photo Voltaic, Wind Energy and Diesel Generator for the Generation of Electrical Energy <br />04. Modernisation of Power System Laboratory <br />05. Modernisation of High Voltage &amp; Power System Laboratory <br />06. On-line transient Security Evaluation of Power Systems using Pattern Recognition Techniques 4.0 3<br />07. Modernization of Control Laboratory 10.0 <br />08. Modernization of Electrical Measurement Laboratory <br />09. On Line Security Evaluation &amp; Preventive Control of Modern Power System <br />10. Exploration of FACTS in Power Systems <br />11. Investigation on Intelligent Controller for PMSM Drive</p>', '', '', '<p><strong>Conferences/Seminars/Workshops Organized :</strong></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>First National Conference on \\"Power Electronics and Intelligent Control</li>\r\n<li>Curriculum Development Workshop</li>\r\n<li>Second National Conference on \\"Power Electronics and Intelligent Control</li>\r\n<li>Third National conference on \\"Power Electronics and Intelligent Control</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p><strong>Summer/Winter Schools Organized:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Two Weeks MHRD-AICTE Short Term Faculty Training Program on \\"Advanced Application of Power Electronics and Drives</li>\r\n<li>Two Weeks MHRD-AICTE Short Term Training Program on \\"Operation and Control of Modern Power System</li>\r\n<li>One week Short term course on \\"Smart Grid Technologies</li>\r\n<li>Short Term Course on \\"Power System Restructuring and Electricity Markets</li>\r\n<li>One week Short term course on \\"Smart Technologies for Power Management</li>\r\n<li>Short Term Training program on \\"Operation and Control of Modern Power Systems</li>\r\n<li>International Seminar under the India UK Scientific Seminar on \\"Economically and Socially Efficient Network Pricing for Smarter Distribution Grids</li>\r\n<li>Staff Development Program on \\''Emerging Technologies for Power Systems Operations &amp; Energy Management</li>\r\n<li>Staff Development Program on \\''Real Time Implementation of Power Electronics Technologies</li>\r\n<li>Short Term Training Program on \\"Role of Power Electronics in Modern Electrical System</li>\r\n<li>Short Term Training Program on \\"Advancement and Application of Power Electronics in Present Scenario</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'branchreview/see_branch_review.php?id=59', 'MNIT Jaipur Electrical Engineering EE99 '),
(60, 'branchreview/img/branch_info60.png', 'img/branch_info_b60.jpeg', 'MNIT Jaipur', 'Electronics & Communication Engineering', '<p>Bachelor\\''s course in Electronics &amp; Communication Engineering was first started in 1981-82, initially in the Electrical Engineering Department. In 1994, the Department of Electronics &amp; Communication Engineering came into existence as a separate entity. Its undergraduate &amp; four postgraduate programmes constitute approximately 20% students strength of the Institute, thus giving it the status of one of the largest Department of the Institute.<br />The first Master\\''s degree programme was started in 1992-93. Currently,<strong> department offers Master\\''s programme in four specializations-</strong><br />(i) VLSI Design<br />(ii) Electronics &amp; Communication<br />(iii) Wireless &amp; Optical Communication and<br />(iv) Embedded Systems.<br />The Department also offers PhD programme in relevant areas. The Department has received grants from government &amp; semi-government agencies such as MHRD, AICTE, Ministry of information Technology, UKEIRI, DST and ISRO. The Department has active collaborations with renowned Institutes &amp; research institutes in India and abroad.<br />The Department of ECE, at MNIT Jaipur has a blend of young as well as experienced, dynamic faculty members and is committed to providing quality education and research in the field.</p>', '<p><strong>Lab Systems:</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\\"padding-left: 30px;\\">1 VLSI lab <br />2 Micro-Processor lab <br />3 Embedded systemslab</p>', '', '', '', '<p><strong>List of Conferences Organized by the Department:</strong><br />National conference on Recent developments in wireless and optical communication 29/10/2012 To 30/10/2012.</p>', 'branchreview/see_branch_review.php?id=60', 'MNIT Jaipur Electronics & Communication Engineering ECE9'),
(61, 'branchreview/img/branch_info61.png', 'img/branch_info_b61.jpeg', 'MNIT Jaipur', 'Architecture and Planning', '<p>Architecture is both the process and product of planning, designing and construction. Architectural works, in the material form of buildings, are often perceived as cultural symbols and as works of art. Historical civilizations are often identified with their surviving architectural achievements. Architecture is a medium of cultural expression displayed using a specific set of principles. These principals are meant to be interpreted so that the culture of a period or a nation can be fully expressed and understood.</p>', '', '', '', '', '', 'branchreview/see_branch_review.php?id=61', 'MNIT Jaipur Architecture and9 Planning');
