(62, 'branchreview/img/branch_info62.jpeg', 'img/branch_info_b62.jpeg', 'NIT Jalandhar', 'Computer Science', '<p>The Department of Computer Science and Engineering was started in 1990 with an intake of 40 students in undergraduate programme, which was revised later on to 60. Present UG intake is 93. Ph.d and Postgraducate programmes were started in 2006.</p>\r\n<p>To be in the frontier of Computer Science and Engineering and to produce globally competent graduates with high moral values committed to build a vibrant nation.<br />To be recognised nationally and internationally for delivering outstanding computer science education and conducting research of high distinction, both of value and relevance to the communities we serve.<br />The mission of the Department is to provide students and faculty with an open environment that fosters professional and personal growth.</p>\r\n<p><br />A strong theoretical excellence and competence in the fundamental areas of Computer Science to nurture students for utilizing high creativity, innovation and out-of-the-box thinking.<br />A breadth of knowledge in a variety of application areas pertaining to the field of Computer Science so that students can maximize on their career options.<br />Preparation for contemporary research and development in Computer Science applicable to industry or academia.<br />The awareness of professional, social and ethical responsibilities through curricular, co-curricular and extracurricular activities.</p>', '<p><strong>Labs:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Computer Programming Language Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Data Communication Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Computer Networks Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Operating Systems Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Computer Graphics Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Natural Language and Pattern Recognition Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Embedded System Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Software Engineering Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Information Security Education and Awareness Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Project Laboratory for M.Tech</li>\r\n<li>Wireless Sensor Networks Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Wireless and Optical Network Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Microprocessor Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Digital Circuit &amp; Logic Design Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>RDBMS Laboratory</li>\r\n</ul>', '', '', '', '<p><strong>Programme Outcomes</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Apply knowledge of Mathematics, Science and Engineering Fundamentals to the areas of Computer Science and Engineering.</li>\r\n<li>Design and conduct experiments to analyze and interpret data.</li>\r\n<li>Design a system component or process to meet desired needs.</li>\r\n<li>Function in multi-disciplinary teams to develop project management techniques.</li>\r\n<li>Identify, formulate and solve engineering problems.</li>\r\n<li>Understand the professional, social, and ethical responsibility.</li>\r\n<li>Communicate effectively both in written and oral formats.</li>\r\n<li>Disseminate broad education necessary to understand the impact of engineering solutions in global, economic, environmental and societal contexts.</li>\r\n<li>Recognize the need and ability to engage in life-long learning.</li>\r\n<li>Develop knowledge on contemporary, networks and security related issues in respective fields.</li>\r\n<li>Use the techniques, skills and modern engineering tools necessary for engineering practices.</li>\r\n</ul>', 'branchreview/see_branch_review.php?id=62', 'NIT9 Jalandhar Computer Science Engineering CS99 CSE9 Computers'),
(63, 'branchreview/img/branch_info63.jpeg', 'img/branch_info_b63.jpeg', 'NIT Jalandhar', 'Civil Engineering', '<p>Established as one of the oldest department of the institute offering B.tech course and M.tech courses. It also has Phd programme. The department is well equipped and enriched with a core team of 30 highly qualified faculty members who are capable of producing good civil engineers out of their students. </p>', '<p><strong>Main laboratories of the department are:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Environmental Engineering Laboratory </li>\r\n<li>Geotechnical Engineering Laboratory </li>\r\n<li>Structures Testing Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Concrete Technology Laboratory </li>\r\n<li>Transportation Engineering Laboratory </li>\r\n<li>Survey Laboratory </li>\r\n<li>CAD Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Structural Analysis Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Hydraulic Engineering Laboratory</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '', '', '', '', 'branchreview/see_branch_review.php?id=63', 'NIT9 Jalandhar Civil Engineering '),
(64, 'branchreview/img/branch_info64.jpeg', 'img/branch_info_b64.jpeg', 'NIT Jalandhar', 'Chemical Engineering', '<p>Department is one of the important and well equipped engineering departments. It aims at creating a centre of excellence in research and technical aspects of the branch. Department offers a 4 year B.Tech course, M.tech course and P.hd degrees with an intake of of 68 students in B.tech course and 24 in Phd course.&nbsp;</p>', '<p><strong>A number of labs are present in the department like:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Fluid Mechanics Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Mechanical Operation Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Energy Engineering laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Chemical Technology Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Heat Transfer Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Chemical Reaction Engineering Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Mass Transfer Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Chemical Process Control Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Pollution Abatement Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Bio-Chemical Engineering Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Process Modeling and Simulation Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Fuel Technology Laboratory</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '', '', '', '', 'branchreview/see_branch_review.php?id=64', 'NIT9 Jalandhar Chem Chemical Engineering '),
(65, 'branchreview/img/branch_info65.jpeg', 'img/branch_info_b65.jpeg', 'NIT Jalandhar', 'Electronics and Communication Engineering', '<p>Department was established to make students able to participate and show their talents in academic field, research and co curricular activities and comprise at least 20% students&rsquo; strength of the institute which is the largest in the institute. Students by giving their excellent results in the fields of industrial, academia and research have always earned name in favour of the department. </p>', '<p>NITJ is known for having very good and advanced laboratory facilities which are totally accessible to all students and the ECE Department has some of the best lab facilities. Students get easy access to the labs and are free to work on any projects they like in conjunction with the faculty.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Some of the most important labs are :</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Devices &amp; Circuits Lab</li>\r\n<li>Microwave Engineering Lab </li>\r\n<li>Embedded Systems Lab</li>\r\n<li>Emerging Technology Lab</li>\r\n<li>Communication Systems Lab</li>\r\n<li>Basic Electronics &amp; IC Lab</li>\r\n<li>Digital Signal Processing Lab </li>\r\n<li>VLSI Lab(under SMDP II) </li>\r\n<li>Biomedical Signal Processing &amp; Telemedicine Lab</li>\r\n<li>Medical Imaging and Computational Modelling of Phy. Systems Lab<br /> </li>\r\n</ul>', '', '', '', '', 'branchreview/see_branch_review.php?id=65', 'NIT9 Jalandhar Electronics and9 Communication Engineering ECE9'),
(66, 'branchreview/img/branch_info66.jpeg', 'img/branch_info_b66.jpeg', 'NIT Jalandhar', 'Mechanical Engineering', '<p>Established to offer U.G. courses and P.G. courses in mechanical engineering. This department is one of the most populated departments of the institute with a intake students including B.tech, M.tech &amp; Phd students which is increasing in the preceding years.</p>', '<p><strong>Labs in this department includes :</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Strength of Materials Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Fluid Machinery Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Heat Transfer and Heat Engine Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Theory of Machines </li>\r\n<li>Computer Aided Design Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Refrigeration and Air Conditioning Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Mechanical Measurement Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Vibration Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Automobile Engineering Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Experimental Stress Analysis Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Automation and Mechatronics Laboratory</li>\r\n</ul>', '', '', '', '', 'branchreview/see_branch_review.php?id=66', 'NIT9 Jalandhar Mech Mechanical Engineering '),
(67, 'branchreview/img/branch_info67.jpeg', 'img/branch_info_b67.jpeg', 'NIT Jalandhar', 'Electrical Engineering ', '<p>The Electrical Engineering Department caters students with a UG course in Electrical Engineering and a PG course in Control ,along with a part-time PG course in Electrical Engineering. Further, the Department also enrolls candidates for Ph.D programs. The Department has qualified and experienced faculty having done research in various fields of Electrical Engineering. The knowledge of the subject is complemented by well-equipped laboratories. There is loads of exchange of ideas between the Electrical Engineering Department and various other departments like Electronics Engineering and Computer Science and Engineering.&nbsp;</p>', '<p>Well-equipped and regularly maintained laboratories are a quality of the department.</p>\r\n<p><strong>The department comprises of following labs:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>CONTROL SYSTEM LABORATORY </li>\r\n<li>POWER ELECTRONICS LABORATORY </li>\r\n<li>COMPUTER SIMULATION LABORATORY</li>\r\n<li>ELECTRICAL MEASUREMENT LABORATORY</li>\r\n<li>PROJECT LABORATORY</li>\r\n<li>ELECTRICAL MACHINES LABORATORY</li>\r\n<li>TESTING AND CALIBERATION FACILITIES</li>\r\n</ul>', '', '', '', '', 'branchreview/see_branch_review.php?id=67', 'NIT9 Jalandhar Electrical Engineering EE99 '),
(68, 'branchreview/img/branch_info68.jpeg', 'img/branch_info_b68.jpeg', 'NIT Nagpur', 'Chemical Engineering', '<p>Established in 2006, the department offers both undergraduate and graduate degree programmes in Chemical Engineering. Led by a team of 17 faculty who are eminent researchers and teachers devoted to their profession, the department is ranked among the nation\\''s best departments in Chemical Engineering. The research in the department is not only limited to traditional Chemical Engineering but more focused on interdisciplinary areas such as Biotechnology, Biochemical Engineering, Catalysis, Energy, Environment, Sustainability, Nanotechnology, Novel Separation techniques, Materials Engineering, Systems Engineering, Interfacial Sciences, Molecular and Process Modeling and Simulations.<br /> <br /> </p>', '', '', '', '', '', 'branchreview/see_branch_review.php?id=68', 'NIT9 Nagpur Chem Chemical Engineering '),
(69, 'branchreview/img/branch_info69.jpeg', 'img/branch_info_b69.jpeg', 'NIT Nagpur', 'Civil Engineering ', '<p>The Department has highly educated and well experienced faculty members who endeavour to produce the finest engineers, contributing incredibly to the nation. The alumni of the department are widespread in India and abroad, occupying high positions in their respective fields..<br />It has an intake of 92 students per year under UG Course and 60 per year under PG Courses.<br /> The aim of the Department is to produce creative, wise, well skilled engineers, capable of taking responsibilities on their own to fulfil the requirements of present and future and to bring advancement for a better tomorrow.</p>\r\n<p><br /> The program strives for excellence in engineering education and profession. It also aims to promote all round development of the personality of students by suitably involving them in Co-curricular and extra-curricular activities.To contribute effectively to the National Endeavour of producing quality human resource of world class standard in civil engineering by developing a sustainable technical education system and to meet the changing technological needs of the Country incorporating relevant of social concerns and to build an environment to create and propagate innovative technologies for the economic development of Nation.</p>', '', '', '', '', '', 'branchreview/see_branch_review.php?id=69', 'NIT9 Nagpur Civil Engineering '),
(70, 'branchreview/img/branch_info70.jpeg', 'img/branch_info_b70.jpeg', 'NIT Nagpur', 'Computer Science and Engineering ', '<p>The Department of Computer Science &amp; Engineering came into being in 1987. It offers under-graduate and post-graduate programs. Currently, there are 21 PhD students enrolled in the department in the areas of parallel computing, real time &amp; distributed systems, cloud computing, network.<br />The department has well qualified and motivated faculty members and support staff. The laboratories are adequately equipped with state-of-the-art facilities<br />The department is actively involved in R&amp;D as well as consultancy projects and has collaborations with several industries, academic institutes and R&amp;D organizations in the country.<br /> </p>', '', '', '', '', '', 'branchreview/see_branch_review.php?id=70', 'NIT9 Nagpur Computer Science Engineering CS99 CSE9 Computers'),
(71, 'branchreview/img/branch_info71.jpeg', 'img/branch_info_b71.jpeg', 'NIT Nagpur', 'Electrical Engineering ', '<p>The department was established in 1960 with a UG programme in Electrical Engineering. The postgraduate programme in &lsquo;Integrated Power System&rsquo; was started in 1968. Later, another postgraduate program in &lsquo;Power Electronics and Drives&rsquo; was introduced. The sanctioned intake for UG programme,B.Tech.(Electrical and Electronics Engineering) is 92. The sanctioned intake for the PG programmes i.e. M.Tech. (IPS) and M.Tech. (PED) is 30 each. The Department is recognised as QIP Centre for M.Tech and Ph.D. programmes.<br />The National Board of Accreditation has accredited the department with the highest grade &lsquo;A&rsquo; for UG as well as PG programme in both the accreditation exercise undertaken so far (one in 1996 and other in 2001).The program strives to facilitatestudents for pursuing higher studiesand to empower graduates to cope up with constantly evolving technology through lifelong learning.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '', '', '', '', '', 'branchreview/see_branch_review.php?id=71', 'NIT9 Nagpur Electrical Engineering EE99 '),
(72, 'branchreview/img/branch_info72.jpeg', 'img/branch_info_b72.jpeg', 'NIT Nagpur', 'Mechanical Engineering ', '<p>Mechanical Engineering Department offers M.TECH.program in Heat Power Engineering ,Industrial Engineering and CAD-CAM Engineering.<br />The program strives to develop state of the art facilities related to mechanical engineering ,to attract highly qualified faculty to the mechanical engineering department and topromote participation of industries in academic research and consultancy.</p>', '<p><strong>laboratories:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Fatigue &amp; fracture mechanics laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Theory of machines lab</li>\r\n<li>Solid mechanics laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Metrology lab</li>\r\n<li>Renewable energy laboratory.</li>\r\n<li>Mechanical measurement lab</li>\r\n<li>Heat transfer lab</li>\r\n</ul>', '', '', '', '', 'branchreview/see_branch_review.php?id=72', 'NIT9 Nagpur Mech Mechanical Engineering '),
(73, 'branchreview/img/branch_info73.jpeg', 'img/branch_info_b73.jpeg', 'NIT Nagpur', 'Electronics and communication Engineering ', '<p>The Department of Electronics and Computer Science was created in 1994 from the Department of Electrical Engineering. Later, the Department of Electronics and Communication Engineering has been created in May 2014. It offers under-graduate program in Electronics and Communication Engineering and post-graduate program in Communication Systems Engineering. The department has well qualified and well motivated faculty members and support staff. There are more than 20 full time PhD students enrolled in the department in the areas of Image Processing, Embedded System Design, RF and Antenna Design.<br />The laboratories are adequately equipped with state-of-the-art facilities. The department is undergoing vigorous growth in emerging areas of Embedded Systems, RF Testing and Communications.<br />Currently, the department has been awarded Center of Excellence in Combedded Systems by MHRD (NPIU). The department is actively involved in R &amp; D as well as consultancy projects and has collaborations with several industries, academic institutes, and R&amp;D organizations in the country.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '', '', '', '', '', 'branchreview/see_branch_review.php?id=73', 'NIT9 Nagpur Electronics and9 communication Engineering ECE9'),
(74, 'branchreview/img/branch_info74.jpeg', 'img/branch_info_b74.jpeg', 'NIT Kurukshetra', 'Civil Engineering ', '<p>The Civil Engineering Department is one of the premier departments of the institute. The department boasts not only of highly qualified and experienced faculty, who are involved in various research projects and consultancy services, but also the Labs that are equipped with advanced software packages to impartpractical knowledge to the students and cover the essential aspects of civil engineering.<br />The department also emphasizes on the importance of industrial exposure and organize industrial tours and workshops in addition to a mandatory survey camp.</p>', '<p><strong>Facilities:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Hydraulics Lab</li>\r\n<li>Irrigation Lab</li>\r\n<li>Geology Lab</li>\r\n<li>Geo-technical Lab</li>\r\n<li>Foundation Engg. Lab</li>\r\n<li>Rock Mechanics</li>\r\n<li>Structures Lab</li>\r\n<li>Surveying Lab</li>\r\n<li>Transportation Lab</li>\r\n<li>Environmental Engg. Lab</li>\r\n<li>Computational Lab</li>\r\n<li>Concrete and Structural Lab </li>\r\n<li>Structural Mechanics Lab</li>\r\n<li>Structural Analysis</li>\r\n<li>Design of Steel structures</li>\r\n<li>Design of Concrete structures </li>\r\n<li>Courses offered:</li>\r\n<li>Fluid Mechanics</li>\r\n<li>Soil Mechanics</li>\r\n<li>Building Construction Materials</li>\r\n<li>Surveying</li>\r\n<li>Hydrology</li>\r\n<li>Water Resources</li>\r\n<li>Irrigation </li>\r\n<li>Geotechnology</li>\r\n<li>Water Supply and Treatment</li>\r\n<li>Engineering Geology</li>\r\n</ul>', '', '', '', '<p><strong>Major Research Projects</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>FIST Scheme</li>\r\n<li>Strengthening of Structural Elements using Tyfo Fibrwrap System</li>\r\n<li>Artificial Artificial Ground Water Recharge Recharge Through Through Rain Water</li>\r\n<li>Water Harvesting to Curb Ground Water</li>\r\n<li>Study of Water Quality Assessment of Braham Sarovar/ Sanhit Sarovar</li>\r\n<li>High Performance Fiber Based Composite Infrastructure</li>\r\n<li>Systems&nbsp;&nbsp;Utilizing Advanced Composites</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Publications and Consultancy</strong></p>\r\n<p>The faculty has published more than 100 papers in international journals like ASCE , ACI and more than 450 papers in National level journals /seminars /conferences /symposia and<br />also received several awards for their research work.<br />The department is engaged in providing consultancy services to various Government, Semi&ndash;Government and Private Organizations. Efforts to Diversify the areas pertaining to various<br />disciplines are continuously being made so that more interaction could be ensured with the industries and various organizations.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'branchreview/see_branch_review.php?id=74', 'NIT9 Kurukshetra Civil Engineering '),
(75, 'branchreview/img/branch_info75.jpeg', 'img/branch_info_b75.jpeg', 'NIT Kurukshetra', ' Computer Science and Engineering Branch', '<p>The department has been offering B.tech Degree Course in Computer Engineering since 1987, attracts the pinnacle students in terms of merit across the nation and abroad. A sound theoretical and practical work prepares the students in wider field of Computer Engineering to take up challenging jobs in the area of Systems Software Development , Application Software Development ,Computer Networking and Database Administration. The department has also been offering B Tech. Degree Course in Information Technology since 2006. The department labs are well equipped with Rack Servers , AMD Optron Based Servers, Stand alone Servers and thin clients.<br />\\"Modernization of &ldquo;Computer Centre&rdquo; under MODROB Scheme is an MHRD initiative to help students compete with the pace of growing technology and provide a strong platform to exhibit innovation at work.</p>', '<p><strong>Facilities:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Computer Networking Lab</li>\r\n<li>Application and System Software Lab </li>\r\n<li>Mobile Computing Laboratory Lab</li>\r\n<li>Computer Hardware and Troubleshooting Lab</li>\r\n<li>Thin Client Lab</li>\r\n<li>Web Development Lab</li>\r\n<li>Software Enggineering Lab</li>\r\n<li>Advanced Architecture Lab</li>\r\n<li>Database Lab</li>\r\n</ul>', '', '', '', '<p><strong>Courses Offered</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Advanced Computer Architecture</li>\r\n<li>Advanced Database Systems</li>\r\n<li>Analog and Digital Communication </li>\r\n<li>Computer Hardware Technologies</li>\r\n<li>Computer Networks</li>\r\n<li>Data Structures</li>\r\n<li>Design and Analysis of Algorithms</li>\r\n<li>Digital Electronics</li>\r\n<li>Internet and Intranet Engineering</li>\r\n<li>Microprocessors</li>\r\n<li>Object Oriented Programming</li>\r\n<li>Programming Methodology and File Structures</li>\r\n<li>Security and Cryptography</li>\r\n<li>Software Engineering</li>\r\n<li>Unix and Linux Programming</li>\r\n<li>Web Engineering</li>\r\n</ul>', 'branchreview/see_branch_review.php?id=75', 'NIT9 Kurukshetra Computer Science Engineering CS99 CSE9 Computers'),
(76, 'branchreview/img/branch_info76.jpeg', 'img/branch_info_b76.jpeg', 'NIT Kurukshetra', 'Electronics and Communication Engineering ', '<p>Since its inception , the Department has shown exponential growth in terms of modernization of the existing laboratories and establishment of new laboratories equipped with state-of- the-art facilities, curriculum development in consonance with the industrial needs. The students under the guidance of faculty members have made a mark in the area of innovative hardware design, modelling &amp; analysis and developing new techniques and algorithms in the fields of data communication systems and wireless networks, signal processing and VLSI design. Analytical and simulation tools and test beds/working benches are available to carry out research and development in different dimensions of Electronics and Communication Engineering. The Department attracts funding from government and industry for its research projects.</p>', '<p><strong>Facilities:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>VLSI Design Laboratory (SMDP-II)</li>\r\n<li>VLSI Design Laboratory 9 Microprocessor Laboratory 9</li>\r\n<li>Basic Electronics Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Communication Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Microwave Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Microwave Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Computer Centre</li>\r\n<li>Electronics Workshop</li>\r\n<li>PCB Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Advanced Electronic Laboratory</li>\r\n</ul>', '', '', '', '<p><strong>Courses Offered</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Analog Communication</li>\r\n<li>Analog Electronics</li>\r\n<li>Antenna and Wave Prop ga ation</li>\r\n<li>Computer Communication andNetworking</li>\r\n<li>Computer Organisation and Architecture</li>\r\n<li>Control Systems</li>\r\n<li>Digital Communication</li>\r\n<li>Digital Electronics</li>\r\n<li>Field and Waves</li>\r\n<li>Linear IC applications</li>\r\n<li>Measurements and Instrumentation</li>\r\n<li>Microprocessors and Microcontrollers</li>\r\n<li>Microwave Engineering</li>\r\n<li>Network Analysis And Synthesis</li>\r\n<li>Semiconductor Devices and Circuits</li>\r\n<li>Signals and Systems</li>\r\n<li>TV and Radar Engineering</li>\r\n<li>VHDL</li>\r\n<li>VLSI design</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'branchreview/see_branch_review.php?id=76', 'NIT9 Kurukshetra Electronics and9 Communication Engineering ECE9'),
(77, 'branchreview/img/branch_info77.jpeg', 'img/branch_info_b77.jpeg', 'NIT Kurukshetra', 'Electrical Engineering ', '<p>In response to the changing requirements of the present day industries , the curriculum structurehas been designed to meet the same.Department has high tech labs to help students improve their practical approach and highly experienced faculty, who help the students to bring the best out of them.Faculty are encouraged to take Independent initiatives with collective responsibility in all the relevant academic and R&amp;D dimensions, teaching, curriculum development , graduate research supervision, continuing education and organization of conferences, symposia etc. Moreover students also bring laurels to the department by successfully accomplishing their projects.</p>', '<p><strong>Facilities:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Basic Electrical Engineering Lab</li>\r\n<li>Electrical Machines &amp; Drivers Lab</li>\r\n<li>Electrical Measurements Lab</li>\r\n<li>Power Systems Lab</li>\r\n<li>Control Systems Lab</li>\r\n<li>Power Electronics Lab</li>\r\n<li>Signals and Systems Lab</li>\r\n<li>Computers and Microprocessors Lab</li>\r\n<li>Instrumentation Lab</li>\r\n<li>Electrical Workshop</li>\r\n<li>High Voltage Lab</li>\r\n<li>Process Control Lab</li>\r\n</ul>', '', '', '', '<p><strong>Research and Development Projects:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Static Reactive Power Compensators</li>\r\n<li>Automation in Industrial Control Using Transputers</li>\r\n<li>Control systems</li>\r\n<li>Analysis and designing systems</li>\r\n<li>Distribution Automation</li>\r\n<li>Educational Technologies</li>\r\n<li>Audio Visual Centre</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Seminars:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>All India Seminar on Electronics Industrial</li>\r\n<li>Applications Summer School on Advances in Control</li>\r\n<li>Techniques ISTE Workshop on Quality Assurance in Technical Education</li>\r\n<li>AICTE Induction Training Program for Transmission System</li>\r\n<li>Workshop on Future Career Avenues in Engg. &amp; Technology</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Courses offered:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Power System analysis</li>\r\n<li>Electrical Machines</li>\r\n<li>Transmission and Distribution</li>\r\n<li>Switchgear and Protection</li>\r\n<li>Electric Drives</li>\r\n<li>Circuit Theory</li>\r\n<li>Signal and Systems</li>\r\n<li>Network Analysis And Synthesis</li>\r\n<li>Control Systems</li>\r\n<li>Microprocessors and Microcontrollers</li>\r\n<li>Analog Electronics</li>\r\n<li>Power Electronics</li>\r\n<li>Digital Electronics</li>\r\n<li>Analog and Digital Communication</li>\r\n<li>Advanced Advanced Programming Programming and Software Software Engineering</li>\r\n<li>Measurements and Instrumentation</li>\r\n<li>Field and Waves</li>\r\n<li>Material, Components and Processes</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><br /><strong>Consultancy Projects:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Line losses determination of Kurukshetra Circle HVPN Ltd.</li>\r\n<li>Testing of UPS Directory Technical Engineering</li>\r\n<li>Testing of Air Circuit breakers M/S. Mohini Electric Works Pvt. Ltd., Delhi</li>\r\n<li>Testing of Welding Transformer, improvement of Power Factor</li>\r\n<li>Relay Design for MITS Karnal, Panel Testing of Paradise Enterprise, Ambala</li>\r\n</ul>', 'branchreview/see_branch_review.php?id=77', 'NIT9 Kurukshetra Electrical Engineering EE99 '),
(78, 'branchreview/img/branch_info78.jpeg', 'img/branch_info_b78.jpeg', 'NIT Kurukshetra', 'Mechanical Engineering ', '<p>The Department comprises of one of the most talented faculty among the engineering institutes . It has been actively involved in various projects at national and international level. The collegiate club, Society of Automotive Engineers recently got selected for BAJA project and there are various other research and recently got selected for BAJA project and there are various other research and development projects that are strongly supported by the institution. The departmental labs are equipped with wide range hi-tech machines, tools and equipment to broaden the practical knowledge of students. It also incorporates labs to carry out design, Simulation and development on computer programs. The department department has laid strong emphasis emphasis on helping helping students students acquire acquire practical practical knowledge. The institution has played a key role in motivating and assisting the students to freely explore the departmental resources and carry out academic activities.</p>', '<p><strong>Facilities :</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Strength of Materials Lab </li>\r\n<li>Strength of Materials Lab</li>\r\n<li>Vibration Lab</li>\r\n<li>Measurement Lab</li>\r\n<li>Metrology Lab</li>\r\n<li>Advanced ManufacturingTechnology</li>\r\n<li>Industrial Engineering &amp; Ergonomics Lab</li>\r\n<li>Thermal Engineering Lab</li>\r\n<li>Refrigeration &amp; Air Conditioning Lab</li>\r\n<li>Heat Transfer and CFD Lab</li>\r\n<li>Hydraulic Machine Lab</li>\r\n<li>Computer &amp; Automation Centre</li>\r\n<li>Energy Lab</li>\r\n<li>Tribology Lab</li>\r\n<li>Machine Vision Lab</li>\r\n<li>Mechanism &amp; Machine Lab</li>\r\n<li>Experimental Stress Analysis Lab</li>\r\n<li>Advanced Welding Lab</li>\r\n<li>PRIDE Lab</li>\r\n<li>Optimization Lab</li>\r\n<li>NDT Lab</li>\r\n</ul>', '', '', '', '<p><strong>Courses Offered:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Strength of Materials</li>\r\n<li>Machine Design</li>\r\n<li>Production Technology</li>\r\n<li>Theory of Machines</li>\r\n<li>Steam and Power Generation</li>\r\n<li>Fluid Machines</li>\r\n<li>Material Sciences</li>\r\n<li>Refrigeration and Air Conditioning</li>\r\n<li>CAD</li>\r\n<li>Mechanical Vibrations</li>\r\n<li>IC Engines &amp; Gas Turbines</li>\r\n<li>Heat Transfer</li>\r\n<li>Renewable Energy Resources</li>\r\n<li>Industrial Engineering</li>\r\n<li>Statistical Quality Control Entrepreneurship</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'branchreview/see_branch_review.php?id=78', 'NIT9 Kurukshetra Mech Mechanical Engineering '),
(79, 'branchreview/img/branch_info79.jpeg', 'img/branch_info_b79.jpeg', 'NIT Raipur', 'Chemical Engineering', '<p>The Chemical Engineering department was established in the year 1962. The first post-graduate degree with specialization in chemical process design was awarded in the year 1998.<br />The department is offering undergraduate course (B. Tech in Chemical engineering) and one post-graduate course (M. Tech in Chemical process design). At present the intake of the department is 62 at under graduate and 15 at post graduate level. Ph.D programme with the financial assistance of MHRD is also available in the department. Currently, 15 Ph.D scholars are conducting their research in various streams of chemical engineering.</p>\r\n<p>The Department has been successfully carrying out testing and consultancy projects for over four decades and now expects to play a major role in the development of chemical industries. Faculty members of department successfully completed two research projects and two more research projects are ongoing, sponsored by various funding agencies. The department has organized some international conferences and short-term courses. There are 10 regular faculty members and 3 temporary faculty members are in the department.</p>', '<p><strong>Labs:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Inorganic Process Lab </li>\r\n<li>Mechanical Operations Lab </li>\r\n<li>Instrumentation Lab </li>\r\n<li>Fluid flow Lab </li>\r\n<li>Heat Transfer Lab. </li>\r\n<li>Fuel Technology Lab. </li>\r\n<li>Process Dynamics &amp; Control Lab.</li>\r\n<li>Separation process Lab I</li>\r\n<li>Separation process Lab II </li>\r\n<li>Organic Technology Lab </li>\r\n<li>Reaction Engineering Lab </li>\r\n</ul>', '', '', '', '<p><strong>PROJECTS:</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\\"padding-left: 30px;\\"><br />1 Slurry formulation for ruthenium chemical mechanical planarization <br />2 Organic acid from sugar cane industry\\''s by - product <br />3 Self Life of Spices <br />4 Studies on a membrane reactor for the etherification of momocarboxylic acids with ethanol <br />5 Kinetics of thermal degradation of cholorofil green leafy vegetables and increasing the shelf life of the vegetables<br />6 Treatment of biodigester effluents (BDE) of rice grain based industry <br />7 Intensification of downstream processing of citric acid using process intensification method (reactive extraction)</p>\r\n<p><strong>Short term :</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\\"padding-left: 30px;\\"><br />1 .Short Term Training Programme on &ldquo;Chemical Process Modeling &amp; Simulation (CPMS-14)&rdquo; <br />2 .Short Term Training Programme on &ldquo;Simulation of Flow Processes using Computational Fluid Dynamics&rdquo; TEQIP II</p>\r\n<p><strong>Workshop Organized:</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\\"padding-left: 30px;\\">1 .Workshop on &ldquo;Renewable Energy &amp; Environment (REE-14)&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Industrial Expert Lectures Organized:</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\\"padding-left: 30px;\\">1 .Shri. D. C. Gupta, Dy. Gen. Manager, JK Tyres, Mysore <br />2 .Shri. Shashank Mishra, Asst. Manager,IFFCO, New Delhi <br />3 .Shri. Madhur Mehrotra, Associate Vice President,UEM Group, Noida</p>\r\n<p><br /><strong>International Conference Organized</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\\"padding-left: 30px;\\">1 . International Conference on Advances in Chemical Engineering</p>\r\n<p><br /><strong>In-house Training Organized</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\\"padding-left: 30px;\\">1 .Gas Chromatography</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'branchreview/see_branch_review.php?id=79', 'NIT9 Raipur Chem Chemical Engineering '),
(80, 'branchreview/img/branch_info80.jpeg', 'img/branch_info_b80.jpeg', 'NIT Raipur', 'Civil Engineering', '<p>The Department of Civil Engineering at NIT Raipur is producing high quality technical manpower required by various industrial establishments, R&amp;D organizations, Govt. &amp; public establishments and academic institutions since 1958. The Department offers B Tech degree in Civil Engineering and M Tech degree in Civil Engineering with specializations in Water Resources Development &amp; Irrigation Engineering and Structural Engineering. The Department has been offering Ph.D. program in various specializations. The Department also encourages its students to engage in extra-curricular and co-curricular activities, essential for development, nurturing of team spirit, and developing organizational skills. The faculty members of the department are involved in research and consultancy activities, and they continue to enjoy academic leader role in the country. </p>', '<p><strong>LAB :</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Computer Center </li>\r\n<li>Concrete Lab </li>\r\n<li>Environmental Engineering </li>\r\n<li>Fluid Mechanics &amp; hydraulics </li>\r\n<li>Geotechnical Lab. </li>\r\n<li>Structural Analysis and design </li>\r\n</ul>', '', '', '', '<p><strong>TESTING CONSULTANCY AND RESEARCH:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Air Pollution, Water and Wastewater Treatment, Solid waste management, EIA and EM.</li>\r\n<li>Health monitoring of structure, Design of structures.</li>\r\n<li>Water shed management</li>\r\n<li>Seismic Hazard Analysis by Ravi Shankar &amp; Seikasar dam by T.Sahu</li>\r\n<li>Seismic Hazard analysis of Hasdeo Bango</li>\r\n<li>Seismic Hazard analysis of Marrum Silly</li>\r\n<li>Testing/consultancy rate of various test/consultancy works in civil engineering department w.e.f. from 1st January 2016</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'branchreview/see_branch_review.php?id=80', 'NIT9 Raipur Civil Engineering '),
(81, 'branchreview/img/branch_info81.jpeg', 'img/branch_info_b81.jpeg', 'NIT Raipur', 'Computer Science & Engineering', '<p>The aim of the department is to promote Research and Development in the frontier areas of Computer Science &amp; Engineering ,to generate Competent Professionals to become part of the industry and Research Organizations at the National and International levelsand to provide necessary strengths to enable the students to Innovate and to become Entrepreneurs.</p>\r\n<p>Department impart effective education at undergraduate levels in the field of Computer Science and Engineering ,conduct Research and Development and offer consultancy services and improve continuously the quality of teaching-learning process.</p>', '<p>&nbsp;<strong></strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>LABORATORIES:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Advanced Computer Networking Laboratory </li>\r\n<li>MATLAB Dual Link Projector</li>\r\n<li>Data Base Management System Laboratory </li>\r\n<li>Operating Systems (Unix/Linux) Laboratory </li>\r\n<li>Artificial Intelligence Laboratory </li>\r\n<li>C Programming Laboratory </li>\r\n<li>OOP&rsquo;s Programming Laboratory </li>\r\n<li>Network Programming Laboratory </li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '', '', '', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>CONSULTANCY AND RESEARCH</strong></p>\r\n<p><em>Area -</em></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Inspection of Computers and Hardware&rsquo;s</li>\r\n<li>Designing of Graphic &amp; multimedia.</li>\r\n<li>Software Design</li>\r\n<li>Software Development.</li>\r\n<li>Software Testing.</li>\r\n</ul>', 'branchreview/see_branch_review.php?id=81', 'NIT9 Raipur Computer Science Engineering CS99 CSE9 Computers'),
(82, 'branchreview/img/branch_info82.jpeg', 'img/branch_info_b82.jpeg', 'NIT Raipur', 'Electrical Engineering', '<p>Electrical Engineering department aims at imparting the state of the art knowledge and skills to the students. Thus, developing them into the excellent Electrical Engineers, Entrepreneurs, Scientists, and Academicians.</p>\r\n<p>The mission of the undergraduate program in Electrical Engineering is to provide students with a supportive environment that facilitates learning the advances in Electrical Engineering, to impart the state-of-the-art knowledge in the relevant field of Electrical Engineering and to provide excellence in learning through dedicated teaching, innovation and industrial projects.</p>', '<p><strong>LABORATORIES</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Basic Electrical Engineering Lab </li>\r\n<li>Machine Lab </li>\r\n<li>Power Electronics Lab </li>\r\n<li>Solid State Devices lab</li>\r\n<li>Computer Lab </li>\r\n<li>Analog Electronics Lab </li>\r\n<li>High Voltage Lab </li>\r\n<li>Power System Protection Lab</li>\r\n<li>Control Lab </li>\r\n<li>Instrumentation Lab (NI Data Acquisition Lab)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '', '', '', '<p><strong>TESTING CONSULTANCY AND RESEARCH</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Electrical Machine </li>\r\n<li>HIgh Voltage </li>\r\n<li>Instrumentation and measurement Calibration of meters</li>\r\n<li>Signal Processing &amp; Accounting </li>\r\n<li>Digital Image Processing </li>\r\n<li>Computer Application to power system </li>\r\n<li>Application of Artificial Intelligence to Power System </li>\r\n<li>Control System</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'branchreview/see_branch_review.php?id=82', 'NIT9 Raipur Electrical Engineering EE99 '),
(83, 'branchreview/img/branch_info83.jpeg', 'img/branch_info_b83.jpeg', 'NIT Raipur', 'Electronics and Telecommunication Engineering', '<p>To be a national leader in imparting quality education, carrying out research and technology development in the field of Electronics and Telecommunication Engineering.<br />Mission is to mould young students into rational thinking engineers and Transforming young students into engineers who are motivated by a passion for professional excellence and to produce engineers who are driven by human values and proactively engaged in betterment of society.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Year Of Establishment :</strong> 1985<br /><strong>Intake :</strong>Under Graduate Program - 92</p>', '<p><strong>LABORATORIES:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Analog Electronics Lab </li>\r\n<li>Communication Systems Lab </li>\r\n<li>Computer Lab</li>\r\n<li>Computer Vision Lab </li>\r\n<li>Digital Electronics Lab </li>\r\n<li>DSP &amp; VLSI Design Lab </li>\r\n<li>Embedded System Lab </li>\r\n<li>Instrumentation Lab </li>\r\n<li>Microwave and OFC Lab </li>\r\n<li>Electronics Workshop </li>\r\n</ul>', '', '', '', '', 'branchreview/see_branch_review.php?id=83', 'NIT9 Raipur Electronics and9 Telecommunication Engineering'),
(84, 'branchreview/img/branch_info84.jpeg', 'img/branch_info_b84.jpeg', 'NIT Raipur', 'Mechanical Engineering', '<p>Department offers undergraduate program (B.Tech.) in Mechanical Engineering and Postgraduate program (M.Tech.) in Thermal Engineering. It is one of the largest department of the institute with intake of 90 students for undergraduate course and 17 students for post graduate course. Department also offers Ph.D. program in all relevant discipline of Mechanical Engineering including Design, Production, Thermal and Industrial Management.<br />Vision is to produce innovative, entrepreneurial and successful engineers and technologists of high caliber for the nation, to serve as a valuable resource for industry and society.</p>', '<p><strong>LABORATORIES:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Strength of Materials</li>\r\n<li>Heat &amp; Mass Transfer</li>\r\n<li>Energy Conversion Lab</li>\r\n<li>Turbo Machines Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>IC Engine Lab</li>\r\n<li>Refrigeration &amp; AC Lab</li>\r\n<li>Dynamic Lab</li>\r\n<li>Metrology Lab</li>\r\n<li>Automobile Engineering Lab</li>\r\n<li>CAD-CAM Lab</li>\r\n<li>Computer Lab</li>\r\n<li>Workshop</li>\r\n</ul>', '', '', '', '', 'branchreview/see_branch_review.php?id=84', 'NIT9 Raipur Mech Mechanical Engineering '),
(85, 'branchreview/img/branch_info85.jpeg', 'img/branch_info_b85.jpeg', 'NIT Patna', 'Civil Engineering', '<p>The Department of Civil Engineering is the oldest and vibrant department of the institute, which was established along with the inception of the Institute in the year 1924.<br />The Department of Civil Engineering is committed to provide quality teaching and research opportunities to its undergraduate, postgraduate and doctoral students. Apart from UG programme, the department also offers M. Tech and Doctoralprogrammes in the areas of Structural Engineering, Transportation Engineering, Water Resource Engineering,Environmental Engineering and Geotechnical Engineering. The intake strength of the Civil Engineering Department is 92 for undergraduate (BTech)and 112forpostgraduate (MTech). Presently, 25 PhD scholars are enrolled with the department for pursuing their doctoral researchprogram.The teaching and education is directed towards their successful career in International and National Industries/ Institutions, Public and Private sectors,and enable them to qualify various competitive examinations such as IES, IAS, GATE examinations etc.<br />The Department is actively involved in international and national research projects, and high valued consultancy works for the Government, Private Sector and Industries.The department also offers its expertise in various consultancy works and research projects fordifferent industries and organisations in the locale. The Department supports in upbringing of society and other educational institutes by providing training, workshops, technology transfer, capacity building, and awareness programs.</p>', '<p><strong>Name of Laboratories</strong>&nbsp;:</p>\r\n<p style=\\"padding-left: 30px;\\"><br />1 Transportation Engineering Lab <br />2 Cement Concrete Lab <br />3 Water Resources Engineering Lab <br />4 Material Testing Lab <br />5 Geotechnical Lab <br />6 Environmental Engineering Lab <br />7 Heavy Structures Lab <br />8 Surveying Lab <br />9 Civil Engineering Computer Lab <br />10 Earthquake and Safety Clinic </p>', '', '', '', '<p><strong>Earthquake Safety Clinic and Centre (EqSC):</strong></p>\r\n<p>In the collaboration of NITP and BSDMA for their joint efforts, EqSC at NIT Patna recognizes the importance of research and development in the areas of disaster risk reduction (DRR), as well as, involvement of engineering faculty &amp; students in dissemination of DRR knowledge to the grass-root stakeholders. It embraces the need for awareness in vulnerable groups, creation of qualified man power in all fields related to DRR and meet societal expectations of disaster resilience. Currently, the center is doing a project on Rapid Visual Screening (RVS) of 400 school buildings in Seismic Zone V under National School Safety Program (NSSP) sponsored by NDMA, Govt. of India.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Centre for Water Resources Studies (CWRS):</strong></p>\r\n<p>The CWRS was set up at erstwhile Bihar College of Engineering under Patna University in response to perceived needs of the people of this region. The CWRS complex has a total floor area of 2000 m2 (Approximately).CWRS is involved in carrying out the research activity for Water Resources. A number of projects and research works have been undertaken and completed through CWRS. The centre has presently a very prestigious Chair named as DrRajendra Prasad Chair for Water Resources. TheChair has been established by Ministry of Water Resources, for the study of Impact of Climate Change on Water Resources. The main objective of the Chair is to carry out studies on water resources with special emphasis on assessment of effect of climate change and adaptation strategies in respect of planning, design and management of water resources systems of particularly Ganga Basin.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'branchreview/see_branch_review.php?id=85', 'NIT9 Patna Civil Engineering '),
(86, 'branchreview/img/branch_info86.jpeg', 'img/branch_info_b86.jpeg', 'NIT Patna', 'Computer Science and Engineering', '<p>The Department of Computer Science and Engineering offers courses leading to Bachelor of Technology in Computer Science and Engineering. The department has a very good infrastructure and faculty to provide excellent education. . The prominent among them includes Data Structures, Design and Analysis of Algorithms, System Programming, Computer Networks, Data Mining and Warehousing, Distributed and Parallel Computing, Mobile and Wireless Computing, Real-time Systems, Cryptography, Genetic Algorithm and Artificial Intelligence. Apart from these, students are also offered a wide variety of electives.</p>', '<p><strong>Departmental Laboratories</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Operating System Lab</li>\r\n<li>Simulation Lab </li>\r\n<li>Network System Lab</li>\r\n<li>Soft Computing Lab</li>\r\n<li>Research Scholar Lab </li>\r\n<li>Image Processing Lab </li>\r\n<li>HP Center of Excellence</li>\r\n</ul>', '', '', '', '<p><strong>Workshops/Seminars/Training/Course Conducted:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Short Term Training Program on \\"Information Security\\"</li>\r\n<li>Workshop on \\"Public Key Infrastructure (PKI)\\"</li>\r\n<li>Research Promotion Workshop on \\"Introduction to Graph and Geometric Algorithms\\"</li>\r\n<li>Workshop on \\"Wireless Network &amp; Security\\"</li>\r\n<li>Workshop on \\"Image Processing and Pattern Recognition\\"</li>\r\n<li>Workshop on \\"Scientific documentation processing using Latex\\"</li>\r\n<li>National level workshop Cum Short Term course on \\"Time Series Analysis and its Application\\"</li>\r\n<li>Workshop on \\"Network Management and Ethical Hacking\\"</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Expert Lectures Conducted:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Pattern Recognition with relevance to Soft Computing / Granular Data Mining with Applications to image processing and Bio-Informatics by Prof. Shankar K. Pal, Distinguished Scientist &amp; Former Director, ISI Kolkata.</li>\r\n<li>Soft Computing by Prof. Paramartha Dutta, VBU, Shantineketan.</li>\r\n<li>ABC of Big Data by Prof. Shankar K. Pal, Distinguished Scientist &amp; Former Director, ISI Kolkata</li>\r\n</ul>', 'branchreview/see_branch_review.php?id=86', 'NIT9 Patna Computer Science Engineering CS99 CSE9 Computers');
