(87, 'branchreview/img/branch_info87.jpeg', 'img/branch_info_b87.jpeg', 'NIT Patna', 'Electrical Engineering', '<p>The Department of Electrical Engineering was established in 1945 under Patna University with an intake of 20 students leading to Bachelor of Science(Engineering) degree of four year duration.he intake was increased from 30 to 40 students in 2005-06 sessions and further in 2006-07 the intake capacity has been increased to 60 students.</p>\r\n<p>M. Sc. (Engg) Degree in two specializations: (i) Power System Engineering and (ii) Control System Engineering with an intake capacity of 10 in each specialization.The intake in PG program was further increased to 18 students per specialization in 2004-05.The Microprocessor Laboratory and Power electronics laboratory were setup to meet the requirement of course curriculum and research activity.A course in Microprocessor was introduced along with many subjects in electronics leading to orientation required for the modem technology, such as Analog Electronics, Digital Electronics, Introduction to Communication and Digital Signal Processing.</p>\r\n<p>The Electrical Engineering department has well qualified faculty, majority of them are with Ph. D and M. Tech degree with specialization in the field of electrical power, control system and microcomputer based instrumentation &amp; control. The department has well qualified panel of visiting faculty from academics and industry. They visit to the department at regular interval to deliver expert lectures and discuss recent trends in the field of Electrical Engg, Power system -generation, transmission and distribution, Thyristorised controlled electrical drives used in industry, microcomputer applications in instrumentation and control etc.<br />The aim of the department is to equip the different labs for modern course curriculum in the field of engineering &amp; technology. In order to carryout research, development and consultancy work in active participation with the industry. The department is in process of establishing labs for computer based process control and digital signal processing. Very recently the department has established a high end SCADA lab with a expense of more than 5 crores which is used for final year ug and pg laboratories and also for research purpose by PhD scholars of the department.</p>', '<p><strong>Departmental Laboratories</strong></p>\r\n<p>The laboratory under this department includes Basic Electrical Engg.,Electrical Machines, Network Theory, Signals &amp; Systems, and Instrumentation, High Voltage Engg., Microprocessor, Switchgear &amp; protection labs. All labs are equipped with machines and instruments to meet the requirement of UG and PG course Curriculum as well as research &amp; development work being under taken by students and faculty. The department has a Computer Lab with all hardware and software facilities to meet the requirements of system modeling and analog and digital circuit simulation. The department has Analog and Digital Circuit Simulation software for analysis, PCB layout, MATLAB software for modeling, simulation of signals and systems and Power World Simulator for power system study.</p>', '', '', '', '<p><strong>SHORT TERM COURSES:</strong></p>\r\n<p>A two day short term course has been conducted on RAMS [Reliability, Availability,Maintainability and Safety] by Dr.Mukul Verma,[Ph.D. (IIT Delhi), Chartered Engineer (UK), Fellow IET (UK), IRSE (UK)] and Dr.Ajeet Pandey [Ph.D. (IIT Kharagpur)]</p>', 'branchreview/see_branch_review.php?id=87', 'NIT9 Patna Electrical Engineering EE99 '),
(88, 'branchreview/img/branch_info88.jpeg', 'img/branch_info_b88.jpeg', 'NIT Patna', ' Electronics & Communication Engineering', '<p>The Department of ECE was established in 1978. BCE was converted to National Institute of Technology Patna in 2004. Initially B.Tech. program in Electronics and Communication Engineering started with intake of 20, which has now become 90. Afterwards, M.Tech. program in Communication System started from 2011 with student strength of 18.<br />Presently, the department is also having Dual Degree (PG + PhD) and PhD programmes with 18 number of students.</p>', '<p><strong>Departmental Laboratories</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Electronic Circuit Lab</li>\r\n<li>Digital Electronics Lab</li>\r\n<li>Semiconductor Device Lab</li>\r\n<li>Computer Lab</li>\r\n<li>Communication Engineering Lab</li>\r\n<li>VLSI Lab</li>\r\n<li>DSP Lab (Under Dev)</li>\r\n<li>Microwave Engineering Lab</li>\r\n<li>Computational Electromagnetics Lab</li>\r\n<li>Project Lab</li>\r\n<li>Signal Processing Research Lab (Un- der Dev.)</li>\r\n<li>Propagation Lab (Under Dev.)</li>\r\n<li>OFC &amp; Photonics Research Lab (Un- der Dev.)</li>\r\n<li>PCB Fabrication Lab (Under Dev.)</li>\r\n</ul>', '<p><strong>Projects:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Remote Detection of Humans Trapped under Debris in Disaster Affected Areas Using RF Sensing of Cardiopulmonary Motion (Cluster Based Project) Development of Speech Based Person Authentication System in FPGA (Individual)</li>\r\n<li>Design and Optimization of CPW-Fed Multiband MIMO Antenna for Handheld Mobile Terminals</li>\r\n<li>Design of CPW-Fed Dual-Band MIMO Antenna for Handheld Mobile Terminals Dr. R. Bhattacharya</li>\r\n<li>Investigations on the Reduction of Side Lobe Label of Linear Antenna Arrays</li>\r\n<li>Intelligent Cognitive Radio Development of a Machine Learning based Cognitive Radio</li>\r\n<li>Development of Remote Person Authentication System Based On Speaker Verification</li>\r\n</ul>', '', '', '<p><strong>Interdepartmental Activity:</strong></p>\r\n<p>A PG course on Nano Technology has been established in cooperation with the department of Physics, Chemistry, ME., and CE.<br />ICT academy has been established for development/ up-gradation to improve the employability of the graduates/diploma holders in various streams in cooperation with other departments.<br /><br /></p>', 'branchreview/see_branch_review.php?id=88', 'NIT9 Patna Electronics & Communication Engineering ECE9'),
(89, 'branchreview/', '', 'NIT Patna', 'Mechanical Engineering', '<p><strong></strong>Bihar College of Engineering (BCE) was established in 1924 and it is the second oldest Engineering College in India. The Department of Mechanical Engineering was established in 1952 and the M.Tech Program was started in 1978. BCE was converted to National Institute of Technology Patna in 2004 Initially B.Tech. Program in Mechanical Engineering started with intake of 20, which has now become 90. Presently, the department is also having Dual Degree (PG + PhD) and PhD programmes with total of 36 students. <br /></p>', '<p><strong>LIST OF LABS/WORKSHOPS:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Heat and Mass Transfer.</li>\r\n<li>Refrigeration and Air conditioning.</li>\r\n<li>Dynamics of machinery.</li>\r\n<li>Steam Power System.</li>\r\n<li>Internal Combustion and Gas Turbine.</li>\r\n<li>Strength of Material.</li>\r\n<li>Design of machine elements.</li>\r\n<li>Fluid Machinery.</li>\r\n<li>Engineering Graphics.</li>\r\n<li>Machine Drawing.</li>\r\n<li>Manufacturing by shaping and joining.</li>\r\n<li>Black Smithy shop.</li>\r\n<li>Fitting shop.</li>\r\n<li>Foundry shop.</li>\r\n<li>Machine shop.</li>\r\n<li>Carpentry shop</li>\r\n<li>Welding shop.</li>\r\n<li>Sheet Metal shop.</li>\r\n<li>Refrigeration System.</li>\r\n<li>Design of Heat Exchanger Equipment</li>\r\n</ul>', '', '', '', '<p><strong>Workshop, Seminar &amp; Conference:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Student competitions by SAEINDIA ,Supra SAEINDIA student formula, Baja SAEINDIA ,Effi Cycle ,Aero design ,Eco kart ,SAEINDIA 2015 and 2nd among all the NITs and IITs.</li>\r\n<li>ASME STUDENT CHAPTER NIT PATNA.</li>\r\n<li>HPVC 2014 &amp; 2015</li>\r\n</ul>', 'branchreview/see_branch_review.php?id=89', 'NIT9 Patna Mech Mechanical Engineering '),
(90, 'branchreview/img/branch_info90.jpeg', 'img/branch_info_b90.jpeg', 'NIT Surathkal', 'Chemical Engineering', '<p>The Department of Chemical Engineering in National Institute of Technology Karnataka, Surathkal was started in the year 1965. A well balanced curriculum having both theory and practice, good infrastructure, well qualified and friendly faculty have been the hall mark of the department right from its inception. Additional space and modern instruments, have been built utilizing funds available from Ministry of HRD, GOI, TEQIP,TIFAC-CORE, DST,DBT,CSIR,MOEF etc.<br />The department offers an under graduate program in Chemical Engineering and three post graduate programs with specializations in Chemical Plant Design, Industrial Pollution Control and Industrial Biotechnology. In addition, M.Tech (Research) and Doctoral programmers are also offered. The department also offers product testing and industrial consultancy.</p>', '<p><strong>Conventional Laboratories:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Mass Transfer Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Heat Transfer Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Momentum Transfer Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Mechanical Operations Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Chemical Reaction Engineering Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Process Dynamics and Control Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Computation Laboratory</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Research labs:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Industrial Biotechnology Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Advanced Instrumentation Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Industrial Pollution Control Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Quality Testing Laboratory</li>\r\n</ul>', '<p><strong>Placements:</strong></p>\r\n<p><br /><em>Major comapnies that visits the campus:</em></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>O9 SOLUTIONS MANAGEMENT</li>\r\n<li>MU-SIGMA</li>\r\n<li>HSBC</li>\r\n<li>RELIANCE INDUSTRIES LTD</li>\r\n<li>HIKAL LTD</li>\r\n<li>HINDUSTAN UNILEVER LIMITED</li>\r\n<li>FRACTAL ANALYTICS</li>\r\n<li>LUPIN LIMITED ,BPCL</li>\r\n<li>EXXONMOBIL</li>\r\n<li>RELIANCE INDUSTRIES LTD</li>\r\n<li>LATENTVIEW ANALYTICS</li>\r\n<li>THINK AND LEARN</li>\r\n<li>PEPSICO</li>\r\n<li>ZS ASSOCIATES</li>\r\n<li>HINDUSTAN UNILEVER LIMITED</li>\r\n<li>CARBORUNDUM UNIVERSAL (MURUGAPPA GROUP)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Projects:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Air pollution induced immune cell dysfunction</li>\r\n<li>Biomass fuel burning smoke induced inflammation</li>\r\n<li>Heavy metal removal by melanin coated polymer matrix </li>\r\n<li>One step CZTS nano ink sythesis by sonochemical route for bifacial solar cell applications</li>\r\n<li>Electrochemical Deposition of CZTS for solar Cell Applications</li>\r\n<li>Synthesis and characterisation of spion embedded inorganic hollow core shell nanoparticles as a magnetic drug delivery vector </li>\r\n<li>Ambient Airborne particulate matter: Effect of biological component on lung inflammation </li>\r\n<li>DST FIST Level I</li>\r\n<li>Reverse Micellar Extraction Of Lactoferrin From Whey: Continuous Process</li>\r\n<li>Measurement and Characterization of ambient bioaerosols in Bangalore city, 53.00 Lakhs,</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><br /><strong>Major areas of Research</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Transfer operations</li>\r\n<li>Hydrodynamics studies in spouted bed and pulsed plate reactors</li>\r\n<li>RTD studies in bioreactors</li>\r\n<li>Mass Transfer, Heat transfer and Kinetic Studies</li>\r\n<li>ATPS Extraction</li>\r\n<li>Alternate Biofuel and Lubricants</li>\r\n<li>Environmental Engineering</li>\r\n<li>Degradation of Hydrocarbons using microbial consortia</li>\r\n<li>Industrial and domestics effluent treatment in aerobic and anaerobic systems</li>\r\n<li>Degradation of halogenated compounds by microbial consortia</li>\r\n<li>Management of municipal leachate</li>\r\n<li>Degradation of Hydrocarbons under Microwave, Sonication</li>\r\n<li>Advanced oxidation of organic effluents</li>\r\n<li>Industrial Biotechnology</li>\r\n<li>Studies on Enzyme Based Biosensors for Pharmaceutical Applications.</li>\r\n<li>Studies on Production of Tannin Acyl Hydrolase by Submerged State Fermentation</li>\r\n<li>Studies on Biological Oxidation of Sulfur Compounds using Autotrophic Sulfur Oxidizing Bacteria</li>\r\n<li>Studies on Microbial Bio-Transformations for the Synthesis of Stereoselective</li>\r\n<li>Novel pharmaceutical Drug Precursors and their Pharmacological Evaluation</li>\r\n</ul>', '', '', '<p><strong>The Department Has Expertise in the Following Areas to Render Professional Consultancy</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Environmental Impact Assessment and Management Plan</li>\r\n<li>Environmental Quality Monitoring</li>\r\n<li>Modelling of Water Quality</li>\r\n<li>Risk and Safety Assessment in Process Industries</li>\r\n<li>Environmental Audit and Safety Audit</li>\r\n<li>Air Quality Modelling and Impact Studies</li>\r\n<li>Process Equipment Design</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Consultancy &amp; Testing to Major Industries</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Mangalore Refineries and Petrochemicals Ltd., Mangalore</li>\r\n<li>BASF, Mangalore</li>\r\n<li>Mangalore Chemicals &amp; Fertilizers, Panambur</li>\r\n<li>New Mangalore Port Trust, Panambur, Mangalore</li>\r\n<li>Karnataka Milk Producers Federation Ltd., Mangalore</li>\r\n<li>Hindustan Lever Ltd., Mangalore</li>\r\n<li>Kudremukh Iron Ore Co. Ltd., Mangalore</li>\r\n<li>Canara Workshop Ltd., Mangalore</li>\r\n<li>Customs &amp; Excise Department, Mangalore</li>\r\n</ul>', 'branchreview/see_branch_review.php?id=90', 'NIT9 Surathkal Chem Chemical Engineering '),
(91, 'branchreview/img/branch_info91.jpeg', 'img/branch_info_b91.jpeg', 'NIT Surathkal', 'Civil Engineering ', '<p>The Department offers one undergraduate, five post-graduate and also research programmes leading to bachelor, master and doctoral degrees. The Department has well experienced faculty, skilled technical staff and well equipped laboratories. It is a recognized QIP centre for training of faculty from other engineering colleges and polytechnics. The Department has been always in the forefront in taking up R&amp;D initiatives and Industrial Consultancy assignments.<br />To produce Civil engineers with the necessary knowledge, skills and attitudes, who can be entrusted by the society to lead a sustainable world with enhanced quality of life.<br />To effectively train our students as Civil engineers who can serve the society competently, collaboratively and ethically as Planners, designers, constructors and operators of the built environment Leaders of the natural environment and its resources Innovators and integrators of ideas and technologies across the public, private and academic sectors Managers of risk and uncertainty caused by natural events, accidents and other threats. Leaders in discussions and decisions shaping public, environmental and infrastructure policies.</p>', '<p><strong>Facilities:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Digital Compression Testing Machine</li>\r\n<li>Field Boring Equipment</li>\r\n<li>Zond 12 e Ground Probing Radar with PRISM Software</li>\r\n<li>CESVA Sound Level Meter</li>\r\n<li>Immersion wheel Tracking Device</li>\r\n<li>Brookfield Viscometer</li>\r\n<li>Automatic Marshall Compactor</li>\r\n<li>MTS Servo Hydraulic Testing System</li>\r\n<li>CBR Testing Machine</li>\r\n<li>Fifth Wheel Bump Integrator</li>\r\n<li>Portable Falling Weight</li>\r\n<li>Deflectometer</li>\r\n<li>Marks 600 Traffic Counter cum Classifier</li>\r\n<li>Transyt 12 Software</li>\r\n<li>CUBE- Voyager Transport System Planning Software</li>\r\n<li>Radar Speed gun</li>\r\n<li>Polarizing Petrological Microscope, Soil Resistivity meter, Aquameter.</li>\r\n<li>State-of-the-art computational facilities are available in a Divisional Level CAD LAB Facility</li>\r\n</ul>', '<p><strong>R &amp; D Projects</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Experimental investigation on rutting and flexural behavior of structural asphalt mixes with warm mix asphalt additives.</li>\r\n<li>Hydrogen Loaded Concrete as Integrated n, a, &szlig;, and ? Radiation Shield.</li>\r\n<li>Dynamic Soil Structure Interaction Effects in Multi-storied Structures on homogeneous and Geo-synthetic Reinforced Soils.</li>\r\n<li>Collaboration in Research in Structural Engineering.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '', '', '<p><strong>Consultancy:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Structural Analysis and Design</li>\r\n<li>Structural distress Assessment and Rehabilitation</li>\r\n<li>Non-Destructive Testing of Concrete Structures</li>\r\n<li>Concrete Mix Design</li>\r\n<li>Testing of Building Materials</li>\r\n<li>Highway and Railway Material Testing</li>\r\n<li>Design of Pavements</li>\r\n<li>Design of Bituminous concrete Mixes</li>\r\n<li>CBR Tests</li>\r\n<li>Traffic Planning</li>\r\n<li>Distance and level Measurements</li>\r\n<li>Estimation of Earthwork</li>\r\n<li>Soil investigations Tests for Soil Classification</li>\r\n<li>Safe Bearing Capacity of foundation systems</li>\r\n<li>Slope stability Analysis and Design of slopes</li>\r\n<li>Plate load Tests</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'branchreview/see_branch_review.php?id=91', 'NIT9 Surathkal Civil Engineering '),
(92, 'branchreview/img/branch_info92.jpeg', 'img/branch_info_b92.jpeg', 'NIT Surathkal', 'Computer Science & Engineering.  ', '<p>Department of Computer Science &amp; Engineering holds a position of pride in NITK. It has consistently fulfilled its role of producing Computer Engineers ready to satisfy the needs of the IT world. The department has always attracted the best of engineering aspirants from all over the country. It has a well qualified and experienced faculty team. The Department offers B.Tech., M.Tech., M.Tech.(By Research) and Ph.D. in Computer Science and Engineering discipline. The department has adequate facilities to support these teaching activities. As computers become obsolete fast, it is necessary to continuously upgrade the facilities. Students of the department have sufficient high end computing facilities. The Department is actively involved in various Research activities. The department has signed MoU with IBM, Intel, Leeds Metropolitan University and others, for academic collaborative projects.</p>', '<p><strong>Facilities:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>High End Server Systems</li>\r\n<li>IBM Open Power Server System </li>\r\n<li>Workstation/Computers </li>\r\n<li>There are more than 15 LaserJet Printers, LCD Projector, 40&rdquo; LCD TV etc for academic activities support.</li>\r\n<li>All the Computers/Servers/Workstations are networked in the departmental LAN and the electrically connected with UPS systems.</li>\r\n<li>Networking accessories</li>\r\n<li>Digital Electronics Hardwares</li>\r\n<li>Digital Storage Oscilloscope</li>\r\n<li>Windows Lab/UG Lab-1</li>\r\n<li>Intel Lab/UG Lab-3</li>\r\n<li>Software Lab/UG Lab-2</li>\r\n<li>Research Project Lab</li>\r\n<li>I PG Lab</li>\r\n<li>Information Security Lab/II PG(IS) Lab</li>\r\n<li>PG Project Lab I</li>\r\n<li>PG Project Lab II</li>\r\n<li>Research Lab</li>\r\n<li>Digital Electronics Lab</li>\r\n</ul>', '<p><strong>Projects:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Design and evaluation of Object oriented Verification approach for Distributed Software Systems</li>\r\n<li>Information Security Education and awareness</li>\r\n<li>Vision Based Activity monitoring for surveillance application</li>\r\n<li>National Mission Project on Education through ICT - &ldquo;Developing suitable pedagogical methods for various classes, intellectual calibers and research in e-learning&rdquo;</li>\r\n<li>Development of tool for Detection of SQL injection vulnerability in Web Applications</li>\r\n<li>Development of tool for Detection of XML based injection vulnerabilities in Web Applications</li>\r\n</ul>', '', '<p><strong>Department has interaction with the following corporations.</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Intel</li>\r\n<li>Microsoft</li>\r\n<li>IBM</li>\r\n<li>Oracle</li>\r\n<li>Yahoo</li>\r\n<li>Dell R &amp; D</li>\r\n<li>Infosys</li>\r\n<li>Corporation Bank HO</li>\r\n<li>MRPL</li>\r\n<li>NMPT</li>\r\n<li>MCF</li>\r\n<li>KIOCL</li>\r\n</ul>', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Events</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>NITK WiNG\\''s 1st Workshop on Simulation of Wireless Networks</li>\r\n<li>Workshop on Information Security Awareness for School Teachers of Dakshina Kannada District</li>\r\n<li>NITK WiNG\\''s 2nd Workshop on Simulation of Wired and Wireless Networks </li>\r\n<li>Workshop on Introduction to Research Methodologies</li>\r\n<li>Workshop on Android Application Development</li>\r\n<li>Short Term Training Program on Recent Advances and Research Directions in Software Engineering </li>\r\n<li>NITK WiNG\\''s 3rd Workshop on Simulation of Wired and Wireless Networks </li>\r\n<li>Recent Developments in Software Testing </li>\r\n<li>Workshop on Network Simulator </li>\r\n<li>Workshop on Medical Image Computing</li>\r\n<li>Short Term Training Program on Big Data and Machine Learning </li>\r\n<li>Workshop on Neural Networks\\'' Approach for Speech Tasks</li>\r\n<li>International Summer School on Leading Edge Software Engineering </li>\r\n<li>Workshop on Fundamentals of Speech Processing</li>\r\n<li>NITK WiNG\\''s 4th Workshop on Simulation of Wired and Wireless Networks</li>\r\n<li>3rd International Conference on Eco-friendly Computing and Communication Systems </li>\r\n<li>2nd International Conference on Advanced Computing, Networking and Security </li>\r\n<li>International Symposium on Cloud and Service Computing </li>\r\n<li>International Conference on Advanced Computing, Networking and Security</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'branchreview/see_branch_review.php?id=92', 'NIT9 Surathkal Computer Science Engineering CS99 CSE9 Computers '),
(93, 'branchreview/img/branch_info93.jpeg', 'img/branch_info_b93.jpeg', 'NIT Surathkal', 'Electrical and Electronics Engineering', '<p>The Department of Electrical and Electronics Engineering was established right from the inception of the institute with the under-graduate programme. The post-graduate programme in Power and Energy Systems was started in the year 1992. Formal research activities leading to a doctoral degree (PhD) were introduced in the year 2003. The department has always exerted the best of its effort to meet the objectives of achieving technical excellence in the areas of Electrical and Electronics Engineering such as power systems, power electronics and drive systems, energy systems, instrumentation, control, industrial automation, analog and digital electronics, signal processing, microprocessor and microcontrollers. The department has well-equipped state-of-the-art laboratories to complement the theoretical coursework. The department also undertakes many consultancy projects from industry and other organisations. There are several full-time Ph. D. scholars pursuing research in the department in addition to the part-time registrants. The faculty members are actively engaged in the Research and Development activities with externally sponsored projects from various funding agencies like CPRI, MoPs, MoCIT, KSCST, DELL, Schneider Electric, L&amp;T, Robert Bosch to name a few. Students from the department are recruited by multinational Core-companies as well as ITcompanies.&nbsp;</p>', '<p><strong>Facilities in the Department:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Digital Implementation Using Microprocessors/microcontrollers/DSC,DSP and FPGA hardware and software facilities from Xilinx, Micro sim, free scale semiconductors and Texas instruments</li>\r\n<li>Energy Audit Equipments</li>\r\n<li>Real Time Hardware emulating Flat-forms</li>\r\n<li>Wind solar Hybrid microgrid system</li>\r\n<li>High voltage lab with 100kV 100 mA HV ac</li>\r\n<li>source and associated DC and impulse voltage test facility.5kV Tera Ohm insulation Tester.</li>\r\n<li>Insulation oil Test kit, 35pF, 100kV standard capacitor, Digital earth Resistance Test kit.</li>\r\n<li>AEPD analyser</li>\r\n<li>VSC models developing-house,testing/performance evaluation of power converters</li>\r\n<li>scale down model of 4 machine power systems, power system simulation lab within house developed simulation packages</li>\r\n<li>Departmental computational facilities catering for signals and systems, power system dynamics, control systems and digital signal processing laboratory</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '<p><strong>Research and Development</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Control Strategies for Dynamic Voltage Restorer under Unbalanced and Disturbed Grid Conditions</li>\r\n<li>Utility Interative based Power supply</li>\r\n<li>Establishing Center of Excellence (CoE) in &ldquo;Renewable Energy Source integrated Smart Grid Technologies (RENEST)&rdquo;</li>\r\n<li>FPGA Implementation of MPPT For PV System</li>\r\n<li>Development of Virtual Laboratory through Simulation for Electrical Engineering Applications</li>\r\n<li>Integration of Multiple Distributed Generation Sources to the Grid</li>\r\n<li>Infrastructure Creation and Upgradation underTechnical Education Quality Improvement Programme (TEQIP)</li>\r\n<li>Development of Hardware for Energy Management Systems</li>\r\n<li>Modernisation in Power Electronics and Drives lab</li>\r\n</ul>', '', '', '<p><strong>Consultancy Project Details</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Calibration of energy meters, CTs and other instruments.</li>\r\n<li>Capacity evaluation of industrial drive motors and welding transformers.</li>\r\n<li>Measurement of Earth resistance of storage tanks of M/s MRPL Ltd., Mangalore.</li>\r\n<li>Development of PAM induction motor</li>\r\n<li>Monitoring and recording of starting current </li>\r\n<li>Failure analysis of the soft starter</li>\r\n<li>Electrification of annexe building of Corporation Bank Head Office </li>\r\n<li>Cable Testing </li>\r\n<li>Electric Drive Testing &amp; Redesign </li>\r\n<li>Gas turbine cycle time measurement </li>\r\n<li>Calibration of high voltage test equipment like Holiday detectors, insulation testing apparatus etc.</li>\r\n</ul>', 'branchreview/see_branch_review.php?id=93', 'NIT9 Surathkal Electrical Engineering EE99 and9 Electronics Electrical Engineering EEE9'),
(94, 'branchreview/img/branch_info94.jpeg', 'img/branch_info_b94.jpeg', 'NIT Surathkal', 'Mechanical Engineering', '<p>Established in the year 1960, the Department of Mechanical Engineering traversed the path of knowledge dissemination and generation as well as delivering over 3500 Mechanical Engineering graduates to the Nation. Over these 53 glorious years, it has carved a niche for itself in the key areas of teaching, research, consultancy, administration and community services. The Department of Mechanical Engineering prioritize the necessary revamping of Mechanical Engineering education, which is driven primarily by dynamics of technological advances and sustainable development and with active involvement of industry, alumni, research organizations and other stakeholders. Department offers B.Tech, M.Tech and Ph.D. programmes. department caters to more than 600 B.Tech. students, 150 M.Tech. students and 65 Ph.D. Scholars.</p>', '<p><strong>Labs:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>CAD/CAM Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Materials Characterization Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Vibration and Condition Monitoring Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Robotics Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Metrology Laboratory </li>\r\n<li>Refrigeration and Air-conditioning Research Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Microsystems Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Heat Transfer Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Machine Dynamics and Vibration Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>CNC, Pneumatic and Electro Pneumatic Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>IC Engine Research Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Fuels Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Theory of Machines Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Automotive Electronics Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Machine Shop </li>\r\n<li>Carpentry Shop</li>\r\n<li>Fitting Shop</li>\r\n<li>Sheet Metal Shop</li>\r\n</ul>', '<p><strong>R &amp; D Projects</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Investigation of machining characteristics of TiNi based Shape Memory alloy using Wire-EDM</li>\r\n<li>Design, Fabrication and Characterization of Magneto-Rheological (MR) Dampers for Industrial Applications</li>\r\n<li>Investigation on Passive Damping Capability of Natural Fiber Reinforced Composite and Visco-elastic Sandwich Structure</li>\r\n<li>Development of HVOF sprayed cermets coatings in improving resistance to hot corrosion and erosion of gas turbine alloys</li>\r\n<li>Vibration based structural health monitoring and progressive failure analysis of a rotating tapered composite plate &ndash; (Co-Investigator)</li>\r\n<li>Remote triggered Lab</li>\r\n<li>Centre for System Design</li>\r\n<li>Virtual Lab</li>\r\n<li>Investigation on enhanced pool boiling methods for cooling of micro-electronic devices</li>\r\n</ul>', '', '', '', 'branchreview/see_branch_review.php?id=94', 'NIT9 Surathkal Mech Mechanical Engineering '),
(95, 'branchreview/img/branch_info95.jpeg', 'img/branch_info_b95.jpeg', 'NIT Trichy', 'Chemical Engineering', '<p>The Department of Chemical Engineering,NIT Trichy is regarded as one of the premier centers for Chemical Engineering in India by industries as well as academia. It also has the distinction of being ranked as one of the top seven Chemical Engineering divisions in India by Chemical Engineering Faculties. It offers a B.Tech programme and M.Tech programme in Energy Engineering, Plant Design and Process Controls &amp; Instrumentation.<br />The department is backed by highly qualified and experienced faculty, most of whom have been involved in various industrial projects and consultancy services. The students, guided by the experienced faculty, have presented many papers in India and abroad and have won several National Level Design Competitions. The programme is supplemented by several state-of-the-art laboratories, which cover all areas of practical interest. Other than traditional laboratories like Fluid Mechanics, Heat and Mass transfer and Mechanical Operations, the students are exposed to specialised ones like Reaction Engineering, Process Control, Biotechnology. The Process Control lab, one of the best in the country, is equipped with the latest instruments for recording and analysis of data used for simulating plant conditions.</p>', '<p><strong>Department Labs</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Fluid Mechanics</li>\r\n<li>Mechanical Operations</li>\r\n<li>Technical Analysis</li>\r\n<li>Heat Transfer</li>\r\n<li>Chemical Reaction Engineering</li>\r\n<li>Mass Transfer </li>\r\n<li>Process Dynamics and Control</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '<p><strong>Placements</strong></p>\r\n<p>Different companies, with both Technical and Software profiles have been recruiting students from this Department.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Here is a brief list of the companies:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>ABB LIMITED</li>\r\n<li>ACC CEMENTS</li>\r\n<li>ANAND GROUP</li>\r\n<li>BALMER LAWRIE</li>\r\n<li>BHARAT PETROLEUM CORPORATION LIMITED</li>\r\n<li>BRITISH OXYGEN COMPANY</li>\r\n<li>CASTROL-BP</li>\r\n<li>CPCL</li>\r\n<li>DALMIA CEMENTS</li>\r\n<li>DRDO</li>\r\n<li>THERMAX</li>\r\n<li>E.I.L.</li>\r\n<li>ENERGY SOLUTIONS</li>\r\n<li>ESSAR GROUP</li>\r\n<li>FOSTER WHEELER</li>\r\n<li>GULF OIL</li>\r\n<li>HPCL</li>\r\n<li>IOCL</li>\r\n<li>JSW STEEL LTD.</li>\r\n<li>LARSEN &amp; TOUBRO</li>\r\n<li>MADRAS CEMENTS</li>\r\n<li>MARICO</li>\r\n<li>MURUGAPPA GROUP</li>\r\n<li>NFCL</li>\r\n<li>PRAXAIR</li>\r\n<li>RELIANCE INDIA LTD.</li>\r\n<li>SANMER</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Projects</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>MHRD Thrust Area project titled,\\"CFD modelling of chemical process equipment\\".</li>\r\n<li>MHRD - MODROBS project on Modernization of chemical reaction Engineering Laboratory in proress.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Industrial projects</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Hydrogen from Biomass for Fuel Cell application: Process research &amp; Development, sponsored by High Energy Batteries, Trichy</li>\r\n<li>Beneficiation of iron Ore &amp; Coal: Process Research &amp; Development, Sponsored by Tata Steel, Jamshedpur.</li>\r\n<li>Enzymatic transformations for value added esters and chemicals from oils &amp; Fats, Sponsored by Bunge India pvt Ltd.</li>\r\n<li>CO2 sequestration from Power plants by Absorption process- Sponsored by BHEL, Trichy- Outlay Rs. 4.8 Lakhs - agreed in Principle awaiting clearance.</li>\r\n</ul>', '', '', '', 'branchreview/see_branch_review.php?id=95', 'NIT9 Trichy Chem Chemical Engineering '),
(96, 'branchreview/img/branch_info96.jpeg', 'img/branch_info_b96.jpeg', 'NIT Trichy', 'Civil Engineering', '<p>To provide valuable resources for industry and society through excellence in technical education and research and offers state-of-the-art undergraduate, postgraduate and doctoral programmesand to &nbsp;generate new knowledge by engaging in cutting-edge research and Shaping infrastructure development with societal focus&nbsp;</p>', '<p><strong>Laboratories</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Computational Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Environmental Engineering Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Fluid Mechanics Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Strength of Materials Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Structural Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Soil Mechanics Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Survey Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Transporation Laboratory</li>\r\n</ul>', '', '', '', '<p><strong>Research And Consultancy</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Consultancy</strong>&nbsp;:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Strength of materials Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Structural Engineering Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Geotechnical Engineering Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Geotechnical investigations for Civil engineering works</li>\r\n<li>Study of Failures</li>\r\n<li>Environmental Engineering Laboratory/ Water Resources</li>\r\n<li>Transportation Engineering Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Water and wastewater quality testing</li>\r\n<li>Design of Treatment plants</li>\r\n<li>Bioremediation</li>\r\n<li>Air quality modeling</li>\r\n<li>Pipe network distribution system design</li>\r\n<li>Soil testing</li>\r\n<li>Design of foundations</li>\r\n<li>Topographic survey</li>\r\n<li>Traffic management</li>\r\n<li>Transportation planning</li>\r\n<li>Pavement design</li>\r\n<li>RS, GIS and GPS</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><br /><strong>Sponsored Project</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Strengthening of the Transportation Engineering Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Multimedia Tools for Teaching of Civil Engineering</li>\r\n<li>Household Survey to Assess Rural Transport Infrastructure, Tamilnadu</li>\r\n<li>Development of a Remote Sensing Image Interpretation Cell for Rural and Urban Planning</li>\r\n<li>Modernisation of Transportation Engineering Laboratory through Plan Fund</li>\r\n<li>Remote Sensing Application in Interpretation and Monitoring of Ambient Air Quality</li>\r\n<li>GIS-GPS Based Monitoring of Public Transport Vehicles</li>\r\n<li>Rural Road Traffic Volume Study in Tamilnadu</li>\r\n<li>Rural Road Pavement Performance Study (RRPPS)</li>\r\n<li>Coir Geotextiles Reinforced Low Volume Rural Road Pavement Performance Studies in Tamilnadu and Puducherry</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><br /><strong>Seminar / Workshop</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Design, Construction, Quality Control and Maintenance of Bridges</li>\r\n<li>Forensic Engineering Practice</li>\r\n<li>Workshop on &ldquo;AutoCAD&rdquo;</li>\r\n<li>Role of Geotechnical Engineering on infrastructure development</li>\r\n<li>Finite Element Analysis</li>\r\n<li>Bridge design, Fabrication and Testing</li>\r\n<li>Reliability Analysis and Design of Sub structures</li>\r\n<li>Recent trends in water resources and coastal modeling</li>\r\n<li>Cleaner Technologies for Water</li>\r\n<li>Transportation Infrastructure Planning</li>\r\n</ul>', 'branchreview/see_branch_review.php?id=96', 'NIT9 Trichy Civil Engineering '),
(97, 'branchreview/img/branch_info97.jpeg', 'img/branch_info_b97.jpeg', 'NIT Trichy', 'Computer Science and Engineering', '<p>The Department of Computer Science and Engineering with its cohesive team of faculty members, offers a sound program at the UG as well as the PG levels. The curriculum is a blend of the conventional and theradical. It is updated regularly to keep up with the growing demands and the changing trends of the software industry and research laboratories. Core courses include Programming Languages, Computer Architecture,System Software, Networking Technologies and Artificial Intelligence.<br />State-of-the-Art computing facilities are provided by the Octagon Computer Center - Computer Support Group, our Computer Centre in the newly established Centre. They epitomize the cutting edge technology available in our college. The servers which support the LAN, also provide a Linux/Unix environment, include SUN SPARC and Silicon Graphics workstations.</p>', '<p><strong>Lab Facilities</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Data Structures Lab</li>\r\n<li>Linear and Digital ICs</li>\r\n<li>System Programming Lab</li>\r\n<li>Microprocessing and Interfacing</li>\r\n<li>Programming Languages</li>\r\n<li>Operating Systems</li>\r\n<li>Database Management Systems</li>\r\n<li>Compiler Design</li>\r\n<li>Software Systems</li>\r\n</ul>', '<p><strong>Projects</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Networking</li>\r\n<li>Data Base Management Systems</li>\r\n<li>Operating Systems</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '', '', '', 'branchreview/see_branch_review.php?id=97', 'NIT9 Trichy Computer Science Engineering CS99 CSE9 Computers'),
(98, 'branchreview/img/branch_info98.jpeg', 'img/branch_info_b98.jpeg', 'NIT Trichy', 'Electrical and Electronics Engineering', '<p>The Department of Electrical and Electronics Engineering, NIT, Tiruchirappalli was started in the year 1964. It offers one Under-Graduate programme (B.Tech.), two Post-Graduate programmes (M.Tech. in Power Systems and Power Electronics) and also research programmes (M.S. and Ph.D.) in the various fields of Electrical and Electronics Engineering. Thus, the department has dedicated and state of the art teaching / research laboratories. The department is recognized for excellence in research (First Department in NIT-T to be accorded QIP status for Ph.D. programe), teaching and service to the profession.<br />The faculty members have strong sense of responsibility to provide the finest possible education for both graduate and undergraduate students. The academic strength of the faculty is reflected by the alumni, many of whom are in the top echelons of industry and academia both in India and abroad.</p>', '<p><strong></strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Laboratories:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Computer Center</li>\r\n<li>Electronics Lab</li>\r\n<li>Machines Lab</li>\r\n<li>Power Electronics Lab</li>\r\n<li>Power Systems Lab</li>\r\n</ul>', '<p><strong>Project:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Dynamic Loading of Conveyer Drive Heads in Mines</li>\r\n<li>Electrical design and drawing for Indian Naval</li>\r\n<li>Design, Development and Analysis of Bio-inspired Control strategies for stand-alone solar powered LED lighting systems</li>\r\n<li>Saving Techniques for the Efficient Utilization of Air Conditioner by Using Renewable Power Resources.</li>\r\n<li>Maximum Power Extraction from Off &ndash; shore Winddriven Generators through HVDC Transmission system</li>\r\n<li>Power Optimization Controller in Switched Mode</li>\r\n<li>Power Supplies Connected with Renewable Energy Sources</li>\r\n</ul>', '', '', '', 'branchreview/see_branch_review.php?id=98', 'NIT9 Trichy Electrical Engineering EE99 and9 Electronics Electrical Engineering EEE9'),
(99, 'branchreview/img/branch_info99.jpeg', 'img/branch_info_b99.jpeg', 'NIT Trichy', 'Electronics and Communication Engineering ', '<p>The department offers Undergraduate (UG), Post Graduate (PG), M.S.(By Research) and Ph.D degree programs that provide students with the knowledge and tools they need to succeed in the Electronics and Communication Engineering. Research in the department focuses on high-impact various disciplines: Communication systems, Wireless networks, Signal and Image Processing, RF MEMS and MIC, Microwave antennas, Optical communication and Photonics, VLSI technologies.<br />Currently the department offers four year B.Tech course with student intake of 120. In 1976 the department started M.E. course in Communication Systems and in 1999, M.E. course in VLSI System was started. Both the PG courses having an intake of 28 students. Department produced first doctoral degree in 1989. In 2005, department started the course M.S. (By Research).<br />The department of ECE is one of the established and largest departments in the institution. Our faculty brings state-of-the-art research, development, and design experience into the classroom, ensuring that our students and alumni are able to apply for registration as professional engineers in all part of global engineering and the scientific community.</p>', '<p><strong></strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Laboratories</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\\"padding-left: 30px;\\">1. Electronic Devices Laboratory<br />2. Digital Circuits and System Laboratory<br />3. Microprocessor and Microcontroller Laboratory<br />4. Communication Engineering Laboratory<br />5. Signal Processing Laboratory<br />6. Microwave and MIC Laboratory<br />7. Fiber Optics Laboratory<br />8. VLSI Design Laboratory<br />9. Wireless System Design Laboratory</p>\r\n<p style=\\"padding-left: 30px;\\">&nbsp;</p>', '<p><strong>Research Projects Already Completed</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Bearing Estimation and Source Identification using High Resolution Spectral Estimation Techniques</li>\r\n<li>Sonar Echo and Signal Processor Simulators</li>\r\n<li>Development of Active Beam forming and Passive DOA Estimation for a Fast</li>\r\n<li>Development of Optimal Passive Tracking Algorithms for Multiple Maneouvering Targets</li>\r\n<li>Sonar System Simulation</li>\r\n<li>Sonar Signal Synthesis for Active and Passive Sonar</li>\r\n<li>Passive Synthetic Aperture Sonar</li>\r\n<li>Development of Voice Activity Detection and comfort noise Generation for 7xx Audio codes</li>\r\n<li>Equalizers for Wireless Communication</li>\r\n<li>Analysis and Design of Coplanar Waveguide filters</li>\r\n<li>Design &amp; Analysis of FPGA-Based Wavepipelined Structures for DSP Applications</li>\r\n</ul>', '', '', '<p><strong>Conferences/ Workshops organized by the Department:</strong><br /> </p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Pattern Analysis and Biologically inspired Algorithms (PABIA)</li>\r\n<li>Colloquium on Corrosion Control and Surface Engineering with a focus: R&amp;D and industrial scenarioorganized by CECASE.</li>\r\n<li>Telemedicine</li>\r\n<li>CAD of Microwaves</li>\r\n<li>Recent Trends in Wireless Networks</li>\r\n<li>Research Methods and Latex</li>\r\n<li>Cancer Perspectives-Then and now by Dr.V.Shantha ,Chairman cancer Institute, Adayar, Chennai.</li>\r\n<li>National Conference on Corrosion, Surface Engineering &amp; Tribology (CST 2013) under CECASE</li>\r\n<li>ISTE Workshop on Signals and Systems</li>\r\n<li>A FDP on Entrepreneurship Development and Management</li>\r\n<li>Advances in cognitive radio and its hardware implementation<br /><br /></li>\r\n</ul>', 'branchreview/see_branch_review.php?id=99', 'NIT9 Trichy Electronics and9 Communication Engineering ECE9'),
(100, 'branchreview/img/branch_info100.jpeg', 'img/branch_info_b100.jpeg', 'NIT Trichy', 'Mechanical Engineering', '<p>The Mechanical Engineering Department of NITT has had the reputation of being among the finest in the country and is dedicated towards the advancement of technology and science.<br />An interactive relationship is maintained between the students and staff which enables the students to develop a sound foundation in the stream in a conducive environment. This is also reflected in our campus placement which has been 100% year after year with our students getting placed in the top industrial houses of the country. About 20% of our students proceed to top universities abroad to pursue their higher education.The calibration facilities developed by the department are in accordance with the National Standards for calibration of pressure, temperature and speed measurement. These facilities are utilized by ISO 9000 certified companies.<br />The department has an excellent industrial interaction and contributes to the industry by offering consultancy services. Some of them are : Heavy Alloy Penetrator Project (HAPP), Oil and Natural Gas Corporation (ONGC) and Bharat Heavy Electricals Limited (BHEL) and its ancillaries.</p>', '<p><strong>Facilities and Services</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Metrology Lab</li>\r\n<li>Thermal Lab</li>\r\n<li>Dynamics Lab</li>\r\n<li>Heat and Mass Transfer Lab</li>\r\n<li>R.G and A.C Lab</li>\r\n<li>Automobile Lab</li>\r\n<li>CAD &amp; Simulation Lab</li>\r\n<li>Safety Lab</li>\r\n<li>Department Library</li>\r\n</ul>', '', '', '', '<p><strong>Ongoing Projects</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Theoretical and Experimental investigations on performance influencing parameters of industrial Air compressors</li>\r\n<li>Process Modeling and Online Monitoring of Laser Beam Welding</li>\r\n<li>Experimental Investigation and finite Element Simulation of Workability of Al-TiC Powder Metallurgy Composites during Cold Upsetting<br /> <br /><strong>Patents Obtained</strong></li>\r\n<li>Non return valve for the pneumatic tube of a vehicle tyre</li>\r\n<li>Instantaneous swept volume measuring device for reciprocating machines</li>\r\n<li>An auxiliary starter and controller assemble for air compressor system</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'branchreview/see_branch_review.php?id=100', 'NIT9 Trichy Mech Mechanical Engineering '),
(101, 'branchreview/img/branch_info101.jpeg', 'img/branch_info_b101.jpeg', 'NIT WARANGAL', 'Civil Engineering ', '<p>Civil engineering is a broad field of engineering that deals with the planning, construction, and maintenance of fixed structures, or public works, as they are related to earth, water, or civilization and their processes. Most civil engineering today deals with power plants, bridges, roads, railways, structures, water supply, irrigation, the natural environment, sewer, flood control, transportation and traffic. In essence, civil engineering may be regarded as the profession that makes the world a more agreeable place in which to live.</p>', '<p><strong>Labs:</strong></p>\r\n<p>The Department of Civil Engineering is having well established laboratories catering the needs of both B.Tech. and M.Tech. programmes. Laboratory courses are designed to support theoretical concepts taught. All the laboratories are equipped well. Project works, dissertation works and thesis works are supported by the laboratories. The following are the main laboratories in the department.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Concrete Technology &amp; Structures Lab</li>\r\n<li>Engineering Geology lab</li>\r\n<li>Environmental Engineering LAB</li>\r\n<li>Fluid Mechanics &amp; WRE Lab</li>\r\n<li>Material Testing LAB</li>\r\n<li>Rock Mechanics lab</li>\r\n<li>RS&amp; GIS LAB</li>\r\n<li>Soil Mechanics Lab</li>\r\n<li>Surveying Lab</li>\r\n<li>Transportation Engineering lab</li>\r\n</ul>', '<p><strong>Projects:</strong></p>\r\n<p>The Department has been active in carrying out Research Projects, since its inception. Main emphasis is always on applied research, in tune with the industry needs. Several research projects were sponsored by MHRD, AICTE, UGC, CSIR, DST, MOUA, MOST, CWC, CRRI, CBIP, R&amp;D wings of AP State Government undertakings, etc.</p>', '', '', '<p><strong>Consultancy:</strong><br />The Department of Civil Engineering has been in forefront, in offering its expertise to provide solutions to field problems. Many public sector undertakings and private companies consult the Department for technical advice. The Department has also excellent rapport with various State and central government Departments and several municipal bodies and UDAs. Some of the organisations, which are in consultation, are listed below.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>NTPC</li>\r\n<li>M/s Gammon India</li>\r\n<li>APSRTC, Govt. Of Andhra Pradesh, Hyderabad</li>\r\n<li>Panchayat Raj Engineering Department, Govt. Of Andhra Pradesh, Hyderabad</li>\r\n<li>R &amp; B Department, Govt. Of Andhra Pradesh, Hyderabad</li>\r\n<li>Public Health Department, Govt. Of Andhra Pradesh, Hyderabad.</li>\r\n<li>Singareni Colleries Company Ltd., Govt. Of Andhra Pradesh, Kothagudem.</li>\r\n<li>Irrigation and Command Area Development Department, Govt. Of Andhra Pradesh, Hyderabad</li>\r\n<li>M/s Larson &amp; Turbo Ltd., Hyderabad.</li>\r\n<li>M/s Captial Fortunes Ltd., Hyderabad,</li>\r\n<li>M/s MC Consulting Engineers (P) Ltd., Hyderabad,</li>\r\n</ul>', 'branchreview/see_branch_review.php?id=101', 'NIT9 WARANGAL Civil Engineering ');
INSERT INTO `branch_review` (`id`, `img`, `b_img`, `clg`, `branch`, `intro`, `infa_labs`, `branch_scope`, `branch_faculty`, `col`, `about`, `url`, `tags`) VALUES
(102, 'branchreview/img/branch_info102.jpeg', 'img/branch_info_b102.jpeg', 'NIT WARANGAL', 'Electrical Engineering ', '<p>The Department of Electrical Engineering is one of the oldest departments of the National Institute of Technology, Warangal (NITW). With excellent faculty, the Department of Electrical Engineering offers undergraduate (B.Tech) and graduate (M.Tech) in Power Electronics &amp; Drives and Power Systems and research (Ph.D) programmes.<br />The Department is strong with most of faculty members holding PhD degrees and expertise in various fields. The broad areas of expertise include State Estimation and Real Time Control of Power Systems, Applications of ANN and Fuzzy Logic in Power Systems, Power System Deregulation, Power System Transients, Power Quality, EMTP applications in Power Systems, Relay Coordination, Application of Power Electronics to Power Quality Improvement and Industrial Drives, DSP controlled Drives, Simulation of Power Electronic Converters and Drives Systems and Control of Special Machines<br />The Department has strong Industry interaction and has been involved in constantly handling various consultancy projects for various Industries and Government of Andhra Pradesh. Department has an MOU with Central Power Research Institute(CPRI) to carry out the collaborative projects.</p>', '<p><strong>Laboratories:</strong></p>\r\n<p><br />The department is backed up by highly efficient Laboratories encompassing the following practical domains:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Electrical Machines Lab.</li>\r\n<li>Electrical Measurements Lab.</li>\r\n<li>Control Systems Lab.</li>\r\n<li>Design and Simulation Lab.</li>\r\n<li>Power Systems Lab.</li>\r\n<li>Power Electronic &amp; Drives Lab.</li>\r\n<li>Electrical Circuits Lab.</li>\r\n<li>Microprocessors Lab.</li>\r\n<li>High Voltage Lab.</li>\r\n</ul>', '<p><strong>R&amp;D Projects</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Reliability Enhancement of AC adjustable Speed Drives, MHRD, New Delhi.</li>\r\n<li>Integrated Operation of Modern Power Systems with Controllable Elements, MHRD, New-Delhi.</li>\r\n<li>Implementation of Efficient Switching Algorithms with Digital Signal Processor for Multi-Level Inverter</li>\r\n<li>Configuration with open end winding Induction Motor, MHRD, New Delhi.</li>\r\n<li>Development of Efficient models for frequency related Availability Tariffs in Deregulated environment, MHRD, New Delhi.</li>\r\n<li>Development of low Voltage High Current Power Supply ,MHRD, New Delhi</li>\r\n<li>Intelligent Transmission Management in Power System Deregulated</li>\r\n<li>Environment Sponsored By Institution Of Engineers</li>\r\n</ul>', '', '', '<p><strong>Consultancy Works:</strong></p>\r\n<p><br />The Department is engaged in and has successfully completed consultancy projects of design vetting of electro-mechanical designs of Lift Irrigation projects undertaken by I&amp;CAD, Govt. of AP to the tune of about INR 4 crore.</p>', 'branchreview/see_branch_review.php?id=102', 'NIT9 Warangal Electrical Engineering EE99 '),
(103, 'branchreview/img/branch_info103.jpeg', '', 'NIT WARANGAL', ' Electronics And Communication Engineering', '<p>The Department of Electronics and Communication Engineering is one of the country&rsquo;s larger ECE departments among all NITs in India and one of the largest departments of the National Institute of Technology, Warangal (NITW). The ECE Department at NITW has been an international reputation of excellence in teaching, research and service. With excellent laboratory facilities and dedicated faculty, the department of ECE offers broad range of programs that include undergraduate(B.Tech) and post graduate (M.Tech) in Electronics Instrumentation, VLSI System design, Communication Systems and research (Ph.D) programs. Some of the recent sponsored project undertaken by the department includes Radar Emitter Identification using Neural Networks sponsored by DLRL, Hyderabad and Special Manpower Development in VLSI sponsored by MIT-Govt. of India.</p>', '<p><strong>Laboratories:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>ELECTRONIC INSTRUMENTATION LAB</li>\r\n<li>COMMUNICATION LABS</li>\r\n<li>ANALOG &amp; DIGITAL CIRCUIT LABS</li>\r\n<li>VLSI DESIGN LABS</li>\r\n</ul>', '<p><strong>R&amp;D Projects</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>O-QPSK Modulator &amp; Demodulator design and its performance analysis for IEEE 802.15.4 Personal Area Networks. </li>\r\n<li>Design of 14 bit 4 channel ADC with high voltage analog input.</li>\r\n</ul>', '', '', '<p><strong>Consultancy Works:</strong></p>\r\n<p><br />The Department is engaged in and has successfully completed consultancy projects of design vetting of electro-mechanical designs of Lift Irrigation projects undertaken by I&amp;CAD, Govt. of AP to the tune of about INR 4 crore.</p>', 'branchreview/see_branch_review.php?id=103', 'NIT9 Warangal Electronics And9 Communication Engineering ECE9'),
(104, 'branchreview/img/branch_info104.jpeg', 'img/branch_info_b104.jpeg', 'NIT Warangal', 'Mechanical Engineering', '<p>Global knowledge hub in mechanical engineering education, research, entrepreneurship and industry outreach services.Impart quality education and training to nurture globally competitive mechanical engineers.Provide vital state-of-the-art research facilities to create, interpret, apply and disseminate knowledge.Develop linkages with world class educational institutions and R&amp;D organizations for excellence in teaching, research and consultancy services.</p>', '<p><strong>Labs:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Metal Cutting and Metal-Matrix Composites</li>\r\n<li>Engineering Design</li>\r\n<li>I.C. Engines</li>\r\n<li>Thermal Systems</li>\r\n<li>Materials &amp; Processing</li>\r\n<li>Metrology</li>\r\n<li>Mechatronics</li>\r\n<li>Industrial Engg. &amp; Mgt.</li>\r\n<li>CAD</li>\r\n<li>Optimization</li>\r\n<li>Robotics</li>\r\n<li>Dynamics and Vibrations</li>\r\n<li>Tribology</li>\r\n</ul>', '<p><strong>R &amp; D Projects</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Investigation on Error Identification and Mitigation in Bio-rapid Prototyping for Oral and Maxillofacial Surgery</li>\r\n<li>Investigations on heat transfer augmentation in a rectangular thermosyphon loop by using nanofluids: mini to large scale study</li>\r\n<li>Experimental Studies On Electronic Cooling Systems Using Newtonian And Non-Newtonian Nanofluids </li>\r\n<li>A novel frost free Refrigerator </li>\r\n<li>Design Optimization through Isogeometric Analysis</li>\r\n<li>Modeling studies on the Hot Deformation and Densification Behaviour of sintered Al-TiB2 composites and its Tribological Characterization</li>\r\n</ul>', '', '', '<p><strong>Ongoing Consultancy Works:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Improvement of Mechanical Properties of Dissimilar Welds of Maraging Steel and AISI 4130 Steel Using various Welding Processes for LRSAM Project </li>\r\n<li>Vetting the designs of Godavari lift irrigation projects</li>\r\n<li>Feasibilty of Compressed Biogas as alternate fuel in diesel engines</li>\r\n</ul>', 'branchreview/see_branch_review.php?id=104', 'NIT9 Warangal Mech Mechanical Engineering '),
(105, 'branchreview/img/branch_info105.jpeg', 'img/branch_info_b105.jpeg', 'NIT Warangal', 'Chemical Engineering ', '<p>The department of Chemical Engineering offers B.Tech., M.Tech. and Ph.D programmes. The department has well qualified faculty dedicated to teaching and doing research in fundamental and advanced areas. The department houses various laboratories catering to the needs of the curriculum. The faculty are actively engaged in industrial consultancy and sponsored research projects. The department has inked MoUs with some of the leading industries. The graduating students are absorbed into reputed firms through campus placements. The department aims at inculcating lifelong learning skills in the students. The alumni of the department are shouldering high positions in multifarious organizations.<br />The B.Tech. programme in Chemical Engineering has been accredited for 5 years by National Board of Accreditation (NBA) with effect from June 2015.</p>', '<p><strong>Laboratories</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Fluid and Particle Mechanics Lab:</li>\r\n<li>Heat Transfer Lab</li>\r\n<li>Chemical Technology Lab</li>\r\n<li>Mass Transfer Lab</li>\r\n<li>Chemical Reaction Engineering Lab:</li>\r\n<li>Instrumentation &amp; Process Control Lab</li>\r\n<li>Simulation &amp; Data Processing Lab</li>\r\n</ul>', '<p><strong>Research Areas</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Modeling, Simulation, Design &amp; Optimization of Chemical Processes</li>\r\n<li>Fluidized Bed Combustion</li>\r\n<li>Waste Water Treatment</li>\r\n<li>Fluidized Bed Drying</li>\r\n<li>Bubbling Fluidized Bed</li>\r\n<li>Circulating Fluidized Bed</li>\r\n<li>Heat Exchanger Network Synthesis</li>\r\n<li>Fuzzy Logic Controllers</li>\r\n<li>Computational Fluid Dynamics</li>\r\n<li>Biochemical Engineering</li>\r\n<li>ASPENPLUS Simulation of Process Plants</li>\r\n<li>Reactive Distillation</li>\r\n</ul>', '', '', '', 'branchreview/see_branch_review.php?id=105', 'NIT9 Warangal Chem Chemical Engineering '),
(106, 'branchreview/img/branch_info106.jpeg', 'img/branch_info_b106.jpeg', 'NIT Warangal', 'Computer Science & Engineering', '<p>The Department of Computer Science &amp; Engineering was established in the year 1990. The department offers high quality undergraduate, postgraduate and doctoral programs. The department has distinguished and committed faculty.<br />The Department has close rapport with prestigious companies such as Microsoft, Tata Consultancy Services, Infosys, EM Corporation, Tata Research Design and Development Centre &ndash; Pune, SUN Microsystems, Accenture, C-DAC, and IBM-Bangalore. Four of the Professors from department were invited to participate in Microsoft Research Faculty Summit at Seattle, Redmond, USA under Microsoft University Relationship Program during 2002-2006. As a part of Microsoft University Relations Programme, the department has received 50,000 USD for R&amp;D works and laboratory development during years 2002 to 2006.</p>\r\n<p>In addition to teaching, faculty of this department were executed several research, software development, content development and consultancy oriented projects. Currently department faculty are guiding doctoral students in Distributed Systems, Parallel Processing, Model driven framework for automated software generation, Databases, Data Mining, Intrusion Detection, Information Security, Bio-informatics, Cryptography, Cryptanalysis, Social networks, Sentiment Analysis, Secure Multi-party Computations, Neural Networks and Soft Computing, Machine Learning, Software Engineering and their allied areas.</p>', '<p><strong>Labs:</strong><br />The Department of Computer Science has the following labs:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Software Engineering Lab</li>\r\n<li>Wireless Security Lab</li>\r\n<li>Computing Lab</li>\r\n<li>Solaris (OSDL) Lab</li>\r\n<li>Data Engineering Lab</li>\r\n</ul>', '<p><strong>Areas Of Research</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Bio-Informatics</li>\r\n<li>Computer Networks</li>\r\n<li>Cryptanalysis</li>\r\n<li>Database Technologies Data Mining / IDS</li>\r\n<li>Distributed Systems</li>\r\n<li>Information Security</li>\r\n<li>Machine Learning</li>\r\n<li>Model driven framework for automated software generation in Distributed Systems environment</li>\r\n<li>Neural Networks and Soft Computing</li>\r\n<li>Parallel Processing</li>\r\n<li>Rough and Fuzzy systems</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '', '', '', 'branchreview/see_branch_review.php?id=106', 'NIT9 Warangal Computer Science Engineering CS99 CSE9 Computers');
