(61, 'West Bengal Joint Entrance Examinations Board announces WBJEE 2016 Result on June 5', 'West Bengal Joint Entrance Examinations Board (WBJEEB) has announced the WBJEE 2016 Result on June 5 for candidates who, appeared in the entrance exam conducted on May 17. WBJEE 2016 Result consists of score obtained by the candidates in the West Bengal Joint Entrance Examination (WBJEE) 2016. The entrance exam was held for providing admissions to various undergraduate engineering courses across the state colleges.<br><br><div>How to check WBJEE 2016 Result:</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>Candidates can check the WBJEE 2016 Result by following these simple steps-</div><div>Enter roll number/application number and date of birth.</div><div>Enter security pin (as displayed on screen).</div><div>Click on Submit button.<br><br>WBJEE 2016 Counselling will be held in the months of June and July tentatively. To participate in the counselling procedure, qualified candidates have to register themselves online. After applying online for counselling, candidates have to pay the fees and proceed to fill their choices for branch and institute preference.</div>', 'news/img/news61.jpeg', 'img/news_b61.jpeg', 'news/php/article.php?id=61', 'WBJEE WBJEEB West Bengal Joint Entrance Examinations Board West Bengal Joint Entrance Examinations WBJEE 2016'),
(62, 'Gateway Institute of Engineering &amp; Technology announces B.Tech admissions 2016', '<div>Gateway Institute of Engineering &amp; Technology (GIET) has invited applications for admissions to undergraduate engineering programmes available at the institute. &nbsp;Application forms for admission to B.E/B.Tech admissions are available now. Aspiring candidates can fill up the application form till August 15, 2016. Interested candidates have to pay Rs. 500 as application fee.&nbsp;<br><br><div>Eligibility criteria:</div><div>Aspirants, who wish to seek admission in B.E/B.Tech programmes at Gateway Institute of Engineering &amp; Technology will be required to have passed in 10+2 examination with 45 per cent marks from a recognized board/university with Physics and Mathematics as compulsory subjects along with one or more of these subjects as optional subjects - Chemistry, Biotechnology, Computer Science, Biology for the courses offered by this college, Physics and Mathematics along with Chemistry/Computer Science.</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>Admission procedure:</div><div>Candidates will be offered admissions to B.E./B.Tech courses as per the regulations of Director Technical Education, Haryana and affiliating DCRUST, Murthal.</div><div>75 per cent seats in each branch will be filled by the Haryana State Counseling Society through counseling</div><div>25 per cent seats in each branch along with other left over seats, which may not be filled through counseling, will be filled up by the college at college level</div><div>Foreign students/NRIs are eligible to get the admission but strictly as per the guidelines/terms stipulated by the State Govt. and Affiliating University.</div><div>B.Tech programmes offered by GIET:</div><div>B.Tech Programme</div><div>Seat intake</div><div>Computer Science</div><div>60</div><div>Electronics and Communication</div><div>60</div><div>Mechanical Engineering</div><div>60</div><div>Civil Engineering</div><div>60</div><div>Fee Structure for 2016-17:</div><div>B. Tech programme (Semester-wise)</div><div>Fee structure</div><div>B.Tech (1st semester)</div><div>Rs.43,500</div><div>B.Tech (2nd semester)</div><div>Rs.34,500</div><div>B.Tech (3rd semester)</div><div>Rs.43,500</div><div>B.Tech (4th semester)</div><div>Rs.34,500</div><div>B.Tech (5th semester)</div><div>Rs.43,500</div><div>B.Tech (6th semester)</div><div>Rs.34,500</div><div>B.Tech (7th semester)</div><div>Rs.43,500</div><div>B.Tech (8th semester)</div><div>Rs.34,500</div><div>Contact details:</div><div>Sonipat Campus, Gateway Campus, Sector 11,</div><div>Sonipat  131001, Phone: (+91) 96500-66221,</div><div>(+91) 88005-53350</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>Admission Helpline:</div><div>Engineering College: 96500-66221</div></div>', 'news/img/news62.jpeg', 'img/news_b62.jpeg', 'news/php/article.php?id=62', 'Gateway Institute of99 Engineering & Technology (GIET) GIET Gateway Institute of99 Engineering & Technology B.E/B.Tech'),
(66, 'IEC Group of Institutions invites applications for B.Tech admissions 2016', '<b>IEC </b>Group of Institutions invites applications for B.Tech admissions IEC Group of Institutions has invited applications for admission of engineering aspirants to its B.Tech courses. Application form for admission to IEC group of institutions is available online till July 31, 2016. Amount of Rs. 1500 is required to be paid by the candidates as application fee. It is must for every candidate to appear and qualify UPSEE 2016 for admission to the institute. Interested candidates can click on the link below to fill the application form of IEC group of institutions. To check all the important details like eligibility criteria, courses offered and admission procedure, candidates can scroll down.<br><br><div><b>Admissions Procedure</b>:</div><div>Admissions to IEC group of institutions are made strictly in accordance with the Merit List of UPSEE 2016. As per the rules of Uttar Pradesh state government, reservation criteria for various categories will also be applicable for aspirants. Candidates have to refer the application form to check their reservation category.&nbsp;</div><div><b><br></b></div><div><b>State Admission</b></div><div>The institute will accept the admission of candidates through the State Entrance Examination (SEE) conducted by AKTU formerly known as UPTU. Counselling, seat allotment and admission procedure will be conducted on the basis of rank/scores obtained by candidates in UPSEE 2016.</div><div><b>&nbsp;</b></div><div><b>Management Quota</b></div><div>Admission to management quota seats will be conducted as per the merit and eligibility criteria decided by the Admission Committee at Greater Noida campus.</div><div><b>&nbsp;</b></div><div><b>Direct Admission (Admission in Second Year)</b></div><div>Candidate who have passed 3 year Diploma (with a minimum of 50% marks) recognized by the U.P. Board of Technical Education in any branch of Engineering except Agriculture Engineering are eligible for direct admission to 2nd year to B.Tech programmes. For direct admissions, candidates must have passed their Diploma with a minimum of 50% marks and their domicile must be of Uttar Pradesh only.</div><div><b>&nbsp;</b></div><div><b>Eligibility Criteria:</b></div><div>For admission to IEC Group of Institutions, candidates must have passed their 10+2 or equivalent exam with minimum 50% marks.</div><div>Candidates must also have appeared and qualified UPSEE 2016 conducted by AKTU, Lucknow.<br><br><p style=\\"margin-bottom: 0px; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px; font-family: Georgia, \\''Times New Roman\\'', Times, serif;\\"><b>Important Dates:</b></p><div class=\\"table-responsive\\" style=\\"font-family: Georgia, \\''Times New Roman\\'', Times, serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 24px;\\"><table class=\\"table\\" style=\\"margin-top: 1.5em; margin-bottom: 1.5em; padding: 5px; border: 1px solid rgb(204, 204, 204); vertical-align: top;\\"><tbody><tr><td valign=\\"top\\" style=\\"padding: 5px; border-right-width: 1px; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-left-width: 1px; border-right-style: solid; border-bottom-style: solid; border-left-style: solid; border-color: rgb(204, 204, 204);\\"><p align=\\"center\\" style=\\"margin-bottom: 0px; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px;\\"><span style=\\"font-weight: 600;\\">Event</span></p></td><td valign=\\"top\\" style=\\"padding: 5px; border-right-width: 1px; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-left-width: 1px; border-right-style: solid; border-bottom-style: solid; border-left-style: solid; border-color: rgb(204, 204, 204);\\"><p align=\\"center\\" style=\\"margin-bottom: 0px; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px;\\"><span style=\\"font-weight: 600;\\">Date</span></p></td></tr><tr><td valign=\\"top\\" style=\\"padding: 5px; border-right-width: 1px; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-left-width: 1px; border-right-style: solid; border-bottom-style: solid; border-left-style: solid; border-color: rgb(204, 204, 204