(67, 'SITM invites applications for B.Tech admissions 2016', '<div>Sarvottam Institute of Technology and Management (SITM) has invited applications for admission to its B.Tech courses through UPSEE 2016. For admission to undergraduate engineering courses available at the institute, it is must for candidates to qualify UPSEE 2016. &nbsp;Amount of Rs. 500 will be required to be paid by candidates as application fee. Candidates aspiring for admission to Sarvottam Institute of Technology and Management can go through the other important details of SITM B.Tech Admission 2016 below.</div><div><br></div><div><b>Application/Registration Procedure:<br><br></b></div><div>1. Registration</div><div>Application/Registration forms are to be filled-in and submitted to the registrar of SITM.</div><div>Incomplete registration forms or forms without photographs will not be accepted.</div><div>Dates for Test/Interview/Interaction will be given at the time of registration.</div><div>Duly self-attested photocopies of marks sheets of Class 10th and class 12th must be enclosed with the registration form.<br><br></div><div>2. Admission Procedure</div><div>85% of total seats of B.Tech courses will be filled through Counseling of UPSEE 2016.</div><div>Reservation for the candidates of various categories will be implemented as per the directives of UP Government.</div><div>Admission to rest 15 % of total seats will be done through management quota. Candidates seeking admission through management quota seats will be required to appear in a written examination after submitting registration form.</div><div>Result of qualified candidates will be displayed on the notice board of the institute on the specified date.<br><br></div><div><b>Eligibility for admission to B.Tech:</b></div><div><br>1. Candidates must have passed their 10+2 or equivalent exam with Physics and Mathematics as compulsory subjects and anyone of the following subjects:</div><div>Course</div><div>Compulsory Subject</div><div>Anyone of the following subjects</div><div>B.Tech</div><div>Physics &amp; Mathematics</div><div>Chemistry/Bio-Technology/Biology/Technical Vocational subject<br><br></div><div>2. For admission in first year of B.Tech, candidate must have passed their 10+2 or equivalent exam from any recognized Board/University with a minimum of 50% marks (45% marks for SC/ST Category candidates).<br><br></div><div>3. It is also mandatory for every candidate to pass in every subject of their class 12th.</div><div><br></div>', 'news/img/news67.jpeg', 'img/news_b67.jpeg', 'news/php/article.php?id=67', 'Sarvottam Institute of99 Technology and9 Management Sarvottam Institute of99 Technology and9 Management (SITM) SITM UPSEE B.Tech'),
(68, 'WBJEE 2016 counselling to be conducted online from June 15 to July 19', '<b>WBJEE</b> 2016 counselling will be conducted online from <i>June 15 to July 19</i>, for candidates who have qualified in WBJEE 2016 conducted on May 17 for admissions to B. Tech programmes, West Bengal Joint Entrance Examination Board (WBJEEB) Chairman Sajal Dasgupta was quoted declaring the counselling date. As per media reports, WBJEEB has given ranking to every examinee of WBJEE 2016 this year. Thus, every candidate, who had appeared for the state level engineering entrance examination, will be given rank cards. The reports also reflect that every examinee who has taken the state level entrance test, will be eligible for WBJEE 2016 counselling this year.<br><br><div>WBJEE 2016 result has been announced on <b>June 5</b>, for candidates who had appeared in the entrance exam on May 17. Among the top 10 rankers of WBJEE 2016, the top 4 slots have been clinched by candidates from Kolkata. The top 3 rankers of WBJEE 2016 are Yashwardhan Didwani (Rank 1 - from Salt Lake), followed by Abhishek Dutta (from Nadia) and Arpan Konar (from Bardhaman) who secured the second and the third position respectively. Among girl candidates, Piyali Manna from Salt Lake bagged rank 91, thereby becoming the topper among female candidates. As per the exam conducting body, the merit list of WBJEE 2016 was dominated by students from CBSE and ISC boards.</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>For admission year 2016-17, approximately 1.27 lakh candidates had registered for WBJEE engineering exam, out of which 21.16 per cent were female candidates. As per a national daily, as many as 1,01,954 examinees will be getting rank cards. As per rough estimates, around 36,263 seats are available across 103 engineering colleges in the state.</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>WBJEE 2016 was conducted on May 17 for admissions to various undergraduate engineering programmes across 103 institutes/colleges of the state.<br><br></div>', 'news/img/news68.jpeg', 'img/news_b68.jpeg', 'news/php/article.php?id=68', 'West Bengal Joint Entrance Examination Board (WBJEEB) West Bengal Joint Entrance Examination Board WBJEEB WBJEE West Bengal Joint Entrance Examination Board'),
(81, 'GNA University announces B.Tech Admissions 2016', '<span style=\\"font-family: Georgia, \\''Times New Roman\\'', Times, serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px;\\">GNA University has announced B.Tech admissions. For admissions to undergraduate engineering courses of the University, candidates can fill the application form online. There is no entrance for admission to the graduate level engineering courses available at the University. The university will consider the score of class 12</span><span style=\\"font-size: 12px; line-height: 0; position: relative; vertical-align: baseline; top: -0.5em; font-family: Georgia, \\''Times New Roman\\'', Times, serif;\\">th</span><span style=\\"font-family: Georgia, \\''Times New Roman\\'', Times, serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px;\\">&nbsp;or equivalent examination for admission in B.Tech courses. Candidates aspiring for admission to B.Tech programmes of GNA University can check all the important details below.<br><b><br></b></span><p style=\\"margin-bottom: 0px; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px; font-family: Georgia, \\''Times New Roman\\'', Times, serif;\\"><b>Eligibility Criteria</b><span style=\\"font-weight: 600;\\">:</span></p><ul style=\\"margin: 1em 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 20px; font-family: Georgia, \\''Times New Roman\\'', Times, serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 24px;\\"><li><p style=\\"margin-bottom: 0px; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px;\\">Candidate must be an Indian national.</p></li><li><p style=\\"margin-bottom: 0px; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px;\\">All aspirants must have passed their 10+2 or equivalent examination from a recognized board/University with a minimum of 50% marks.</p></li></ul><p style=\\"margin-bottom: 0px; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px; font-family: Georgia, \\''Times New Roman\\'', Times, serif;\\"><b>Application Form</b><span style=\\"font-weight: 600;\\">:</span></p><p style=\\"margin-bottom: 0px; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px; font-family: Georgia, \\''Times New Roman\\'', Times, serif;\\"><span style=\\"font-weight: 600;\\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\\"margin-bottom: 0px; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px; font-family: Georgia, \\''Times New Roman\\'', Times, serif;\\">Application form for admission to GNA University can be filled online only. For filling the application form, candidates can click on the link given below. After clicking on the link, a new page will appear where candidates are required to fill their personal details, qualification details and programme they are interested in. Candidates can pay the application fee at the end of the application form.<br><b><br></b></p><p style=\\"margin-bottom: 0px; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px; font-family: Georgia, \\''Times New Roman\\'', Times, serif;\\"><b>Important Dates</b><span style=\\"font-weight: 600;\\">:</span></p><p style=\\"margin-bottom: 0px; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px; font-family: Georgia, \\''Times New Roman\\'', Times, serif;\\"><span style=\\"font-weight: 600;\\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\\"margin-bottom: 0px; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px; font-family: Georgia, \\''Times New Roman\\'', Times, serif;\\">Date of Notification  <i>May 23, 2016</i></p><p style=\\"margin-bottom: 0px; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px; font-family: Georgia, \\''Times New Roman\\'', Times, serif;\\">Result <i> June, 2016</i></p><p style=\\"margin-bottom: 0px; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px; font-family: Georgia, \\''Times New Roman\\'', Times, serif;\\">Counseling  July, 2016</p>', 'news/img/news69.jpeg', 'img/news_b69.jpeg', 'news/php/article.php?id=81', 'GNA9 University GNA9 B.Tech '),
(82, 'Assam CEE 2016 result announced on June 8', 'Dibrugarh University has declared Assam CEE 2016 result on <b>June 8</b>, for examinees who had taken the engineering entrance exam on May 14 and 15. Assam CEE 2016 result is available online. For checking their Assam CEE result 2016, the candidates have to enter their Assam CEE 2016 roll number and click on the submit button on the result page. Examinees can click here to check their result of Assam CEE 2016. Admissions to various B.Tech/B.E. programmes available across the state engineering colleges, will be given based on Assam CEE 2016 result.<br><br><div>Counselling for the qualifying candidates will tentatively be conducted in the third week of July. Eligible candidates will be required to submit Assam CEE 2016 Counselling Form (Form-B) for BE/B.Tech courses at the time of counselling. The candidates appearing for counselling of Assam CEE 2016 should also produce all the required documents during the counselling process. If the candidates fail to produce the required documents, they shall be disqualified.</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>Each paper of Assam CEE 2016 was of 2 hours duration with a total of 100 multiple choice questions in each paper which carried 1 mark each. For any wrong answer, there was no negative marking, while for more than one answer options marked, no mark was awarded.</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>Assam CEE is a state level engineering entrance exam conducted every year for admissions to B.Tech/B.E. programmes available across the state engineering colleges.&nbsp;</div>', 'news/img/news82.jpeg', 'img/news_b82.jpeg', 'news/php/article.php?id=82', 'CEE9 Assam CEE9 Assam Common Entrance Examination (Assam CEE) Assam Common Entrance Examination '),
(83, 'CMR College of Engineering and Technology announces B.Tech admissions 2016', 'CMR College of Engineering and Technology (CMRCET) has announced the admissions to its B.Tech programmes. Admission to undergraduate engineering courses of the institute will be conducted on the basis of candidates score/rank in TS EAMCET 2016. It is must for every aspirant to appear and qualify TS EAMCET 2016 for admission to CMRCET. &nbsp;As per their rank in the entrance exam, candidates have to appear in TS EAMCET 2016 counselling for admission to the institute. Interested candidates can check all the important details like eligibility criteria, courses offered and admission procedure below on this page.<br><br><div><b>Admissions Procedure:</b></div><div>To step in four-year undergraduate degree course in engineering, a student must qualify Telangana State Engineering, Agricultural Sciences and Medical Common Entrance Test (TS EAMCET). The state level entrance test is conducted by the Government of Telangana. Only those students who had qualified TS EAMCET will be admitted to the institute strictly on merit bases.</div><div><br></div><div>Candidates marks in their qualifying exam (10+2 or equivalent) and in TS EAMCET 2016 will be considered for allotment of seat in CMRCET. Students will also be admitted through Management and NRI Quota. For the aforementioned quota, candidates must possess first class in three subjects: Physics, Chemistry and Mathematics.</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div><b>Eligibility Criteria:</b></div><div>Candidates must be citizen of India.</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>For admission, aspirants must have passed their 10+2 or equivalent exam from Board of Intermediate, Government of Andhra Pradesh or from any recognized board/University of India.</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>It is also mandatory that all aspiring candidates must have studied Mathematics, Physics and Chemistry as compulsory subjects in their 10+2 or equivalent exam.</div><div><br></div>', 'news/img/news83.jpeg', 'img/news_b83.jpeg', 'news/php/article.php?id=83', 'CMR9 College of99 Engineering and9 Technology (CMRCET) CMR9 CMR9 College of99 Engineering and9 Technology CMRCET TS99 EAMCET B.Tech'),
(84, 'IIT lectures to go live through 32 Direct-to-Home channels', '<div>Lectures happening at 6 Indian Institutes of Technology (IITs) and some other top engineering institutes will soon go live through 32 Direct-to-Home channels, a national daily quoted Ministry of Human Resource Development (MHRD) officials. According to the media report, students at IIT Chennai, IIT Mumbai, IIT Delhi, IIT Kharagpur, IIT Kanpur and IIT Guwahati and some other top engineering colleges will soon be able see the live telecast of what is being taught in the classroom, while sitting in their living rooms. However, names of the other premiere engineering colleges have not been finalized yet.</div><div><br></div><div>To make this service accessible to students at these engineering institutes, MHRD has launched 32 Direct-to-Home channels. These channels are expected to go live by August 2016. The ministry has also joined hands with the Department of Space where the latter has given its consent to allot two transponders on a GSAT series satellite for this project.</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>Several other institutes will also play a vital role in the project by providing content and lessons, for which the MHRD has signed MoUs with these institutions.</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>\\"The government is focusing on using space technology to expand the reach of high quality education. Through the 32 DTH channels the aim is to ensure that live classrooms can be transmitted from ten \\''Teaching Ends\\'' out of which six will be IITs located in Chennai, Mumbai, Delhi, Kharagpur, Kanpur and Guwahati,\\" a senior MHRD official said.</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>The report also reflected that these 32 channels will be accessible for students without any charges over Doordarshan\\''s Free Dish DTH platform. But to watch the live lectures, the students will be required to install a Set Top Box.</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>This move by MHRD comes after a meeting last month where a committee chaired by IIT Gandhinagar Director worked out the finer details of operationalizing this ambitious project.</div>', 'news/img/news84.jpeg', 'img/news_b84.jpeg', 'news/php/article.php?id=84', 'IIT9 IITs Indian Institutes of99 Technology 3299 Direct-to-Home channels top9 engineering institutes Lectures'),
(91, '<p>Madhya Pradesh Engineering Admissions (MP B.E Admission)</p>', '<p>Madhya Pradesh Professional Examination Board (MPPEB) has begun MP BE Admissions 2016 counselling from June 15, for admission to B.E. programmes available across the state engineering colleges. MPPEB is conducting counselling for General Pool and T.F.W. (Based on JEE Main 2016) from June 15 to July 11 (3 pm), while counselling for MP BE Admissions 2016 based on qualifying exam will be conducted from July 12 to 30 (5 pm). For NRI seats, the process of counselling is being held from June 6 to 22 (11.30 pm). The counselling process of MP BE Admissions 2016 include document verification, login for choice filling, common merit list, allotment of letters and reporting at the institute.<br /><br />All candidates have to first register themselves to be able to participate in MP BE Admissions 2016 counselling procedure. Candidates participating through qualifying exam, will receive Roll no, using which he/she will be able to complete the counselling process.<br /><br /></p>\r\n<p>For counselling based on JEE Main 2016, the candidates have to enter JEE Main roll number and date of birth for registration. Candidates must ensure that all required information is correct in all the fields. After the registration process is complete, they have to take registration receipt.</p>\r\n<p>Seat allotment and first round of seat upgradation will take place from July 14 to July 23 (5 pm), whereas the board will conduct second round of seat allotment from July 20 to 30 (5 pm).</p>\r\n<p>Candidates, who wish to opt for internal branch change, can do so from August 1 to August 2 (5 pm). After opting for internal branch change, the candidates have to print their allotment letter, which they can do till 2 pm on August 4, 2016.<br /><br /></p>\r\n<p>Madhya Pradesh Professional Examination Board offers admissions to undergraduate engineering programmes across the colleges of the state through JEE Main or based on qualifying exam.&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'news/img/news91.jpeg', 'img/news_b91.jpeg', 'news/php/article.php?id=91', 'MP99 madhya pradesh engineering colleges COLLEGE admission counselling BE99 B Tech B.99 Tech'),
(92, '<p>KRMU announces B.Tech Admissions 2016</p>', '<p>K R Mangalam University (KRMU) has announced B.Tech admissions for 2016-17 session. Candidates have to fill the form online only for admission to the University. Application forms of the University are available now and the last date to fill the application form in is June 30, 2016. KRMU will consider the scores of candidates in JEE Main 2016 or in UPSEE 2016 for admission to B.tech courses available at the institute. It is must for all the students aspiring admission in KRMU to appear in the aforementioned exams. Interested candidates can check all the details related to KR Mangalam University B.Tech admissions below on this page.<br /> <br /><strong>Eligibility Criteria:</strong><br />Candidate must be an Indian national.<br />All aspirants must have passed their 10+2 or equivalent examination from a recognized board/University with a minimum of 50% marks.<br /><br /><strong>Application Form:</strong><br /> <br />Aspirants have following options to fill the application form for admission to KRM University:<br /> <br /><strong>Online</strong>: Application form can be filled online by the aspiring candidates. They also have to upload their 1oth or equivalent marks sheet and scanned passport sixe coloured photograph. To fill the application form, candidates can click on the link given below.<br /><br /><strong>Download Application Form:</strong><br />Application form can also be downloaded from the link given above, but before downloading the application form, candidates have to fill all the details. After downloading the filled in application form, print out of it must be taken by the candidates. After affixing a recent color passport size photograph and enclosing photocopy of class 10th mark sheet, application form must be submitted at the respective campus candidates are applying to.<br /> <br /><strong>Offline:</strong><br /> <br />Application form and admission prospectus for B.Tech 2016 admissions to KRMU can be obtained from the admission office of the University and from the city office of the University. Address for both the offices is given below:<br /> <br />Admission office,<br />K R Mangalam University Campus,<br />Sohna Road,<br />Gurgaon &ndash; 122103<br />City Office:<br />K.R. Mangalam Institute,<br />N - Block,<br />Greater Kailash - 1,<br />New Delhi- 110048<br /> <br /><strong>Programme Profile:</strong><br /> <br />K R Mangalam University offers B.Tech Programmes in the following disciplines:<br />Computer Science &amp; Engineering<br />Mechanical Engineering<br />Electrical and Electronics Engineering<br />Electronics and Communication Engineering<br />Civil Engineering<br />Important Dates:<br /> <br /><strong>Last Date</strong> to fill application form &ndash; June 30, 2016<br /><br /><strong>Fee Structure:</strong></p>\r\n<table border=\\"2\\" cellpadding=\\"4\\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>Course</strong></td>\r\n<td><strong>Duration</strong></td>\r\n<td><strong>Total Fee</strong></td>\r\n<td><strong>Semester I</strong></td>\r\n<td><strong>Semester II</strong></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>B.Tech (CSE, ECE, EEE, ME, CE)</td>\r\n<td>4 Years</td>\r\n<td>175000</td>\r\n<td>90000</td>\r\n<td>85000</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>BCA - Bachelor of Computer Application</td>\r\n<td>3 Years</td>\r\n<td>135000</td>\r\n<td><br />70000</td>\r\n<td>65000</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>', 'news/img/news92.png', 'img/news_b92.jpeg', 'news/php/article.php?id=92', 'KRMU K R Mangalam University engineering colleges admissions B.99 Tech B.Tech B Tech btech b tech be99 BE99 B.E. engineering private college delhi new9 delhi'),
(95, 'JoSAA : All you need to know about.', '<div class="container white_bg">\r\n<div class="col-md-9 col-sm-8 col-xs-12">\r\n<div>\r\n<p>The&nbsp;<strong>Joint Seat Allocation Authority (JoSAA) 2016</strong>&nbsp;has been set up by the Ministry of Human Resources Development (MHRD) to manage and regulate the joint seat allocation for admissions to 92 institutes for the academic year 2016-17. This includes 22 IITs, ISM, 31 NITs, 20 IIITs and 18 Other-Government Funded Technical Institutes (Other-GFTIs). Admission to all the academic programs offered by these Institutes will be made through a single platform.<br /><br /><strong>All the candidates</strong>&nbsp;who appeared for<strong>&nbsp;</strong><strong>JEE (Main) 2016 / JEE (Advanced) 2016 should take note of the following important points:</strong><br /><br /></p>\r\n<strong>Registration</strong>:\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\nAll candidates who have appeared in&nbsp;<strong>JEE (Main) 2016</strong>&nbsp;are eligible to register for seat allocation in NIT+ system (except IITs &amp; ISM).\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\nAll candidates who have declared qualified in&nbsp;<strong>JEE (Adv) 2016</strong>&nbsp;are eligible to register for seat allocation in all participating Institutes.\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<strong>Filling-in of choices</strong>: Candidates may fill-in their choices of Institutes and branches in decreasing order of their preference. Candidates are strongly urged to fill-in as many choices as possible.\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<strong>Locking of choices: </strong>Candidates MUST &ldquo;lock&rdquo; their choices. For candidates who do NOT lock their choices, their last saved choices will be locked automatically when the time-window for filling-in of choices closes.\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<strong>Number of rounds of seat allocation: </strong>JoSAA will conduct&nbsp;four rounds that is 1st through 4th rounds&nbsp;of seat allocation for academic programs offered by Institutes under JoSAA 2016.\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<strong>Seat acceptance:&nbsp;</strong>Candidates allotted a seat must pay the seat acceptance fee (through e-Challan/SBI NetBanking) and get the documents verified at any reporting center (josaa.nic.in) for provisional seat acceptance .\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<strong>Participation in subsequent rounds: </strong>A candidate is required to fill option for &lsquo;freeze&rsquo;, &lsquo;slide&rsquo; or &lsquo;float&rsquo; the choice of academic program.\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<strong>Dual Reporting: </strong>If in a subsequent round, a candidate&rsquo;s allotment from NIT+ system changes to an IIT/ ISM, the candidate MUST report ONCE AGAIN at an IIT reporting centre, similarly if a candidate&rsquo;s allotment from IIT/ISM changes to an NIT+ system, the candidate MUST report ONCE AGAIN at any NIT+ reporting centre, failure to do so will result in forfeiture of seats allocated in both NIT+ system and IIT/ISM.\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<strong>Withdraw option</strong>: A candidate, who has already accepted a seat, can withdraw the seat by reporting at a reporting center before the fourth round of seat allocation.<br /><br />\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<strong><em><u>Important:&nbsp;</u></em></strong>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<strong>Registration&nbsp;&ndash; </strong>Candidates who do NOT register within the specified time window WILL NOT be able to seek admission for this academic year\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<strong>Filling-in of choices&nbsp;&ndash; </strong>Candidates who do NOT fill-in choices within the specified time window WILL NOT be able to seek admission for this academic year\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<strong>Dual Reporting: </strong>Two times reporting required in case of seat allotment changes from NIT+s system to IITs/ISM and vice versa.\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n&nbsp;<strong>No modification of locked choices</strong>&nbsp;&ndash; once locked, choices CANNOT be modified.\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>For complete details, please visit http://josaa.nic.in and&nbsp;_MUST&nbsp;_read&nbsp;_BUSINESS RULE.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div id="footer">&nbsp;<br /><br /></div>\r\n<div class="link_box">\r\n<div class="tab">\r\n<h2>Important Links</h2>\r\n</div>\r\n<ul id="ctl00_CurrentEvents_BLinks">\r\n<li><a href="http://josaa.nic.in/webinfocms/Handler/FileHandler.ashx?i=File&amp;ii=68&amp;iii=Y" target="_blank">Seat Allotment Schedule</a></li>\r\n<li><a href="http://josaa.nic.in/webinfocms/Public/View.aspx?page=65" target="_self">Business Rules</a></li>\r\n<li><a href="http://josaa.nic.in/SeatInfo/root/InstituteView.aspx" target="_blank">List of Participating Institutes</a></li>\r\n<li><a href="http://josaa.nic.in/webinfocms/Handler/FileHandler.ashx?i=File&amp;ii=60&amp;iii=Y" target="_blank">List of Reporting Centres</a></li>\r\n<li><a href="http://josaa.nic.in/SeatInfo/root/SeatMatrix.aspx" target="_blank">Seat Availability</a></li>\r\n<li><a href="http://josaa.nic.in/webinfocms/Public/View.aspx?page=64" target="_self">Document Formats<br /></a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<ul id="ctl00_LeftLinks_BLinks" class="nav nav-pills nav-stacked arrow_link altlks">\r\n<li><a href="http://josaa.nic.in/webinfocms/Handler/FileHandler.ashx?i=File&amp;ii=62&amp;iii=Y" target="_blank">Opening and Closing Ranks JoSAA 2015</a></li>\r\n<li><a class="arrow_link2" href="http://www.jeeadv.ac.in/orcr" target="_blank">Opening and Closing Ranks for IITs<br /><br /><br /></a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div class="col-md-9 col-sm-8 col-xs-12">\r\n<h2 class="page_heading">Contact JoSAA</h2>\r\n<div class="history">(Last Update :18/06/2016)</div>\r\n<br />\r\n<div>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: medium;"><strong><span style="font-size: large;">For any query related to IITs and ISM admission, please contact</span><br /> </strong></span>Organizing Chairman, JEE (Advanced) 2016<br /> Indian Institute of Technology Guwahati<br /> Guwahati 781039<br /> Phone: +91 361 2692795<br /> Fax: +91 361 2582180<br /> E-mail: josaa2016@iitg.ac.in</p>\r\nContact details of zonal IITs :- <a href="http://www.jeeadv.ac.in/zonal-iits">Click Here</a><br /> <br /> <span style="font-size: medium;"><strong>For any query related to NITs, IIITs and Other-GFTIs admission, Please Contact<br /> </strong></span>National Institute of Technology Patna<br /> Ashok Rajpath, Patna, Bihar-800 005 <br /> Contact No. : +91 612 2678045<br /> Fax No. : +91 612 2678046 <br /> Email : csaboffice@nitp.ac.in</div>\r\n</div>', 'news/img/news95.png', 'img/news_b95.jpeg', 'news/php/article.php?id=95', 'josaa JoSAA Joint Seat Allocation Authority Joint Seat Allocation Authority 2016 JoSAA 2016 josaa 2016'),
(98, 'Joint Admission Counselling Delhi 2016', '<p>Admission Notice for B.E. / B. Tech. and B. Arch Program 2016-17.</p>\r\n<p>Online applications are invited for admissions to B.E. / B. Tech. and B. Arch Program of following universities/ institutes established by govt. of NCT of Delhi.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Delhi Technological University (formerly DCE)</strong></li>\r\n<li><strong>Indira Gandhi Delhi technical university for women</strong></li>\r\n<li><strong>Indraprastha Institute of information technology, Delhi (IIITD)</strong></li>\r\n<li><strong>Netaji Subhas Institute of technology (NSIT)</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>For detailed procedure about eligibility criteria, Reservation, Admission Procedure,etc please visit the official website: <a href="http://www.jacdelhi.nic.in" target="_blank">www.jacdelhi.nic.in</a></p>\r\n<p><strong>Online Application Process:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Candidates will have to register online at <a href="http://www.jacdelhi.nic.in" target="_blank">www.jacdelhi.nic.in</a> as per the information given on the website.</strong></li>\r\n<li><strong>All candidates are required to pay a non refundable fee of INR1200 either online or with cash using E-challan at any SBI branch.</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>CONTACTS:<br />Email: <a href="mailto:jacdelhi2016@gmail.com">jacdelhi2016@gmail.com</a></strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Phone: 9599384990 to 9599384997 (eight lines)<br /></strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Important Links:Eligibility: <a href="http://jacdelhi.nic.in/publicinfo/Handler/FileHandler.ashx?i=File&amp;ii=7&amp;iii=Y" target="_blank">Click here</a><br />Counselling Schedule: <a href="http://jacdelhi.nic.in/publicinfo/Handler/FileHandler.ashx?i=File&amp;ii=15&amp;iii=Y" target="_blank">Click Here</a><br />Counselling Procedure: <a href="http://jacdelhi.nic.in/publicinfo/Handler/FileHandler.ashx?i=File&amp;ii=13&amp;iii=Y" target="_blank">Click Here</a><br />Seats Distribution: <a href="http://jacdelhi.nic.in/publicinfo/Handler/FileHandler.ashx?i=File&amp;ii=11&amp;iii=Y" target="_blank">Click Here<br /></a>Annual Fee Details: <a href="http://jacdelhi.nic.in/publicinfo/Handler/FileHandler.ashx?i=File&amp;ii=10&amp;iii=Y" target="_blank">Click Here</a><br />Reservation: <a href="http://jacdelhi.nic.in/publicinfo/Handler/FileHandler.ashx?i=File&amp;ii=8&amp;iii=Y" target="_blank">Click Here</a><br /></strong></p>', 'news/img/news98.jpeg', 'img/news_b98.jpeg', 'news/php/article.php?id=98', 'JAC9 DELHI admission NSIT IIIT'),
