(103, 'COMEDK UGET 2016 counselling for Round 1 begins on June 28', '<p>COMEDK UGET 2016 Counselling for first round is being conducted from June 28 to July 12. The first session of COMEDK UGET 2016 counselling for round 1 started at 8.30 am on June 28. For the first round of COMEDK UGET 2016 counselling, there are a total of 7 sessions every day till July 12. The first 6 counselling sessions are conducted based on candidates&rsquo; ranks, whereas the last or the 7th counselling session is for latecomers.<br /><br />COMEDK UGET 2016 counselling is being conducted offline and candidates have to be physically present at &ldquo;Mangala Mantapa, NMKRV College for Women premises, 3rd Block, Jayanagar, Bangalore &ndash; 560 011&rdquo; to participate in the counselling process of COMEDK UGET 2016.<br /> <br />Consortium of Medical Engineering and Dental Colleges of Karnataka Under Graduate Entrance Test (COMEDK UGET) will conduct counselling for the second round tentatively in the fourth week of July 2016. COMEDK UGET conducts counselling for COMEDK UGET 2016 through a Centralized Single Window.<br /> <br />The process of COMED UGET 2016 counselling involves registration, document verification, seat selection and seat allotment along with fee admission in part.<br /> <br />COMEDK UGET &ldquo;Under Graduate Entrance Test&rdquo; is conducted annually by COMEDK and floated by the Associations of Medical, Dental and Engineering private colleges for merit determination of students seeking admission to member institutions.<br /> <br />The exam was conducted on May 8, 2016 in computer based mode across 697 test centers located in 153 cities across the country. Presently, there are 181 engineering colleges in Karnataka that are affiliated to COMEDK and offer admissions to almost 20,000 seats. Against 68,628 candidates, who had applied for the entrance exam in undergraduate engineering programmes, 55,680 (81%) candidates have taken the test on 8th May 2016.<br /><br /></p>\r\n<div 