(109, 'Common counselling for IISERs along with IITs, NITs from 2017', '<p>Indian Institutes of Science Education &amp; Research (IISERs) will offer admissions to eligible candidates through common counselling along with Indian Institutes of technology (IITs) and National Institutes of Technology (NITs) from the academic year 2017-18. According to a national daily, the Ministry of Human Resource Development (MHRD) has given its approval to bring all 7 IISERs under the ambit of common counselling along with the prestigious IITs and NITs from next year onwards, for admissions to 5-year BS-MS Dual degree programmes. Counselling and seat allotment for IITs and NIT+System at present is done by Joint Seat Allocation Authority (JoSAA).</p>\r\n<p>At present, admissions to 5-year BS-MS Dual degree programmes at IISERs are offered based on three channels - through JEE, Kishore Vaigyanik Protshahan Yojna (KVPY) and being in the top 1 per cent students of all school boards. Candidates applying through the aforementioned three channels, have to fill in an application form for admission, which is common for all IISERs and all the three channels of admission. 50 per cent of the seats across all IISERs are filled through KVPY and IIT-JEE (JEE Advanced), while the remaining seats are filled through state and central boards channel based on an aptitude test conducted by IISERs. This aptitude test is conducted for the top 1 per cent students of all school boards.<br /> <br />The decision to conduct common counselling for admission to IISERs from the next academic year was taken in a recent meeting of standing committee of IISERs.<br /> <br />Currently, counselling and seat allotment for admission to IITs, NITs, IIITs and GFTIs is conducted by JoSAA. JoSAA comprises of representatives from JAB and CSAB, which was introduced in the year 2015 for conducting joint seat allotment process for qualifying candidates of JEE for admission to various undergraduate engineering programmes across IITs, ISM Dhanbad, NITs, IIITs and GFTIs.<br /> <br />Earlier, till 2014, seat allocation for JEE Main qualifiers for admissions to NITs, IIITs and GFTIs was conducted by Central Seat Allocation Board (CSAB), while seat allocation for JEE Advanced qualifiers was done by Joint Admission Board (JAB).<br /> <br />There are a total of 1,125 seats across seven IISERs &mdash; IISER Kolkata, IISER Pune, IISER Mohali, IISER Bhopal, IISER Trivandrum, IISER Tirupati and IISER Behrampur. Among the 7 IISERs, Tirupati and Behrampur are the new campuses. </p>', 'news/img/news109.jpeg', 'img/news_b109.jpeg', 'news/php/article.php?id=109', 'iiser josaa 2016 counselling'),
