110.jpeg', 'img/news_b110.jpeg', 'news/php/article.php?id=110', 'iiit iiit-h iiith international institute of99 information technology'),
(111, 'JOSAA 2016 : MOCK SEAT ALLOCATION', '<p>Joint Seat Allocation Authority (JoSAA) has declared the result of mock seat allocation today. It&rsquo;ll help the candidates get an idea about which college they can get as per their currently filled choices.</p>\r\n<p>Students are advised to use this opportunity to modify their choices accordingly so that they can get the best college as per their rank. JoSAA will declare the result of Round 1 of Seat Allocation on June 30th, 2016.</p>\r\n<p>Joint Seat Allocation Authority (JoSAA) consists of representatives from Joint Admission Board (JAB) 2016 representing the IITs and ISM Dhanbad and the Central Seat Allocation Board (CSAB) 2016 representing the NITs, IIITs and other technical institutes funded fully or partly by Central or a State government.<br /><br /><br /></p>', 'news/img/news111.jpeg', 'img/news_b111.jpeg', 'news/php/article.php?id=111', 'josaa iit9 nit9 iits nits 2016 counselling engineering colleges mock'),
(112, 'Graphic Era University invites applications for B.Tech admissions 2016', '<p>Graphic Era University has invited applications for admissions to its B.Tech courses. Application form for admission to the university can be filled till July 31, 2016. Candidates can fill the application form online and can obtain the same in person from the university office after payment of Rs. 1200. Admission of candidates to B.Tech courses of Graphic Era University will be done on the basis of their score in JEE Main 2016 or on the basis of their merit in class 12th. Candidates aspiring for admission to Graphic Era University can check all the related details below.<br /><br /><br /><strong>Eligibility Criteria:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>For Admissions on the basis of JEE Main 2016 score, candidates must have passed their 10+2 or equivalent exam with minimum of 60% aggregate marks.</li>\r\n<li>For Admissions on the basis of 10+2 merit, candidates must have passed their 10+2 or equivalent exam with minimum of 65% aggregate marks.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Application Form:</strong><br /> <br />Aspirants can fill the application form of Graphic Era University in following modes:<br /> <br /><strong>Online:</strong> Application form can be filled and application fee can be paid in online mode by aspiring candidates. After clicking on the link given below, students will be required to fill personal details, contact details, course details and academic details. As the last step of filling the application form, candidate will be required to pay the fee. Application fee can be paid online as well as offline.<br /><br /><strong>Offline:</strong><br />Application form and admission prospectus for B.Tech 2016 admissions to Graphic Era University can be obtained from the University. Address of the University is given below:<br /> <br /><strong>Graphic Era University,</strong><br /><strong>566/6, Bell Road, Clement Town</strong><br /><strong>Dehradun, Uttarakhand</strong><br /><strong>India -248002</strong><br /> <br /><strong>Programme Profile:</strong><br /> <br />Graphic Era University offers B.Tech Programmes in the following disciplines:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Computer Science and Engineering with specialization in Big Data Analytics</li>\r\n<li>Computer Science and Engineering</li>\r\n<li>Computer Science and Engineering with specialization in Cloud Computing</li>\r\n<li>Electronics and Communication Engineering</li>\r\n<li>Electronics and Communication Engineering with specialization in Electronic System Design &amp; Manufacturing</li>\r\n<li>Information Technology</li>\r\n<li>Mechanical Engineering</li>\r\n<li>Civil Engineering</li>\r\n<li>Electrical Engineering</li>\r\n<li>Automobile Engineering</li>\r\n<li>Petroleum Engineering</li>\r\n<li>Biotechnology</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Important Dates:<br /><br /></strong></p>\r\n<table class="table" border="1">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<p align="center"><strong>S. No</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<p align="center"><strong>Event </strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<p align="center"><strong>Date</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<p align="center"><strong>1.</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<p>Application form availability date</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<p>January 1, 2016</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<p align="center"><strong>2.</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<p>Last date of form availability</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<p>July 31, 2016</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<p align="center"><strong>3.</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<p>Last date of form submission</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<p>July 31, 2016</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<p align="center"><strong>4.</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<p>Shortlisting date</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<p>July 31, 2016</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<p align="center"><strong>5.</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<p>GD/Personal Interview</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<p>May to July, 2016</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<p align="center"><strong>6.</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<p>Final Result Date</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<p>July, 2016</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>', 'news/img/news112.jpeg', 'img/news_b112.jpeg', 'news/php/article.php?id=112', 'graphic era9 b.tech be99 btech admissions private engineering colleges '),
(113, 'JoSAA 2016 announces round 1 seat allocation result on June 30', '<p>Joint Seat Allocation Authority (JoSAA) 2016 has announced the seat allocation result of round one on June 30. Candidates can check JoSAA 2016 round 1 seat allotment result by logging in through their JEE Main 2016 Roll Number and Password.</p>\r\n<p>Acceptance of seats at designated reposting centres is scheduled between July 1 and 5. JoSAA 2016 Seat Acceptance Fee is Rs.45,000 for candidates with the category tag GEN, OBC-NCL or Foreign national and Rs.20,000 for candidates with the category tag SC, ST, GEN-PwD, OBC-NCL-PwD, SC-PwD or ST-PwD. At the time of accepting the seat, a candidate can opt to &lsquo;Freeze&rsquo;, &lsquo;Slide&rsquo; or &lsquo;Float&rsquo; the choice of academic program for subsequent round(s), if any, of Joint Seat Allocation 2016.</p>\r\n<p>The authority, constituted in 2015 with the purpose of reducing the number of seats going vacant in prestigious engineering institutes, is conducting counselling and seat allotment procedure for admissions to as many as 92 participating institutions. The joint body comprising representatives from Central Seat Allocation Board (CSAB) and Joint Admission Board (JAB) has released the round 1 seat allocation result for granting admissions to 22 IITs, ISM Dhanbad, 31 NITs, 20 IIITs and 18 GFTIs after the online choice filling concluded on June 29. <br /> <br />There will be four rounds of JoSAA 2016 Seat Allotment for offering admissions to over 30,000 seats. The seat allocation authority has already announced the seat matrix, mock seat allotment result and other allocation details, including the procedure and schedule. JoSAA will allocate the seats as per the seat matrix data provided by the participating Institutes.</p>', 'news/img/news113.png', 'img/news_b113.jpeg', 'news/php/article.php?id=113', 'josaa '),
(114, 'IPU ADMISSIONS 2016: ROUND 1 SEAT ALLOTMENT RESULT DECLARED', '<p>GGSIPU (Guru Gobind Singh Indraprastha University) has declared the result of 1st Round Seat Allotment for B.Tech course in University Schools &amp; Affiliated Institutes.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Where &amp; How to check</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Go to IPU Admissions website.</li>\r\n<li>Login to your account to check the result</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>WHAT NEXT<br /></strong><br />All the candidates who have been allotted a seat should proceed with paying the part academic fee, failing which the candidate will loose any claim to the allotted seat &amp; the candidate will not be considered further for any subsequent round of online counselling.</p>\r\n<p>Last date for payment of part academic fee is July 1, 2016.</p>', 'news/img/news114.png', 'img/news_b114.jpeg', 'news/php/article.php?id=114', ''),
(115, ' TANCET 2016 Result Announced; Download Marks Sheet!', '<p>Anna University has announced the TANCET 2016 Results on June 30, 2016. The Marks sheet is also available for download for candidates who have qualified in the TANCET 2016 exam. Candidates must download the TANCET 2016 Marks Sheet as it will be required for the counselling to be held through TANCA 2016. Check the details below.<br /><br />Exam: TANCET 2016</p>\r\n<p>Conducted by Anna University</p>\r\n<p>TANCET 2016 Result: <a href="https://www.annauniv.edu/" target="_blank">Click here</a></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Candidates can log in by entering their Email ID and password to access their TANCET 2016 Result.</li>\r\n<li>Their TANCET 2016 Result will be displayed with details of the marks obtained by them in the TANCET 2016 along with details like name, Registration No/ Application No, Category, Qualified or not, qualifying marks etc.</li>\r\n<li>The TANCET 2016 Marks Sheet will also be available and candidates must download this. To download the TANCET 2016 Marks Sheet Click here</li>\r\n<li>They must print this as it will be required to be submitted during the counselling to be held in July 2016 through TANCA 2016</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>TANCET 2016 was conducted on June 12, 2016 for the various M.E and M.Tech courses available across the many engineering institutes and colleges in Tamilnadu. Candidates with valid GATE scores are exempt from the test but the others have to appear for the entrance exam. The TANCET 2016 exam was conducted in 23 papers on June 12, 2016</p>\r\n<p>Counselling will be held in July 2016 through the TANCA 2016 which will be announced shortly by Anna University. Keep watching our website for the latest updates on TANCET 2016 as well as TANCA 2016.</p>', 'news/img/news115.jpeg', 'img/news_b115.jpeg', 'news/php/article.php?id=115', ''),
(116, 'JEE for IIT admissions likely to go international', '<p>Starting next year, the HRD Ministry is planning to conduct IIT entrance exam for undergraduate(JEE Main and Advanced) and postgraduate courses(GATE 2017) abroad to attract foreign students for boosting international rankings.<br /><br /></p>\r\n<p>According to latest information, the IIT Joint Entrance Exam (IIT JEE) is expected to be held simultaneously in 10 countries which includes the seven SAARC nations - Afghanistan, Bangladesh, Bhutan, Nepal, Sri Lanka and the Maldives &mdash; the UAE, Ethiopia and Singapore. However, the Indian security establishment still needs to give its approval for the same. Pakistan has been recently removed from the list of JEE 2017 exam centers.</p>\r\n<p>As part of this initiative, this year, the exam was held across the eight countries.</p>\r\n<p>Until now, first phase of the exam (JEE Main) was being held in West Asian countries like UAE which already has various CBSE-affiliated schools. Moreover, only the Indian expatriate population out there was eligible to take the exam. Infact, to take JEE Advanced, which is the second phase of IIT admissions, aspirants had to come to India.<br /><br /></p>\r\n<p>Commencing from 2017, aspirants across the above mentioned 10 countries will take the exam on the very same day as their Indian counterparts for the first ever.</p>\r\n<p>A senior official from the Ministry was quoted as saying," The Ministry of Home Affairs is looking at the proposal. We have told them that they can scrutinise the students'' backgrounds at the time of application for visa".</p>\r\n<p>If reports are to believed, the test will be conducted and administered by IITs. The seats that would be on offer for foreign nationals will be supernumerary in nature. It would have no effect on the seats that would be available for Indian students. Around 10% of the seats will be reserved for foreign students. Subsequently, as many as 10,000 undergraduate seats are expected to be added to the existing capacity to ensure that Indian students do not lose out.</p>\r\n<p>The outreach programme, which also includes the fee structure for foreign structure, is being anchored by IIT Bombay. Though there is no official information about the exact fee that students would have to shell out, but latest reports indicate that the fee would be far more than Rs 2.5 lakh.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'news/img/news116.jpeg', 'img/news_b116.jpeg', 'news/php/article.php?id=116', ''),
(118, 'BITS Pilani announces BITSAT 2016 Result of Iteration 1 on July 1', '<p>BITS Pilani has announced BITSAT 2016 Result of Iteration 1 on July 1 for admission to integrated first degree programs for the academic year 2016-17. Candidates can check their result by entering BITSAT 2016 hall ticket number and password.</p>\r\n<p><a href="http://projects.bitsadmission.com/FD/FDOFFERPCM/Default.aspx" target="_blank">Click here</a> to check your result now.</p>\r\n<p>The lowest cut-off for admission to any program other than B. Pharm. at the end of iteration 1 is 307. The cutoff for waiting list is 280.</p>\r\n<p>BITSAT 2016 result of 2nd iteration for admission to integrated first degree programs will be announced on July 12 by 5.00 PM.<br /> <br />BITSAT (Birla Institute of Technology and Science Admission Test) 2016 was conducted by Birla Institute of Technology and Science (BITS) from May 14 to 28 for granting admissions to various integrated first degree programmes of engineering. Nearly 2 lakh candidates appeared for BITSAT 2016 and competed for around 2,000 seats available in various BE (Hons.) programmes across its campuses in Pilani, Goa and Hyderabad.</p>', 'news/img/news118.png', 'img/news_b118.jpeg', 'news/php/article.php?id=118', ''),
(119, 'RTU CAM 2016 Application Form Available Now!', '<p>The Rajasthan Technical University has announced that the RTU CAM 2016 Application Form is available now for the M.Tech aspirants of the state. The RTU CAM 2016 Application Form will be available till July 7, 2016 and candidates have to apply online for the M.Tech admissions in the state. The Application fees can be paid online or through E-Mitra. Check the detailed procedure for the RTU CAM 2016 Application Form as well as the other crucial details of the deadlines for the same and eligibility required.<br /><br /></p>\r\n<p>Admission Details of RTU CAM 2016</p>\r\n<p>Conducted by Rajasthan Technical University</p>\r\n<p>Candidates must check the detailed RTU CAM 2016 Eligibility Criteria to endure they meet it before applying. This is important as the responsibility of proving their eligibility will be on the applicants during the RTU CAM 2016 Counselling<br /> <br /><strong>RTU CAM 2016 Application Form:&nbsp;</strong><br /><br /></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Candidates must register giving details of their name, father&rsquo;s name, date of birth and the payment mode.</li>\r\n<li>The payment mode if online or through E-Mitra and the application fees are Rs 3000 (Rs 1500 for SC/ ST candidates) plus service charges extra.</li>\r\n<li>After the payment mode is selected candidates will be directed to their payment receipt which will contain a unique Challan No.</li>\r\n<li>Candidates must note this down for future logins.</li>\r\n<li>Candidates who have opted for E-Mitra payment must print the receipt and pay the fees at the nearest E-Mitra Kendra.</li>\r\n<li>After payment, they will be issued a recipt as well as an unique 12 digit or 16 digit Token No which again has to be kept safe to be used for login.</li>\r\n<li>Candidates paying online must note their transaction ID after payment as this has to be entered in lieu of the Token No while logging in.</li>\r\n<li>After registration, candidates must log in and fill the details, upload a photograph and signature as per specifications and submit the application form.</li>\r\n<li>They must take a printout of the RTU CAM 2016 Application Form for their reference.</li>\r\n<li>They need not send the application form or any documents to the University.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>RTU CAM 2016 Counselling:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Candidates who have registered and filled the RTU CAM 2016 Application Form can fill their choices of courses and institutes till July 4, 2016.</li>\r\n<li>The selection criteria will be valid GATE scores or the performance in the qualifying degree course.</li>\r\n<li>Candidates will have to check their seat allotment as per the specified schedule and report to the allotted college with the specified documents in original along with two sets of the same.</li>\r\n<li>They must pay the admission fees and complete their admission formalities.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Candidates can keep track of the dates for RTU CAM 2016 with the help of the <strong>RTU CAM 2016 Important Dates.</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<table class="table" border="1">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<p><strong>S.no</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<p><strong>Event</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<p><strong>Date</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<p>1</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<p>Notification of Counselling</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<p>May 21, 2016</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<p>2</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<p>Training of Co-ordinators at participating Institutes</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<p>May 18, 2016</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<p>3</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<p>Start of Application Form and application Fee Payment</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<p>May 23, 2016</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<p>4</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<p>Start of Choice Filling</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<p>May 26, 2016</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<p>5</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<p>Last Date for Online Registration and payment by Bank challan/ EMitra</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<p>July&nbsp; 7, 2016</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<p>6</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<p>Last Date for Choice Filling and Automatic Locking of Choices</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<p>July 9, 2026</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<p>7</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<p>First round of Seat Allotment</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<p>July 11, 2016</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<p>8</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<p>First Round for Reporting to Allotted colleges</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<p>July 12 to 15, 2016</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<p>9</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<p>Last Date for withdrawal, Seat surrender as well as last dates for acceptance letter at nodal centres and consent for upward movement</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<p>July 16, 2016</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<p>10</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<p>Second round of Seat Allotment</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<p>July 18, 2016</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<p>11</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<p>Second Round for Reporting to Allotted colleges</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<p>July 19 to 21, 2016</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<p>12</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<p>Third Round- Fresh or Re-Registration and choice filling</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<p>July 19, 2016</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<p>13</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<p>Last Date for registration and choice filling</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<p>July 28 to August 2, 2016</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<p>14</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<p>Third Round of Seat Allotment</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<p>August 3, 2016</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<p>15</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<p>Third Round for Reporting to Allotted colleges</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<p>August 4 to 6, 2016</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<p>16</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<p>Last Date for Withdrawal</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<p>August 8, 2016</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<p>17</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<p>Fourth Round Upward movement allotment</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<p>August 9, 2016</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<p>18</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<p>Fourth Round Reporting to Allotted colleges</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<p>August 10 to 11, 2016</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<p>19</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<p>Commencement of classes</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<p>August 12, 2016</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>', 'img/news119.jpeg', 'img/news_b119.jpeg', '', '');
