(121, 'JoSAA 2016 announces round 2 seat allotment result on July 6', '<p>Joint Seat Allocation Authority (JoSAA) 2016 has announced the seat allotment result of round two on July 6. Candidates can check JoSAA 2016 round 2 seat allotment result by logging in through their JEE Main 2016 Roll Number and Password.</p>\r\n<p><a href="http://josaa.nic.in/" target="_blank">Click here</a> to check your result now.</p>\r\n<p>JoSAA 2016 has also announced the status of vacant seats after round 1. As many as 78 seats remained unfilled across five NITs (home state quota). <a href="http://josaa.nic.in/" target="_blank">Click here</a></p>\r\n<p>Acceptance of seats at designated reporting centres is scheduled between July 7 and 9. Only those candidates, who are allotted seats first time in round 2 and those who have to do dual reporting, must report at the respective reporting centres and accept the seats. JoSAA 2016 Seat Acceptance Fee is Rs.45,000 for candidates with the category tag GEN, OBC-NCL or foreign national and Rs.20,000 for candidates with the category tag SC, ST, GEN-PwD, OBC-NCL-PwD, SC-PwD or ST-PwD. At the time of accepting the seat, a candidate can opt to &lsquo;Freeze&rsquo;, &lsquo;Slide&rsquo; or &lsquo;Float&rsquo; the choice of academic program for subsequent round(s), if any, of Joint Seat Allocation 2016.<br /> <br />The authority, constituted in 2015 with the purpose of reducing the number of seats going vacant in prestigious engineering institutes, is conducting counselling and seat allotment procedure for admissions to as many as 92 participating institutions. The joint body comprising representatives from Central Seat Allocation Board (CSAB) and Joint Admission Board (JAB) has released the round 2 seat allocation result for granting admissions to 22 IITs, ISM Dhanbad, 31 NITs, 20 IIITs and 18 GFTIs.</p>\r\n<p>There will be four rounds of JoSAA 2016 Seat Allotment for offering admissions to over 30,000 seats. The seat allocation authority has already announced the seat matrix, mock seat allotment result and other allocation details, including the procedure and schedule. JoSAA will allocate the seats as per the seat matrix data provided by the participating Institutes.</p>\r\n<p>to check the details.<br /><br /><br /></p>', 'img/news121.jpeg', 'img/news_b121.jpeg', '', ''),
(122, 'SEC announces B.Tech admissions 2016', '<p>Sphoorthy Engineering College (SEC) has announced B.Tech admissions 2016. Candidates are not required to fill &amp; submit any separate application form for admission to the college. Admission to B.Tech courses will be conducted on the basis of candidates&rsquo; score either in JEE Main 2016 or in TS EAMCET 2016. It is must for all the aspiring candidates to qualify the aforementioned exams for admission to Sphoorthy Engineering College. Candidates interested in admission to B.Tech programmes of Sphoorthy Engineering College can check all the details below.<br /><br /><strong>Eligibility Criteria:</strong><br /><br /></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Applicant must be an Indian citizen.</li>\r\n<li>All aspirants must have passed their 10+2 or equivalent examination with Physics and Mathematics as compulsory subjects along with any one of the subjects Chemistry/Biotechnology/Biology/Computer Science.</li>\r\n<li>It is mandatory for all the candidates to appear in any of the two exams: JEE Main 2016 or TS EAMCET 2016.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Programme Profile:</strong></p>\r\n<p><br />Sphoorthy Engineering College (SEC) offers B.Tech Programmes in the following disciplines:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<table class="table" border="1">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<p align="center"><strong>S. No</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<p align="center"><strong>Name of the Course</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<p align="center"><strong>Intake</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<p align="center"><strong>1</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<p>Computer Science &amp; Engineering</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<p>240</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<p align="center"><strong>2.</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<p>Electronics &amp; Communication Engineering</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<p>240</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<p align="center"><strong>3.</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<p>Electrical &amp; Electronics Engineering</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<p>60</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<p align="center"><strong>4.</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<p>Civil Engineering</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<p>120</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<p align="center"><strong>5.</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<p>Mechanical Engineering</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<p>180</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p><br /><strong>Important Dates:</strong><br /><br /></p>\r\n<table class="table" border="1">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<p><strong>Event </strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<p><strong>Date</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<p>Admission Notification Date</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<p>June 29, 2016&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<p>Counselling Date</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<p>July 5 to July 11, 2016&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<p>Result Date</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<p>July 14, 2016&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>', 'img/news122.jpeg', 'img/news_b122.jpeg', '', ''),
(123, 'DU BTech Admissions 2016: Results Postponed Again', '<p>Delhi University was expected to declare the result for the entrance exam conducted by it to offer admission to aspirants in its BTech and B.E. programme on July 4, 2016. But the varsity postponed the results for BTech admissions 2016 at DU colleges and shared that it would be declaring the result on July 6, 2016.</p>\r\n<p>However, on the given day DU issued another notification informing aspirants that the result has been further delayed and candidates should check the official website regularly for further details. DU has not mentioned any date for BTech results 2016 in this new notification.</p>\r\n<p>Also, Delhi University (DU) had earlier informed that the results for BA Hons (Humanities and Social Sciences) entrance exam results would be declared on July 5, 2016. However, the results for this course have also been postponed and at present there is no further notification regarding the resuly date.</p>\r\n<p>Aspirants can check their result for DU BTech admissions on the official website of the varsity. DU will be declaring the BTech result in such a way that the name and roll number of shortlisted candidates will be displayed in a merit list.</p>\r\n<p>Delhi University (DU) recently released a modified answer key for BTech Entrance Exam 2016. In this modified answer key, DU deleted three questions in each of the sets of the entrance test.</p>\r\n<p>DU conducted the BTech Entrance Exam 2016 from June 19 to June 23. Total seats on offer in BTech programmes at DU are as mentioned below:</p>\r\n<table class="MsoTableGrid" style="border: none;" border="1" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style="width: 239.4pt; border-width: 1pt; border-color: windowtext; padding: 0in 5.4pt; background: #92cddc;" valign="top" width="319">\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-align: center;" align="center">Category</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style="width: 239.4pt; border-top-wid