r-left-color: windowtext; border-top-style: none; padding: 0in 5.4pt; background: #daeef3;" valign="top" width="319">\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt;">ST</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style="width: 239.4pt; border-top-style: none; border-left-style: none; border-bottom-width: 1pt; border-bottom-color: windowtext; border-right-width: 1pt; border-right-color: windowtext; padding: 0in 5.4pt; background: #daeef3;" valign="top" width="319">\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt;">3</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style="width: 239.4pt; border-right-width: 1pt; border-bottom-width: 1pt; border-left-width: 1pt; border-right-color: windowtext; border-bottom-color: windowtext; border-left-color: windowtext; border-top-style: none; padding: 0in 5.4pt; background: #daeef3;" valign="top" width="319">\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt;">OBC</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style="width: 239.4pt; border-top-style: none; border-left-style: none; border-bottom-width: 1pt; border-bottom-color: windowtext; border-right-width: 1pt; border-right-color: windowtext; padding: 0in 5.4pt; background: #daeef3;" valign="top" width="319">\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt;">11</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style="width: 239.4pt; border-right-width: 1pt; border-bottom-width: 1pt; border-left-width: 1pt; border-right-color: windowtext; border-bottom-color: windowtext; border-left-color: windowtext; border-top-style: none; padding: 0in 5.4pt; background: #92cddc;" valign="top" width="319">\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-align: center;" align="center">Total Seats</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style="width: 239.4pt; border-top-style: none; border-left-style: none; border-bottom-width: 1pt; border-bottom-color: windowtext; border-right-width: 1pt; border-right-color: windowtext; padding: 0in 5.4pt; background: #92cddc;" valign="top" width="319">\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-align: center;" align="center">40</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>Cluster Innovation Centre, Delhi University offers admission to aspirants in BTech (Information Technology &amp; Mathematical Innovation) course on the basis of their performance in DU entrance exam 2016.</p>', 'img/news123.jpeg', 'img/news_b123.jpeg', '', ''),
(124, 'JoSAA announces 6 rounds of counselling; academic session at IITs to begin from July 22', '<p>Joint Seat Allocation Authority (JoSAA) has announced 6 rounds of counselling and seat allotment for the academic year 2016-17, while the academic session 2016-17 for IIT admissions will begin from July 22. For admission to National Institutes of Technology (NITs), Indian Institutes of Information Technology (IIITs) and Government Funded Technical Institutes (GFTIs), all candidates, who have either accepted or will accept seats, have to report to the respective institutes during July 22 to 26. <br /><br />With the latest announcement, JoSAA 2016 has also made available online seat withdrawal and seat rejection fee refund facility.<br /><br /></p>\r\n<p>The joint counselling authority has released a revised counselling schedule, where it reflects that the ongoing counselling process for admissions to Indian Institutes of Technology (IITs), National Institutes of Technology (NITs), Indian Institutes of Information Technology (IIITs) and Government Funded Technical Institutes (GFTIs) will now be conducted in 6 rounds, till July 20. Joint counselling for admissions to IITs and NIT+System commenced on June 24 with registration and choice filling for academic programmes. JoSAA has already conducted two rounds of seat allotment, where the result for first round of seat allotment was announced on June 30, while the seat allotment result of round 2 was declared on July 6.<br /> <br />Earlier, the counselling authority had announced that JoSAA will conduct counselling and seat allotment in 4 rounds, however JoSAA has now added 2 more counselling and seat allotment rounds. For the academic year 2016-17, JoSAA is conducting joint counselling for B. Tech admissions across 92 participating institutes, which include 22 IITs, ISM Dhanbad, 31 NITs, 20 IIITs and 18 GFTIs. You may also like to know about JoSAA 2016 Reporting Centres.<br /> <br />Last year, counselling for IIT admissions was closed after third round of seat allotment. A fourth round was conducted by JoSAA for admissions to NITs, IIITs and GFTIs only. This was followed by a special round of counselling conducted by CSAB separately for reserved seats other than Open-CRL category. However, for this year, the seat allocation authority has more rounds of counselling for admission to IITs, ISM Dhanbad and NIT+System.</p>\r\n<p>Till 2014, separate counselling was conducted for admissions to IITs and NITs/IIITs/GFTIs. Counselling and seat allotment to IITs and ISM Dhanbad was conducted by Joint Admission Board (JAB) for JEE Advanced qualifiers, while admissions to NITs, IIITs and GFTIs were offered through counselling and seat allotment conducted by Central Seat Allocation Board (CSAB) for JEE Main qualifiers. Joint Seat Allocation Authority (JoSAA) consists of representatives from Joint Admission Board (JAB) and Central Seat Allocation Board (CSAB).</p>', 'img/news124.jpeg', 'img/news_b124.jpeg', '', ''),
(125, 'MHRD to appoint Directors at 12 NITs', '<p>The Ministry of Human Resource Development (MHRD) has invited applications for the post of Director at 12 National Institutes of Technology (NITs). NIT campuses, where the appointments will be conducted include NIT Arunachal Pradesh, Bhopal, Goa, Hamirpur, Meghalaya, Mizoram, Pondicherry, Sikkim, Srinagar, Surathkal, and Uttarakhand.</p>\r\n<p>According to an official notification by MHRD, the applicants should not be more than 65 years of age at the time of registration. Appointment at the post of director at the aforementioned NITs will be done for a tenure of 5 years or till the candidate turns 70, whichever is earlier.<br /><br /><br />The applicants should possess Ph.D Degree with first class masters and bachelor&rsquo;s degree in engineering/technology. Further, they need to have 15 years of experience in teaching/industry/research. Out of the total 15 years of experience, 10 years of experience should be at the level of professor or above in a reputed educational institute, industry and research organisation. In case, a candidate has obtained Ph.D. directly after B.E/B.Tech, then he/she should have obtained first class at undergraduate level of engineering /technology.<br /> <br />Aspirants need to send filled-in applications (complete in all respects in the prescribed format) along with their curriculum vitae by registered\\speed post to Anil Kumar Singh, Under Secretary (NITs), Department of Higher Education, Ministry of Human Resource Development, Room No.523, C &ndash; Wing, Shastri Bhawan, New Delhi &ndash; 110115. Candidates must note that the applications should reach at the aforesaid venue within 30 days of the publication of this official notification in the employment newspapers, together with the vigilance clearance certificate from the parent organisation.<br /> <br />Aspiring candidates employed in government departments, autonomous organisations and public sector undertakings (PSUs), have to send their application forms through proper channel along with vigilance clearance. However, they can also send a copy of their application form in advance directly to the aforementioned address.<br /> <br />There are a total of 31 National Institutes of Technology (NITs), out of which 1, National Institute of Technology, Andhra Pradesh is new. These 31 NITs are institutes of national importance that offer admissions across a total of 17,390 seats for undergraduate engineering programmes.</p>', 'img/news125.jpeg', 'img/news_b125.jpeg', '', ''),
(126, 'JoSAA 2016 announces round 3 seat allotment result on July 10', '<p>Joint Seat Allocation Authority (JoSAA) 2016 has announced the seat allotment result of round three on July 10. Candidates can check JoSAA 2016 seat allocation result of third round by entering their JEE Main 2016 Roll Number and password.</p>\r\n<p><a href="http://josaa.nic.in/" target="_blank">Click here</a> to check your result now.</p>\r\n<p>Acceptance of seats for round 3 is scheduled between July 11 and 13, 2016. Candidates who have been allotted seats in round 3 must report at the reporting centre for seat acceptance. The acceptance fees to be paid by candidates at the time of document verification vary for different categories. Candidates belonging to General, OBC-NCL or foreign national category are required to pay Rs.45,000. Those belonging to SC, ST, Gen-PwD, OBC-NCL-PwD, SC-PwD or ST-PwD are required to pay Rs.20,000. At the time of accepting the seat, a candidate can opt to &lsquo;Freeze&rsquo;, &lsquo;Slide&rsquo; or &lsquo;Float&rsquo; the choice of academic program for subsequent round(s), if any, of Joint Seat Allocation 2016.</p>\r\n<p>There will be total six rounds of seat allotment, out of which the seat allotment result for two rounds has been already declared. Earlier on July 6, JoSAA announced the vacant seat status after round 2 seat allotment. Around 136 seats remained unfilled across 7 NITs after the second round.<br /> <br />JoSAA is a joint seat allotment body comprising members of Central Seat Allocation Board (CSAB) and Joint Admission Board (JAB). The body is conducting counselling for admissions to over 30,000 seats available across 22 IITs, 20 IIITs, 21 NITs, 18 GFTIs and ISM Dhanbad.</p>', 'img/news126.jpeg', 'img/news_b126.jpeg', '', '');
